title: heavenly hash
directions: Drain fruits. Add remaining ingredients. Let stand in refrigerator overnight. Serve.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Make a well in them; add oil, eggs, water and pumpkin.
Mix until smooth.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Divide batter into 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans that are both greased and floured.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add molasses and egg; mix until well blended.
Sift spices and 2 cups of flour together and add to the creamed mixture, alternating with the boiling water.
Add another cup of flour and mix well.
Add remaining 2 cups of flour with the baking soda and the salt.
Stir thoroughly.

title: red punch
directions: Mix all together in punch bowl. Chill before serving.

title: creamy cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour, salt and dry mustard; stir until smooth.
Gradually add Carnation.
Continue cooking over medium heat, stirring, until sauce just comes to a boil. Remove from heat.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Serve hot over your favorite vegetable.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix well.
Drop by spoonful in hot oil.
Cook until brown.

title: 30 minute beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat in large frying pan.
Add water, mushrooms and soup mix.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream grated cheese and margarine.
Sift flour and salt and pepper together.
Add the dry mixture to cheese and margarine. (Use hands or mixer to work until well mixed.) Use pastry tube with "star" plate to make straws.
Bake 12 minutes in a preheated 375° oven.
(Yields approximately 100 three-inch straws; this allows for some broken straws.)

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or in a 9 x 9-inch pan and bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Pour all ingredients in a bowl and mix.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until toothpick tests dry.

title: cherry fruit dessert
directions: Mix above ingredients, except Cool Whip, which is spread on top.
Chill 1 hour.
Serve.
Optional:
Use part of Cool Whip in mixture, if desired.

title: potato soup(lighter eating - 2 points per cup serving)
directions: Spray pan with Pam. Saute potatoes 10 minutes, stirring gently. Add broth and bring to a boil. Prepare gravy mix according to pkg. directions. Add to potatoes and broth. Simmer 20 - 30 minutes.

title: rosemary chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray chicken with cooking spray.
Coat chicken with rosemary on both sides.
Place in a large baking dish.
Toss the potatoes, carrots, onions, garlic and olive oil in a bowl.
Arrange mixture around the chicken.
Cover with foil and bake for one hour or so.
Check to be sure the chicken does not dry out.

title: chocolate chip cinnamon cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat sugar, brown sugar, margarine and egg until light and fluffy.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Stir in flour, rolled oats, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add chocolate chips; mix well. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes or until light golden brown. Cool slightly.
Remove from cookie sheets.
Makes 24 cookies.

title: broiled mushrooms
directions: Wash caps.
Let dry on paper towel.
Combine mayo, cheese and garlic powder.
Mix well.
Fill caps.
Place under broiler 4 inches from flame for approximately 5 minutes.
Done when golden brown and bubbly.

title: cumin meatballs
directions: Puree the tomatoes with their liquid in a food processor. Saute onion, garlic, 1/4 teaspoon cumin and 1/2 teaspoon salt in 1 tablespoon oil until onion is soft.
Add tomato puree and red pepper flakes.
Simmer over low heat partly covered (about 30 minutes).

title: crunchy beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Drain.
Brown the ground beef.
Drain fat.
Combine all ingredients, except onions.
Pour into a 2-quart greased casserole dish.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover.
Top with onions.
Bake 5 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: In a blender, sprinkle gelatin with juice.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes.
Heat milk just to boiling.
Pour into blender.
Add sugar and almond flavoring.
Add 3 cups strawberries and puree. Add 2 more cups strawberries.
Process 2 to 3 minutes on and off motion to slice berries.
Pour into individual parfait glasses or 9-inch French pie plate.
Slice remaining cup of berries.
Arrange over top.
Chill until firm. You can use plain apple juice.

title: cheese squares
directions: Cream margarine, brown sugar and flour; stir in nuts, then set aside 1/2 cup. Press remainder in 8 x 8-inch pan and bake in preheated 350° oven for 12 minutes.

title: spicy oven fried catfish
directions: Move oven rack to slightly above middle of oven.
Preheat to 450°.
Combine cornmeal, bread crumbs, salt, paprika, garlic powder, pepper and thyme.
Dip fish into milk; coat with cornmeal mixture.
Place in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Pour margarine over fish.
Bake, uncovered, until fish flakes with fork (15 to 20 minutes).

title: old fashioned chocolate fudge
directions: Cook cocoa, sugar and milk until soft ball is formed in cold water.
Add butter and remove from heat.
Let stand until nearly cold.
Then add vanilla and beat until it thickens. Pour into a buttered pan. Nuts may be added, if desired.

title: cushaw pie
directions: Cook all the ingredients over low heat until it begins to thicken.
Cool, then pour in an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until edge of pie shell has browned.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix and freeze overnight, making a slush.
Serve in punch cups or small glasses with cocktail straws.
Makes about two punch bowls full.
To make half a recipe, use small frozen fruit cans and 1/2 fifth of rum.

title: orange walnut cake(from florence fabricant in the new york times, 3-1-87.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour a 9-inch spring-form baking pan.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt together and set aside.
Beat the butter and 1 1/3 cups of the sugar together until light, then beat in the eggs.
Add flour alternately with one cup of orange juice.
Fold in the walnuts and orange rind.

title: honey bear brownies
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar in a small bowl.
Blend in honey and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, cocoa and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from edge of pan.
Cool.
Frost, if desired.

title: old fashioned chocolate fudge
directions: Stir over medium heat until chocolate melts and sugar dissolves.
Cook to 234° or until a little dropped in cold water forms a soft ball.
Stir occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add 2 Tbsp. butter.
Cool to lukewarm without stirring.
Add 1 tsp. vanilla.
Beat until thick and no longer glossy.
*See Special Note.
Quickly stir in 1/2 c. nuts.
Pour into buttered 8 x 9-inch inch sq. pan.
When set, cut into squares.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Saute onion and celery.
Combine all ingredients (except noodles) and heat until bubbly hot.
Serve over warmed chow mein noodles.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Saute celery, green pepper, onion and mushrooms in butter for 5 minutes.
Stir in flour, then milk gradually, cooking and stirring until thickened.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Makes 10 to 12 cups.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix first four ingredients and chill.
Prior to serving, layer onion, lettuce, tomatoes and cheese.
Serve with taco chips.

title: caddo relish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Do not boil.
Seal in jar.

title: kringler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut 1/2 cup butter into 1 cup flour. Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons water and mix into a ball.
Divide in half.
Press each half onto ungreased baking sheet, spreading into a rectangle about 6 x 12-inches.
Heat remaining butter and water to boiling.
Remove from heat and stir in almond extract and flour. Stir vigorously until mixture forms a ball (1 minute).
Beat in all eggs at once, mixing until smooth and glossy.
Divide in half; spread evenly over first layer.
Bake 60 minutes or until topping is crisp and brown.
Cool.
Frost with glaze and sprinkle with almonds.

title: home-made "everything" seasoning salt
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Store in a screw-top glass jar.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Mix oil, dill weed, Greek seasoning and Ranch dressing until all is mixed well, then add oyster crackers and mix until all the oil is absorbed.

title: microwave broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in boxes for 7 minutes on High in microwave. Mix broccoli and all other ingredients in casserole.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Cook on High in microwave for 10 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: hot chex party mix
directions: Mix
first
ingredients.
Heat remaining ingredients and pour over dry mixture.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 20 minutes.

title: old fashioned pot roast
directions: In a 6-quart saucepot or Dutch oven, brown roast over medium-high heat.
Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally 2 minutes.
Add beef broth, Worcestershire sauce and bay leaves. Bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, turning occasionally, 1 hour.
Add vegetables and continue simmering covered 1 1/2 hours or until roast and vegetables are tender.
This may be cooked in your oven at 325° to 350°.
If desired, remove roast and vegetables to serving platter and thicken gravy.

title: double chocolate treasures
directions: Heat oven
In a heavy saucepan over low heat, melt 1 cup chocolate pieces.
Stir until smooth; cool slightly.* Beat together margarine and sugar until light and fluffy. Blend in eggs, vanilla and melted chocolate.
Add combined dry ingredients except powdered sugar; stir in remaining chocolate pieces.
Shape dough
into
1-inch
balls;
roll
in powdered sugar, coating heavily.
Place
on an ungreased cookie sheet; bake 10 to
12 minutes.
Cool
minute
on
a cookie sheet; remove to
wire rack.
Store
in
airtight
container.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: broccoli-chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken and broccoli in bottom of a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine salt, mayonnaise, chicken soup, lemon juice and curry powder.
Mix and spread over chicken and broccoli.
Top with Cheddar and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 25 minutes until boiling.
Serves 4.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil 2 minutes the sugar, cocoa, milk and oleo.
Add the oatmeal, vanilla and nuts.
Beat and drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.
Cool.

title: stir-fry
directions: Cut and saute vegetables in canola oil.
Season with Bragg Amenos or soy sauce.
Boil rice sticks in water until soft, like spaghetti noodles.
Serve sauteed vegetables over rice sticks.

title: brown in a bag chicken livers
directions: You will need 1 regular size Brown-in-Bag.

title: brownies
directions: Melt oleo and stir in cocoa.
Mix in next 6 ingredients, one at a time, with a wire whisk.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: baked fudge pudding
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Beat eggs, sugar, flour, salt and vanilla.
Stir in butter and chocolate mix.
Add nuts.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Set pan in a larger pan with hot water, 1/2-inch up.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serve with topping or ice cream if desired.
Delicious by itself.

title: stratta
directions: Break bread into pieces.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cut cheese into cubes and place over bread.
Sprinkle cooked meat over cheese.
Pour margarine over meat. Beat eggs, mustard, salt and milk and pour over casserole. Chill overnight. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until firm.
Great for breakfast.

title: floreine hudspeth's hoosier cake
directions: Place milk and flour in a small, heavy-bottomed pan and whisk vigorously until the mixture is perfectly smooth.
Bring to a boil over moderate heat and boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
The mixture will be very stiff.
Remove from heat and let cool.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt caramels, 1/2 stick butter and 1/2 cup milk.
Mix cake as directed on box and add 1 1/2 sticks butter.
Add 1/2 cup milk. Pour 1/2 batter in pan and bake for 7 minutes, then pour caramel mixture over evenly.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour on rest of batter and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: spoon burgers(like a sloppy joe)
directions: Mix all together.
Simmer 30 minutes.
If too thick, add a little water.

title: sue bee soft 'n chewy popcorn balls
directions: Combine ingredients in pan over low heat until mixture bubbles around edge.
Pour over 10 to 12 cups seasoned popcorn.
Stir and let cool slightly.
Grease hands lightly and form popcorn into balls.

title: texas chili
directions: Brown beef; drain grease.
Mix together all ingredients and cook.
Can add hot peppers, if desired.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Heat water until boiling in covered pot.
Cut potatoes, carrots,
onion and bell pepper in bite-size pieces.
Place in boiling
water with salt and pepper.
Cut broccoli stalks into small
pieces.
Cook
in small
amount of water for 6 minutes. Add remaining
broccoli flowerets and cook another 6 minutes. Add broccoli
to
other pot.
Add margarine.
Bring to a boil and serve.

title: asparagus supreme
directions: Place asparagus in baking dish; sprinkle with next five ingredients.
Drizzle with butter.
Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight for best flavor.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Set aside.
Beat oil, sugar and vanilla in a large bowl with a mixer. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Gradually add flour mixture, beating just until smooth and well blended.

title: thunder pie
directions: Mix the 4 big spoonfuls of applesauce with alot of red food coloring.
Put on the raisins, gummy fish and pretzels, then eat.

title: microwave potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes medium thin and onions in rings.
In microwave dish put single layer of potatoes, then layer of onions.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic salt and dot with butter.
Continue to layer potatoes and onions topped with seasonings and butter to fill dish.
Cover.
Cook on High about 5 minutes.
Test for doneness. Cook about 5 minutes more; test again.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Mix all together.
Put in a well greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes a small 8 x 8-inch pan. Double recipe; bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: reese's cup brownies
directions: Mix brownie mix according to directions.
Pour into muffin cups.
Before you put it in the oven, stick Reeses cups down into batter into each individual brownie.
Bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes.
Kids love these!

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients. Pour into a hot, greased iron skillet.
Top with 1/2 cup grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Super good with homemade vegetable soup.

title: smoky salmon cheese spread
directions: Drain salmon, reserving 2 teaspoons of liquid.
Flake. Combine reserved liquid with salmon, cream cheese, onions and liquid smoke.
Blend thoroughly.
Refrigerate several hours.
Form mixture into a log 6 to 8 inches long; sprinkle with parsley. Makes about 1 1/2 cups.
Serve with crackers.

title: milk rolls
directions: Mix enough flour into milk to make a dough.
Pour on a floured board.
Roll out like a pie crust.
Sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon, raisins and pecans.
Dot margarine over this.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Cut into slices.
Place in baking pan.
Pour about 2 1/2 cups milk over the slices and bake at 450° until brown.
Eat hot.

title: egg custard pie
directions: In a quart measuring cup, add flour, sugar, nutmeg and vanilla.
Add enough milk to make a paste.
Add eggs and beat with electric mixer.
Add enough milk to fill your measuring cup; mix well.
Put in a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firm.

title: italian beef
directions: Cook roast, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Add all other ingredients together and pour over roast.
Cover and cook for 3 1/2 hours at 350°.
Marinate in liquid overnight in refrigerator. Slice the next day and cook in the marinade at 350° until warm.

title: icebox cheese cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Save some for topping.
Pat remainder in bottom of pan.
Put canned milk in large mixing bowl. Put bowl in freezer until milk is freezing around edges of bowl. Dissolve lemon Jell-O in water and lemon juice.
Let cool until almost ready to set.
If Jell-O is too warm, the milk will break down.
Cream together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add to Jell-O mixture.
Beat canned milk on high speed until it forms stiff peaks.
Then add other mixture to whipped milk on low speed. Pour into cake pan.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Chill until firm.

title: sugarless cake
directions: Combine raisins and water and simmer for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Add beaten egg and soft shortening.
Add rolled oats, sweetener and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon and add to top mixture.
Stir well.
Pour into greased one layer cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Test for doneness. Stick toothpick in the center; if it comes out clean, it's done.

title: buffalo chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken in 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Combine chicken and pepper sauce.
Let set 5 minutes, then drain.
In a plastic bag, combine flour and salt.
Add chicken.
Toss until coated.
Heat oil and margarine or butter in a nonstick skillet.
Add chicken, a few at a time.
Cook until golden brown.
Keep chicken warm in oven until finished cooking the rest.

title: hush puppies
directions: Blend ingredients.
Drop by small tablespoons into preheated deep fat.
Cook until brown.
Yield: approximately 30.

title: orange grove muffins
directions: In a bowl, sift together flour, salt, sugar and baking powder. In separate bowl, beat eggs with fork.
Blend in milk, orange juice and melted butter.
Add orange rind and pecans.
Stir liquid mixture into dry ingredients with few strokes.
Mixture will be lumpy.
Do not overbeat.
Spoon batter into well-greased muffin cups.
Mix 1 tablespoon orange rind and 2 tablespoons pecans. Sprinkle a little on top each muffin if desired.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Yield: 1 1/2 dozen.

title: golf balls
directions: Cream margarine and confectioners sugar in bowl until light and fluffy.
Add peanut butter; mix well.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs, pecans and coconut.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler over hot water.
Dip balls into chocolate mixture.
Place on waxed paper.
Let stand until firm.
Yield:
72 servings.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour batter into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cream butter and powdered sugar; add vanilla and salt.
Add flour, 1/4 cup at a time, mixing well.
Mix in chopped walnuts.
Roll into balls about 1-inch in size.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, until set, but not brown.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm and repeat.

title: strawberry balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Shape into small balls and roll in sugar.

title: mom's no work cake
directions: Put all ingredients into bowl.
Mix well with mixer for 3 minutes.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 (9-inch) round pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Check after 40 minutes.
This is an excellent moist, dark chocolate cake.
Top with peanut butter frosting or icing.

title: sandra's french toast delight
directions: Combine the cream cheese, walnuts and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Spread on 6 slices of bread; top with the remaining 6 slices of bread to form sandwiches.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except chips and cheese.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle top with chips and cheese. Return to oven for about 10 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: caramel layers
directions: Combine 2 c. flour, salt, soda, brown sugar and oatmeal.
Cut in with pastry blender.
Reserve 2 cups, press remaining mixture into bottom of greased 12 x 18-inch jellyroll pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Combine caramel sauce with 1/4 c. flour.
Spread over base.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips, then reserved crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 12-15 minutes until delicately browned.

title: country-style yellow squash
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Cover tightly with heavy-duty plastic wrap; fold back a small corner of wrap to allow steam to escape.
Microwave at High for 15 to 17 minutes or until tender.
Drain well; mash squash mixture and set aside.

title: velveeta cheese potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Fry onions and peppers in butter until soft.
Add pimentos and cheese; and over low heat, stir until cheese is melted.
Pour over potatoes and bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: tea sandwiches
directions: Remove crusts; have open or closed.

title: easy summer veggies
directions: Thinly slice potatoes and onion.
Saute in olive oil with garlic.
When potatoes start to soften, add zucchini slices. After 5 minutes, add cubed tomatoes.
Cook until tomatoes start to fall apart.

title: "y" chili
directions: Mash all tomatoes with hands, removing cores.
Add hamburger and mix with hands.
Add water according to thickness of chili desired, approximately 1 gallon.
Salt to taste.
Cook over medium heat approximately 2 1/2 hours.
When water turns chalky white, add 4 full tablespoons of chili powder.
(We used to use Try Me chili powder at the "Y.")

title: spoon bread
directions: Set oven to 375°.
Melt margarine; set aside.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, egg and flour.
Add margarine.
Put in bowl; cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Put in greased muffin pans and bake for 20 minutes.
Dough will keep in refrigerator for 1 week.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix well and put in pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter until soft; add the sugar gradually and continue to cream until the mixture is light and fluffy.
Beat the eggs until they are blended and slightly bubbly.
Add the beaten eggs alternately with the corn syrup to the sugar and butter mixture. Make sure this mixture is thoroughly blended.
Add salt and vanilla flavoring.
Stir in the pecans.
Pour the mixture into the unbaked pie shell.

title: lola's vinegar dumplings
directions: Make dumplings by mixing 1 cup milk and enough flour to make stiff dough.
On floured surface, roll out dough and cut into strips.
When the first 4 ingredients gets to boiling big, drop in the dumplings and cook until dumplings are done.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Press crescent roll dough into bottom and sides of ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and salad dressing mix; spread on crust.
Stir vegetables together; sprinkle over cream cheese and pat lightly.
Sprinkle with cheese. Cut into 1 inch squares, approximately 6 dozen.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix together zucchini, peppers or carrots and salt. Set aside for several hours; then rinse in cold water. Mix together in a large pot the following: sugar, vinegar, nutmeg, black pepper, dry mustard, corn starch, and celery seed. Simmer until very hot and pour over zucchini; seal in jars.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, butter and syrup.
Place pecan halves into bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Pour mixture over top of pecans. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small saucepan, melt 1 cup margarine.
Stir in 1/4 cup cocoa, then water.
Bring to a boil; remove from heat.
In a large bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add cocoa mixture; beat well. Stir in 1/3 cup condensed milk, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into greased 15 x 10-inch jellyroll pan.
Bake for 15 minutes, or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
In small saucepan, melt remaining 1/4 cup margarine.
Stir in remaining 1/4 cup cocoa and sweetened condensed milk.
Stir in confectioners sugar and nuts.
Spread on warm cake.

title: snicker's cake
directions: Prepare cake mix.
Pour 1/2 or little more than 1/2 batter into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: president kennedy's favorite seafood dish
directions: Mix together as making salad and put in low open baking dish. Cook at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: christmas lime jello
directions: Mix dry lime jello with cream cheese until free of lumps. Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Dissolve marshmallows in hot water.
Mix with the lime and cheese mixture.
Drain pineapple and add to mixture.
Put in bowl and let set in refrigerator. After cooling down and before hardening, mix in Cool Whip.
Put in large pan and put in refrigerator until well set.
For best results, make the day before.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer in large bowl as listed.

title: old-fashioned muffins
directions: Beat eggs slightly with fork.
Add milk and oil.
Sift together all the dry ingredients and add to milk mixture.
Mix until flour is moistened.
Batter will be lumpy.
Pour into medium size greased muffin tin, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mary kay's gypsy round-a-layer cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar gradually.
Blend in eggs.
Sift flour, soda, salt and baking powder with the spices and cocoa; then add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Blend in flavoring and nuts.
Pour into two well greased 9-inch cake pans and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sugar cookie
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs.
Then add flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.
Roll out to desired thickness and cut out.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: onion soup
directions: In 4-quart pan over medium heat, melt butter; add onions; cook until tender and golden, stirring occasionally.
Stir in undiluted beef broth, water, sugar, Worcestershire and salt.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 15 minutes. Preheat broiler, place bread on cookie sheet.
Toast both sides. Add cheese to bread and melt in broiler.
Put bread on top of bowl of soup.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Boil sugar, margarine, milk and cocoa for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add chips, vanilla and oatmeal.
Stir until mixed. Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: potluck potato casserole
directions: Place 1/4 cup butter in medium microwave-safe bowl; cover loosely with plastic wrap. Heat on High heat about 50 to 60 seconds or until completely melted. Add undiluted soup, sour cream, onion and salt to butter; mix well. Peel potatoes and cut into 1/2-inch cubes.

title: crispy gingerbread cookies
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar.
Add cinnamon, ginger, cloves and baking soda.
Whip in 1/4 cup of the water and stir in the flour.
Dough should be pliable and easy to roll out.
If the humidity in your area is very low you may need to add more water to keep the dough from being crumbly.
Roll dough out to about 1/4-inch thickness, the thinner the dough, the crisper the cookies.
Cut out cookies in shapes as desired.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hot dog eggwiches
directions: Lightly brown
hot
dog
pieces in butter or margarine. Thoroughly mix
eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour egg mixture over hot dog slices and cook over low heat.
As mixture begins to set at bottom and sides, gently lift cooked portions with a spatula so	that
the
thin, uncooked part can flow to bottom. Avoid constant
stirring.
Cook until eggs are thick but still moist, about
to
minutes.
Spoon
into
buns.
Makes
6 eggwiches.

title: instant baked potatoes
directions: Mix desired amount of ingredients in 6 cups prepared potatoes. Shape heavy-duty foil in boat-like container.
Fill each with 3/4 cup of potato mixture.
Heat 20 minutes on top of grill.
Serve with a pat of butter.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Mix sour cream and soup mix.
Add spinach.
Put in casserole dish and top with grated cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: tomato soup salad
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Add to heated soup along with other ingredients.
Cream cheese may be diced before adding.
Put in bowl and chill.

title: veal-scaloppine marsala
directions: On cutting board, cut veal into 3 x 3-inches.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Coat veal lightly with flour.
In a 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in 3 tablespoons of hot butter or margarine, cook meat a few pieces at a time, until lightly browned on both sides.
Add more butter or margarine as needed.
Remove meat to warm platter as browned.
Into pan drippings, add Marsala wine; cook 1 minute, loosening flour bits.
Pour over veal. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: dilled broccoli salad
directions: Boil broccoli briefly until tender, 2 to 3 minutes. Drain; refresh under cold water and drain again. Place in bowl with other vegetables. Mix sour cream and mayonnaise with dill. Toss with broccoli mixture. Serves 8.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Cream 1/3 of the sugar with oleo and salt in a large bowl. Blend vanilla, 2 tablespoons of milk and remaining sugar into mixture.
Gradually stir in remaining milk until desired consistency.

title: cassava bibingka
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Cook for 15 minutes in a 3-quart saucepan.
Pour dressing over hot drained potatoes.
Add onion flakes, sour cream, mustard and pickles and toss lightly.
Pour into airtight container and marinate overnight.
The next morning, add mayonnaise, chives, pickle juice, celery, eggs and salt. Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
If kept in airtight container in refrigerator, it will keep 5 or 6 days without losing its flavor.

title: quick and easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt frosting in a large bowl in a microwave for 2 1/2 minutes.
Mix in peanut butter and nuts.
Blend in powdered sugar and pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan that has been sprayed with nonstick spray.
Cut in pieces and serve.
Preparation time:
15 minutes.

title: gogi bokum(deep-fried beef slices)
directions: Cut steak into very thin slices and beat them quite flat. Arrange in a single layer on a dish and sprinkle with spring onion, leek and garlic. Mix sugar, soy sauce, sesame oil and chili sauce together.
Spoon over the beef.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Place in small bowl the cream cheese, egg, 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon salt.
Beat well; stir in chocolate chips and set aside.

title: fluffy pink thing
directions: Mix it all up!

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, shortening and salt until it's the texture of cornmeal.
Add milk and vinegar.
Put vinegar in milk.
Will keep for weeks in refrigerator in covered container.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt margarine and allow to cool slightly.
Add sugar and salt.
Beat egg until frothy, then add to mixture.
Add vinegar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour in pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: easy hot fudge sauce
directions: Using a heavy bottom pan, mix over very low heat the sugar and cocoa for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add milk and margarine; stir over low heat for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fried turkey
directions: Combine dressing, butter and spice.
Inject bird with the mix. Fry 4 to 5 minutes per pound in peanut oil heated to 350° to 375°.

title: unbelievable never fail sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Buy pre-made meatballs from grocery store.
Heat meatballs in pan on stove.
Add chili sauce and grape jelly.
Continue to simmer.
Enjoy the best ever sweet and sour meatballs.

title: tootsie's meatballs
directions: Add beaten eggs to meat and mix.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Brown in 325° oven on greased cookie sheet for 30 minutes.
Makes approximately 60 meatballs.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Boil potatoes until easily pierced by fork.
Place cooked potatoes in large mixing bowl and beat until smooth.
Stir in butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add spices, salt and Pet milk.
Bake 70 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Steam and drain shrimp.
Cut shrimp in medium pieces.
Stir mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Add celery and onion.
Stir in shrimp.
Shake in Crazy salt.
Let sit for at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: italian sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together with your hands and roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm.
Once sampled, they go like crazy.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. In saucepan, melt butter, add onion and bell pepper and saute 5 minutes.
Blend in flour and seasonings; add milk and cook and stir until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in olives, hominy and sausage.
Pour into prepared dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake 30 minutes or until well browned.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter and chocolate. Add sugar, cream, corn syrup and vanilla. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil for 1 1/2 minutes. Remove from the heat. Serve warm or cold over ice cream or pound cake. Refrigerate leftovers. Yield: about 3 1/2 cups.

title: prune whip
directions: Whip the egg whites until stiff, gradually adding the sugar while beating continuously. Fold in prunes, pitted and chopped, and continue beating until light. Turn into a buttered baking dish (1 1/2-quart) and bake in a moderate over (350°) for about 15 minutes. Serve warm with soft custard (made from the egg yolks) or with cream. Serves 3 or 4.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Combine flour, sugar and milk.
Melt butter in baking dish. Pour in flour, sugar and milk mixture.
Do not stir!
Add fruit. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Beat all ingredients, but shrimp, until blended and smooth. Add shrimp.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Let dip set a minimum of 2 hours before serving to blend flavors.

title: oyster stew
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan.
Add oysters (with liquor); cook and stir over low heat just until edges curl.
In another saucepan, heat milk and cream.
Stir in salt, pepper and oysters. Makes 4 servings (1 cup each).

title: hayla's pecan pie
directions: Beat egg and sugar together.
Add butter, corn syrup, vanilla, pecans, and salt.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 350 for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Saute bacon in a deep kettle, stirring occasionally. Stir in dried thyme and onions. Cook, stirring occasionally until tender. Add potatoes and next four ingredients. Cover and simmer 5 minutes. Add the tomatoes and clam liquid. (If you don't have 3 cups of clam liquid, add water to make up the difference.)

title: sloppy joes
directions: Grill onion and garlic in tablespoon of oil. Add meat and cook until done. Add tomato sauce and ketchup. Heat until boiling. Toast buns and place sauce on buns.

title: pink witch punch
directions: Blend milk, lemonade and strawberry ice cream with beater. Add ginger ale.

title: chicken divine
directions: Brown chicken parts until almost done.
Butter 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put broccoli in bottom of dish.
Add chicken on top. Mix soup, mayonnaise and curry powder.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Top with grated cheese and crushed cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: beef and bean casserole
directions: Brown beef.
Add pork and beans, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar and salt to taste.
Heat in oven at 325° to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pegliarni
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper; drain.
Mix other ingredients with the beef mixture.
Top with 1/2 pound grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: gnocchi parisian style
directions: Prepare sauce in a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat.
Melt butter or margarine, cook onion until tender.
Stir in flour, cook 1 minute.
Stir in half and half and chicken broth, cook, stirring, until thickened.
Remove pan from heat, stir in Swiss cheese and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and eggs, 1 at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake in greased, floured pan for 1 hour and 25 minutes at 325°.

title: easy creamy peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla and peanut butter; mix until creamy.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese.
Add sugar and nuts.
Fold in Dream Whip.
Pat ingredients in baked pie shell.
Top with 1/2 can blueberry pie mix.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan; stir in flour.
Mix in liquids and seasonings.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Add chicken, peas and almonds.
Continue cooking until heated through.
Serve hot in patty shells or over biscuits.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Add sugar gradually to beaten eggs; continue to beat until mixture is very stiff.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into can and freeze as directed.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, vegetables, soup and put in a casserole. Sprinkle cheddar cheese over mixture. Pour flour, milk, and oil over this AFTER MIXING these together. DO NOT COVER!!

title: plain baked custard
directions: Scald milk.
Mix sugar, eggs, salt and flavoring and combine with scalded milk.
Pour into custard cups or baking dish.
Set in a pan of boiling water and poach in a slow oven (300°) until firm.
A knife blade run into the center of custard should come out clean (30 to 35 minutes if in cups).

title: baked eggplant
directions: Slice eggplant thin long ways.
Saute eggplant 30 to 45 seconds in vegetable oil.
Let cool.
Mix Ricotta, basil, salt, pepper and egg together.
Lay ham on eggplant, then add spoonful of mixture on ham.
Roll eggplant up.
Bake in 350° oven until center is hot.
Use nonstick pan or add water to pan. Add tomato sauce on top to finish.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix onions with squash.
Cook 5 minutes.
Drain liquid except small amount.
Add sour cream and chicken soup to squash.
Stir well.
Add package of dressing to melted margarine.
Place 1/2 of dressing in bottom of deep casserole dish.
Spread evenly.
Pour in squash mixture.
Place remaining dressing on top of squash. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Mix cake as calls for and bake in two 8-inch round pans.
Make pudding.
Crush Heath bars and mix in separate bowl with Cool Whip.
Make sure cakes are thoroughly cooled.

title: russian chicken
directions: Rinse skinless chicken and pat dry.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In a bowl, mix dressing, preserves and onion soup mix.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° (uncovered) for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until done.

title: m&m's chip-po cookies
directions: Cream
margarine, add sugar and brown sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in beaten eggs and vanilla.
In large bowl, combine crushed potato chips, oatmeal, flour and baking soda; add to sugar mixture and mix well.
Fold in M&M's.
Bake at
on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let set
1 minute before removing from pan.
Makes approximately 6 to 7 dozen cookies.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef, garlic and onion.
Drain.
Add tomato paste, tomatoes, salt, pepper, oregano, basil, parsley flakes and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook together and simmer 15 minutes.
Cook lasagna noodles.
Add salt and oil to water.
Grease pan.
Layer noodles, meat sauce, cheese, noodles, meat sauce and cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: country style chile sauce
directions: Combine tomatoes, peppers, onion, celery, hot pepper, garlic, vinegar, salt, both sugars and corn syrup in a large kettle. Bring to boiling.
Lower heat and simmer, uncovered, stirring once in a while for 1 hour.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix dry ingredients (except additional flour).
Add egg and oil; mix well.
Put wooden skewer in end of frankfurters; coat with additional flour, then dip into corn meal batter.
Fry in deep, hot oil until golden brown.

title: chicken corn chowder(makes 6 servings)
directions: Combine flour and 2 tablespoons fajita seasoning in a heavy-duty zip-top plastic bag. Add chicken; seal and shake to coat. Cook chicken in hot oil in a large Dutch oven over high heat, stirring often, 4 minutes or until browned. Reduce heat to medium-high. Add onion and garlic; saut 5 minutes. Stir in remaining fajita seasoning, corn, next 5 ingredients, and if desired, olives. Bring mixture to a boil. Reduce heat to medium-low, cover and simmer 5 minutes. Remove lid and stir in nacho cheese soup, chopped cilantro and lime juice. Garnish, if desired, and serve with breadsticks, if desired. Prep: 15 minutes. Cook: 15 minutes.

title: greek chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter in large pan. Add chicken breasts mixed with Greek seasoning. Brown chicken breasts and simmer until hot. Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and set aside. Using the same pan, saute bell pepper, celery, onion and garlic until tender, about 2 minutes. To this mixture, add rice and remaining ingredients. Mix together and pour evenly over chicken. Bake, covered, in a preheated oven at 400° for 45 minutes. Garnish and serve. Serves 4.

title: german apple pancakes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Put two 9-inch round cake pans in oven to heat up.
Beat eggs, flour, milk and salt in small mixer bowl on medium speed for 1 minute.
Remove pans from oven and put 2 tablespoons margarine in each pan, rotating until margarine is melted and coats sides.
Arrange half of apple slices in each pan. Divide batter between pans covering apples.
Mix sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over batter in each pan.
Bake uncovered until puffed and golden brown.

title: italian beef
directions: Cook roast; cool and slice thinly.
To drippings in pan, add water and bouillon cubes.
Add seasonings, garlic and green pepper. Simmer 15 minutes.
Add sliced beef and marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Heat and serve.

title: crab meat delight
directions: Mix ingredients in a small bowl.
Slice bread and spread sparingly of mixture.
Broil until brown.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water until tender, but not mushy. Drain; set aside.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer for a few minutes.

title: lemon cake
directions: Beat butter until creamy. Add sugar slowly and mix well. Add eggs one at a time. Mix in sifted dry ingredients. Add milk. Mix in flavoring. Pour into three cake pans, 3x8 inch or 2x9 inch and bake at 375°.

title: carolyn's beans
directions: Brown bacon, ground beef and onion.
Drain all of these ingredients and put into large baking pot or slow cooker.

title: ham and sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine cornstarch and apple juice in small saucepan.
Mix well.
Add raisins.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add brown sugar, lemon juice, mustard and pepper.
Stir until smooth.

title: homemade barbecue sauce
directions: Chop all bacon and onion into small pieces.
Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan and simmer on low heat for 6 to 8 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Mix in oblong pan with other ingredients. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello with hot water.
Add pineapple (juice included) and frozen strawberries.
Pour this mixture into a 9 x 12-inch container.
Let mixture congeal.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oatmeal and oleo.
Let stand for 20 minutes, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and butter.
Pour over rice.
Put frozen broccoli in buttered 13 x 9-inch dish.
Combine water and milk.
Pour over rice on top of broccoli, then put onion and butter on top of rice. Put cheese on top of rice.
Dilute mushroom soup a little.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered with tinfoil.
Remove last 5 to 7 minutes.
Toss lightly.
Put onion rings on last 2 minutes.

title: upside-down shepherds pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Spray 1 1/2 quart ceramic or glass baking dish or deep dish pie plate.
Press cold mashed potatoes onto bottom and up sides of casserole.
Bake potato crust 20 minutes or until edge is golden.
Meanwhile, brown ground beef. Drain. Melt butter in pan used for beef.
Add onions and cook 6 - 7 minutes.
Return beef to skillet reducing heat.
Stir a ketchup and dried dill.
Reduce heat to low, stir in parsley and sour cream.
Spoon ground beef mix into mashed potato crust. Garnish with springs of dill weed.

title: seven minute pickles
directions: Boil ingredients for 2 minutes.
Add cucumbers and boil 7 minutes.
Put in pint jars and process in boiling bath water for 5 minutes.

title: fruit tea
directions: Cook tea and 1 pint of water for 3 boiling minutes.
Remove tea bags and add the rest of water and remaining ingredients in a gallon container.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Take tubes of crescent rolls and press into cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Cool.
Mix remaining ingredients except vegetables.
Put mixture on cooled crust and chill.
On top of this, put diced vegetables.
You can use radishes, broccoli, onion or cauliflower.
(I use all 4.)
Some use tomatoes, but they are a little juicy.
Slice and serve.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain off excess grease.
Mix in the other ingredients.

title: cinnamon bubble bread
directions: Place frozen bread in refrigerator overnight to thaw.
Cut into cubes and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix other ingredients and pour over cubes.
Let rise.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: potato candy
directions: Peel potatoes; mash in a large mixing bowl.
Add vanilla and enough sugar to make the consistency of dough.
Roll out on wax paper.
Spread generously with peanut butter.
Roll into a log. Chill for several hours.
Slice and store in refrigerator or freezer.

title: refrigerator sweet cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm (110°) water.
Combine and beat next 6 ingredients.
Cover with damp cloth; put in refrigerator 2 hours or overnight.
Divide dough in half, roll in rectangle and brush with melted butter.
Combine 1 cup sugar, cinnamon and raisins and sprinkle over dough.
Roll up jelly-roll style.
Cut and put in greased pans.
Cover for about 1 hour or until double in size. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Glaze with powdered sugar and milk.

title: toasted coconut cake
directions: See Filling instructions before mixing.

title: sloppy joes for a crowd
directions: Brown ground beef, drain fat.
Add the next seven ingredients; simmer or cook in a large crock-pot or roaster for 1 hour (longer for crock-pot).
Stir occasionally.
Serve on buns.
Makes about 50 servings.

title: eagle brand milk substitute recipe
directions: Blend powdered milk and sugar in blender.
Add melted butter and hot water.
Blend well.
Use when recipe calls for 1 can Eagle Brand milk or 1 can sweetened condensed milk.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Mix all together.
Add cubed cheese (Velveeta or Mozzarella). Serve on hamburger buns.
Keep in refrigerator up to 2 weeks. Freezes well.

title: ham and cheese ball
directions: Shape deviled ham into a ball.
Mold cream cheese around ham ball.
Roll in Cheddar cheese.
Chill, wrapped in plastic wrap, until serving time.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Yields 10 servings.

title: swiss cabbage
directions: Quarter cabbage; cook in salted water until crispy tender (8 to 12 minutes); drain.
In saucepan, melt oleo.
Add carrots and celery; cook until tender.
Remove from heat; stir in flour and add milk.
Cook until mixture boils and thickens slightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Pour over cabbage.

title: fresh mountain apple cake
directions: Beat eggs in beater.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla; mix well. Blend dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Beat well.
Add apples and nuts. Stir.
Pour into greased Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Ice.

title: white cake
directions: Sift flour and baking powder together.
Cream butter and sugar; add flour and water alternately to sugar mixture; add vanilla; fold in egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in three 8-inch pans.

title: bacon water chestnuts
directions: Cook bacon until soft.
Wrap around chestnuts and secure with toothpicks.

title: seafood mold
directions: Heat soup and V-8 juice with cream cheese, stirring until the cheese is melted.
Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup of water and then dissolve in hot soup mixture.
Stir in green pepper, celery, minced onion and scallions; chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in mayonnaise, lemon juice, avocados and crab or shrimp.
Pour into a mold that has been rinsed in cold water.
Chill until set. Unmold on a chilled serving dish.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Mix in beans, tomato paste and 1/2 package taco seasoning.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Mix remaining taco seasoning with sour cream.
Spread over meat mixture.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes and cheese.
Chill.
Serve with taco chips.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cheese until light and fluffy.
Add salt and vanilla; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in flour.
Blend well.
Spoon in greased and floured tube pan, then bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry pie(shoney's)
directions: Cook sugar,
water and cornstarch until clear.	To this mixture, add jello and
stir well.	Let cool and pour over pie shell filled with strawberries.
Cover with whipped cream.

title: baked chicken with rice
directions: Melt the oleo in casserole.
Stir the remaining ingredients, except chicken, together.
Place chicken pieces in casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until chicken is tender.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients to hard crack stage, then add the peanuts, salt, 2 teaspoons soda and butter.
Stir until it changes color.
Add 1/2 teaspoon (heaping) soda.
Stir and pour into buttered pan.
Let harden and break into pieces.

title: aunt dorothy's scrumptious carmelcorn
directions: In 2 1/2 quart saucepan; combine sugar, corn syrup, butter, cream of tartar and salt.
Heat to boiling point.
Stirring constantly, boil to hard ball stage.
(Note:
I don't ever boil to hard ball stage, but just until it forms a good soft ball in water).
Remove from heat, stir in baking soda; quickly and thoroughly pour at once over popcorn in large pan.
(I use canning kettle).
Stir until all is coated.
Bake in preheated oven (200°) for 1 hour; stirring every 15 minutes during the baking.
Turn out at once on waxed paper, spread apart and allow to cool completely. Break apart and store in tight container.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: monica's chili
directions: Cook ground beef until brown.
Drain grease.
Add all ingredients and simmer approximately 3 hours.
Makes 4 servings.

title: d.j.'s noodle salad
directions: Cook noodles until done, drain.
Wash noodles with cold water until cool, then drain.
Set aside noodles.
In separate bowl, dice the tomatoes, and add balsamic vinegar, olive oil, salt and pepper. Pour 1 cup of the cheese into mixture.
Pour mixture over noodles; stir.
Pour into serving dish; sprinkle the remainder of cheese over the top of the salad.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute onion or cook with squash.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 6 ovenproof custard cups.
Stir flour and salt together in mixing bowl.
Add eggs and milk.
Beat mixture with mixer until smooth.
Do not overbeat.
Fill custard cup 3/4 full.
Bake until puffed and brown, about 30 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 15 minutes.
Remove from custard cups and serve immediately.
Fill with butter, fruit, jelly, custard or pudding.
Can use muffin tins.
Makes 6.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Tear angel food cake into pieces into a 9 X 13 cake pan.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Spread over angel food cake.
Mix glaze and strawberries.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Put in refrigerator and cool.

title: chili beef casserole
directions: Peel and chop onion.
Rinse peppers and cut in halves.
Remove the seeds and membranes and cut in strips.
In a skillet, saute the onion and peppers in butter until soft, but not brown. Add ground beef and saute over medium heat, stirring until meat is lightly brown. Drain beans and corn.
Add to pan. Add salt, chili powder, basil and garlic.
Cook, uncovered, 6 to 8 minutes. Finally add olives and parsley. Serve immediately.

title: butterscotch cheesecake
directions: Melt margarine and butterscotch chips.	Mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Press half of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: hungry boy's casserole
directions: Saute, in skillet, beef, onion, green pepper and salt until vegetables are tender; drain.
Add water and tomato paste. Reserve 1 cup for biscuits.
Add beans.

title: nibblin' fish
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Spread on shallow pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: skillet peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in your electric skillet.
Set at 280°.
Bring to boil and boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Add remaining ingredients.
Turn into buttered 8-inch or 9-inch square pan and cool before cutting into squares.
Makes about 2 pounds.
Store in covered tin.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice until done.
Melt in saucepan the Cheez Whiz, soup and butter.
Mix into broccoli and rice until well coated.
Pour into glass baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Add Cheddar cheese on top, if desired.
Cook until cheese melts and top is golden brown.

title: pineapple mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup of boiling water.
Add sour cream; stir.
Add pineapple with juice.
Stir with mixer until real blended.
Pour into mold and leave in refrigerator for 2 days before serving.

title: buttermilk rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients except flour in large bowl.
Stir until yeast is well dissolved.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough. Stir well and knead.
Make into rolls.
Place in greased pan. Brush tops with butter.
Let rise about 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for approximately 10 to 20 minutes, or until light brown.

title: creamy chicken broccoli bake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until chicken is cooked through. Serves 6.

title: creamy corn
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake at 350° until done, approximately 40 minutes.

title: crab mushroom cheese quiche
directions: Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid.
Saute mushrooms in butter 2 minutes.
Scatter in pie shell.
Remove any membrane from crabmeat. Scatter crabmeat and cheese over mushrooms.
Mix sour cream and mayonnaise with saved mushroom liquid, salt and flour.
Add enough light cream to mixture to make 2 cups.
Blend in eggs and hot pepper sauce and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until set.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan on medium heat.
Add sugar, cocoa and milk.
Turn heat to high and stir constantly until mixture comes to a full, rolling boil.

title: speedy caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan; blend in the brown sugar and salt.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put corn flakes on top and pour the butter on top of these.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: carrot travelers
directions: Cream in order. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. (Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet; flatten slightly.)

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating each egg into creamed mixture well.
Add flour.
Beat well after each cup.
Beat in vanilla and 7-Up.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured jumbo tube pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.

title: ripe olive tamale pie casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in 2 tablespoons oil.
When meat is almost cooked, stir in chopped onion and cook until onion is transparent. Add tomatoes, corn, chili powder and salt.
Heat to boiling. Slowly stir in corn meal.
Cook over low heat 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking.
Add the olives; stir into tamale mixture and turn into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake in moderate oven, 250°, for 30 to 40 minutes. Serves six.

title: butternut squash praline casserole
directions: Combine squash, 4 tablespoons butter, salt and pepper in saucepan. Cook over low heat until squash is hot, stirring frequently.
Add squash to eggs, mixing well.
Pour squash into greased 1-quart casserole. Combine brown sugar, cinnamon, butter and pecans. Sprinkle praline mixture over squash.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Yields 6 servings.

title: no bake peanut butter bars
directions: Combine all ingredients into large mixing bowl; stir until mixed thoroughly.
Grease a Pyrex dish, 13 x 9-inch.
Pour mixture into greased Pyrex dish; pat into dish.
Chill until firm. Sprinkle top with brown sugar or top with icing or chocolate Cool Whip.
Cut into desired amounts.

title: easy salad
directions: Mix all together.
I always slice grapes in half.
Chop apples size of croutons.
Slice bananas.
Serve on bibb lettuce for ladies' luncheon.
Top with 1/2 cherry.

title: seven layer refrigerator salad
directions: Shred lettuce in a medium sized bowl with a tight fitting lid.
Mix together onion, celery, and bell pepper.
Place these is a layer on top of lettuce.
Add English peas as next layer.
Beat mayonnaise and sugar together, spread on top of English pease. Sprinkle bacon bits on top of mayonnaise.
sprinkle cheese on top. Cover tightly and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: plentiful potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Toss gently.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together lightly and pile into 2-quart shallow baking dish or a 13 x 9-inch dish.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Melt margarine; add sugar, beaten eggs, pineapple and coconut. Pour into 1 large deep dish uncooked pie shell or 2 regular sized uncooked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, until set.

title: hot fruity sipper
directions: In a large saucepan, combine water and tea bags.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and cover.
Steep 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer over low heat 15 minutes or until hot.
Yields 5 (1 cup) servings.

title: boneless steak or shortribs
directions: Cut steak or ribs in oblong shape.
Flour meat and brown in oil. Put in crock-pot with water and au jus mix.
Simmer 4 to 6 hours or until meat is tender.
May also use pork chops and/or barbecue sauce.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Press crescent rolls into a jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool crust.
Mix together Miracle Whip, Hidden Valley Ranch dressing and cream cheese.
Spread on crust.
Top with vegetables and grated cheese (can use any raw vegetable). Refrigerate.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: no-roll peach cobbler
directions: Mix sliced peaches with 1 cup sugar; set aside.
Heat oven to 350°.
Place butter in a 2-quart baking dish.
Set in oven to melt butter.
Combine remaining 1/2 cup sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk; pour over melted butter, but do not stir.
Put sugared peaches on top of batter, again without stirring.
Bake for about 1 hour, until batter has risen to top and is crisp and brown.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add to boiling water.
Stir over medium heat until thickens.
Add butter and vanilla.
Serve hot.
Can be stored in refrigerator and served later.
Great over homemade ice cream!

title: healthy soup
directions: In a medium size pot put all ingredients and bring to boil; then reduce heat to medium heat and cook, covered, about 30 minutes.
You may cook longer if you like your vegetables softer.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender. Blend until well mixed. Serve immediately.

title: aunt alice's spaghetti
directions: Brown beef; take off grease.
Add onion, bacon, tomato soup, tomato sauce, tomato paste, cheese, salt and pepper.
Cook elbow macaroni.
Mix with beef mixture and pour into casserole.
Bake in oven at 350° for one hour.

title: chocolate chip apple cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, water and vanilla. Sift together all dry ingredients.
Beat dry ingredients into soft ingredients.
Stir in apples and chocolate.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Cool and eat!

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender, then pour off water.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl.
Pour over carrots; mix well.
Chill.
Let carrots marinate several hours before serving.
When ready to serve, heat in oven or on stove.

title: taco burger
directions: Simmer
ground
beef
until
almost done.
Drain excess grease.
Add onion and garlic and finish cooking.
Add rest of ingredients
and simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Add water as needed to help blend flavors.
After 30 minutes, cook, uncovered, if needed, to remove excess moisture.

title: stuffed fresh mushrooms
directions: Wash and scoop out mushrooms.
Blend remaining ingredients. Fill mushroom caps with cheese and clam mixture.
Place filled mushroom caps under broiler until bubbly.

title: savory baked fillet of sole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place fish on well-greased baking dish. Sprinkle with lemon juice and pepper.
Fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Combine bacon with breadcrumbs and parsley.
Set aside.
Remove all but 2 tablespoons of bacon drippings from the pan.
Saute the onion slices until tender.
Spread onions over fish.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over onions.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: pinch-me-cake
directions: Mix together sugar, butter or margarine and vanilla.
Bring to a rolling boil.
In a plastic bag, combine cinnamon and sugar. Cut biscuits into 1/4 pieces.
Shake biscuit pieces in bag to coat with cinnamon-sugar.
Spray a Bundt pan with Pam; place coated biscuit pieces in pan, alternating with hot sugar-syrup mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until biscuit pieces are done. (Excellent breakfast cake.)

title: hungarian swiss steak
directions: Cut beef into 4 serving pieces. Sprinkle both sides of beef with seasoned salt. Spray 12 inch nonstick skillet with nonstick cooking spray; heat over medium high heat. Cook beef in skillet 4 to 5 minutes, turning once, until brown. Stir in tomatoes, paprika, ketchup and caraway seeds; reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until beef is tender. Top each serving with sour cream and chives. This has 8 grams carbohydrates.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Mix sugar,
flour
and salt in mixing bowl.
Mix cocoa, water and margarine
in
pan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Stir well and add buttermilk, eggs and soda plus vanilla.
Pour
in greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: parmesan oven-fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400° (moderately hot).
Coat chicken with mixture of flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Dip in mixture of eggs and milk which has been slightly beaten.
Roll in Parmesan cheese and bread crumb mixture.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Melt butter and oil in shallow baking pan in heated oven.
Place coated chicken, skin-side down in pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
Turn skin-side up and continue baking until tender, about 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Stir all ingredients in saucepan.
Bake in greased baking pan for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza bread appetizers
directions: Beat together egg, oregano and parmesan cheese.
Roll dough into two 8 x 14 inch rectangles.
Spread egg mixture on the dough, reserving 3 Tbsp.
Layer pepperoni and provolone cheese on top. Roll dough jelly-roll style.
Place seam-side down on a greased baking sheet and seal the ends.
Brush with reserved egg mixture. Bake in 350 oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Slice for appetizers size. Serve plain or with marinara sauce.

title: shrimp a la newburg
directions: Cut the shrimp into small pieces; heat in the butter with salt and a shake of paprika to taste.
Add the lemon juice.
Remove the shrimp from the pan.
When slightly thickened, add the beaten egg, return the shrimp to the mixture and cook one minute.

title: spice of christmas life (not punch)
directions: In basket of coffee percolator, put first 4 ingredients.
In the pot, put last 3 ingredients.
Perk.

title: candied dill pickles
directions: Pour off liquid; slice pickles. Add sugar, vinegar and spices. Let set overnight and stir. Refrigerate 2 days before eating.

title: amazing apricot pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate, place all ingredients except preserves in blender.
Cover and blend about 1 minute or until smooth.
Pour into plate (pie).
Bake about 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely. Heat preserves over low heat until melted.
Spread over pie; cool. Garnish with whipped cream, if desired.

title: snax
directions: Melt butter, fat, peanut butter, Accent, garlic salt and Tabasco sauce in pan.
Pour melted sauce over cereals and nuts. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 200°.
Stir every 15 minutes while baking.
These get better with age.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Cream butter with sugar and salt.
Add vanilla, then sifted flour and pecans.
Press mixture through cookie press (or shape into 1-inch balls).
Place on slightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 250° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: orange sauce meat balls
directions: Combine egg, bread crumbs, cloves, cinnamon and salt in a large bowl.
Add meat and currants.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven 15 to 18 minutes or until no longer pink.
Mix orange juice, cornstarch, honey and soy sauce.
Cook until thick.
Cook and stir 2 more minutes.
Place meat balls in a chafing dish.
Pour sauce over meat balls.
Serve warm.
Makes 32.

title: baked beans
directions: Drain canned beans.
Cook onion and pepper in 2 tablespoons oil or bacon drippings.
Add to beans with Ro-Tel tomatoes and canned tomatoes.
Add a clove of garlic if you like.
Place in a baking dish.
Place strip of bacon on top.
Bake about 350° until brown on top about 45 minutes.

title: cuban chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place potatoes in saucepan; cover with water and boil for 10 minutes.
Put margarine and olive oil in shallow baking pan and place in oven until margarine melts.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together
and bake in loaf pan at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: strawberry angel delight
directions: In large glass dish (13 x 9-inches), crumble cake (pack tightly).
In bowl, dissolve Jell-O in hot water and stir.
Add sugar and strawberries.
Pour mixture over crumbled cake evenly. Spread Cool Whip over entire surface and refrigerate overnight (or at least 6 hours until set).
Cut in squares and serve.
Makes 20 squares.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll and place in refrigerator overnight.
Slice and bake in moderate oven at 350° until done.

title: tutti-frutti
directions: Empty can of crushed pineapple in a bowl.
Pour package of pistachio pudding over pineapple and mix together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Enjoy!

title: shrimp ball
directions: Leave cream cheese out for 2 hours to soften.
Prepare the chopped celery and onion.
Combine the first 5 ingredients in a large bowl, then add shrimp.
Form the mixture into a ball or other shape.
Refrigerate overnight or longer.
Use within 3 days.
Spread on a variety of crackers.

title: glazed orange cake
directions: Juice the orange; add 1/2 cup sugar.
Set aside.
Grind orange rind and pulp with the raisins.
Cream together sugar, eggs, butter and sour milk.
Add the orange rind mixture.
Sift soda with flour and fold into mixture.
Pour into a lightly greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
Pour orange juice and sugar mixture over hot cake.
Good served with whipped topping.

title: remoulade sauce for shrimp and crab(my favorite - and dan's - for lump crab meat cocktails!!)
directions: In large electric food blender, put all ingredients to blender, 3 or 4 items at a time, mixing in blender as you continue to add each additional series of ingredients.
Do not add hard-boiled eggs until all other ingredients have been blended together.
Chop hard-boiled eggs and fold into mixture by hand. Yields 2 quarts.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Lightly fry tortillas to soften, one at a time.
Fill each with 2 tablespoons cheese and a sprinkle of onion. Roll and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt butter.
Blend in flour. Add chicken broth, stirring constantly, until thickened. Stir in chicken, sour cream, bell pepper and jalapenos.
Pour sauce over tortillas.
Bake at 375° until sauce is bubbling.

title: old fashioned crumb cake
directions: Heat milk, sugar, shortening, and salt in saucepan over medium heat, just until shortening is melted.
Let cool until lukewarm.
Pour warm water into a large bowl.
Sprinkle yeast over top.
Let stand until foamy, about 5 minutes.
Stir to dissolve yeast.
Add cooled milk mixture, eggs, and 1/2 c. flour.
Beat with wooden spoon until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour until dough comes together.
Turn out onto floured surface.
Knead 5 minutes or until smooth and silky.
Place dough in a greased bowl; turn to coat.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Coat 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking pan with non-stick cooking spray.
Punch dough down; press into pan and cover.
Let rise in warm place 1 hour or until almost doubled. Heat oven to 375 degrees.
Crumble streusel topping evenly over dough.
Bake for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean and crumbs are slightly brown and crisp.
Cool in pan on rack for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar. Cut into 16 squares and serve warm or at room temperature.

title: arabian meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, mix meat, eggs, onion, bell pepper, salt, black pepper, tomato sauce and mustard.
Add oats and mix well. Place into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pat down to 1-inch thickness, leaving at least 2-inches on the sides for potatoes. Add potatoes, then pour juice from tomatoes over meat.
Bake in oven at 350° until done, about 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: angel food strawberry dessert
directions: Place cake pieces in a loaf pan.
Mix pudding and milk until it begins to thicken.
Stir in ice cream; pour over cake. Dissolve jello in hot water and add frozen berries; pour over cake.
Refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: beet salad
directions: Let jello partially set.
Fold in other ingredients.
Let set.
Serve with Cool Whip or salad dressing.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook mixed vegetables according to pkg. directions and drain. Add cheese, mayonnaise, onion & celery. Mix and pour into a casserole dish. Top with crackers & butter. Bake at 350 degrees for 20-30 minutes.

title: lazy day lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package.
Add oregano to spaghetti sauce.
In greased 2-quart baking dish, make layers of each: noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and spaghetti sauce. Repeat 2 or 3 times.
Bake at 375° about 30 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: penny carrot salad
directions: Cook sliced carrots until tender.
Drain and cool in ice water.
Add diced onion and green pepper.
For dressing, mix tomato soup, salad oil, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, yellow mustard and salt.
Blend and beat well.
Pour over onion, carrots and pepper.
Mix and marinate for 1 day.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat sugar, syrup and vanilla until sugar dissolves.
Add peanut butter and stir until smooth.
Add Rice Krispies.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let cool and serve.

title: baked fish fillets in mushrooms cheese sauce
directions: Cut fish in serving pieces and arrange in serving baking dish. Sprinkle with salt. Mix rest of ingredients except paprika. Spread on fish. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake in moderate oven (375°) for about 25 minutes. Serves 3.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening until fluffy.
Add sugar; beat well.
Beat in egg yolks.
Mix together flour and soda.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Mix in vanilla.
Add nuts and coconut.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into 3 prepared (9-inch) layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and 3 tablespoons butter over low heat.
Cool. Cream remaining butter with cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar, creaming until light.
Add 1 egg, 1 tablespoon flour and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Set aside. Gradually add and beat remaining sugar until thick.
Fold in remaining flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend in chocolate mixture.
Add almond extract, remaining vanilla and nuts.
Measure 1 cup batter and reserve (set aside).
Spread remainder in 9-inch square pan.
Grease pan first.
Pour cheese mixture over top.
Drop reserved chocolate batter by tablespoons over top.
Swirl mixtures together with spatula to marbleize.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool in pan on cake rack.
Cut into 2 1/2-inch squares.
Makes 16.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Sift together soda and flour.
Stir in egg mixture.
Stir in banana and peanut butter.
Pour batter into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream the butter.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add beaten egg yolks and sour cream.
Sift dry ingredients and gradually add to creamed mixture, mixing well after each addition.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Fill cookie press.
Form desired shapes on ungreased sheets and sprinkle with colored sugar.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 12 dozen.

title: apple crisp
directions: Spray saucepan with Pam.
Add apples, apple juice, sugar and cinnamon.
Saute until apples are tender and juice caramelized, about 15 minutes.
Spray Pam on a 6 x 8-inch baking dish.
Place apples in pan and reserve juice.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cover apples with granola and pour over reserved juice.
Dot with butter.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla frozen yogurt.

title: golden chicken surprise
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove skin from chicken; wipe dry. Melt butter with garlic, salt, poultry seasoning and pepper.
Mix potato chips and cornflakes together.
Dip chicken in butter mixture and then into crumbs. Arrange in baking pan.
Remove garlic from butter mixture.
Pour butter over chicken.
Bake for about 1 hour.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, 2 eggs, oleo and pecans and spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine the confectioners sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs and pour on top of the cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool completely.

title: cheese and ketchup sandwich
directions: Take 2 slices of white bread.
Spread mayonnaise on the slices.
Add lettuce on 1 slice. Put American cheese on the other slice of bread.
Spread ketchup on the cheese.
Put sandwich together.

title: macaroni supreme
directions: Cook macaroni in salt water until tender and put in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix grated cheese (leave out enough for topping) with all other ingredients and pour over macaroni.
Top with cheese.
Bake in 300° oven for 30 minutes.

title: paglia and fieno (italian)(straw and hay)
directions: Mix by hand all ingredients (you may add more or less according to your party). Be sure there is 1 1/2 cups water in the pan. Scoop meatballs with an extra large ice cream scoop (they should be the size of a small baseball). Place them on an aluminum tray and bake at 400° for at least 40 minutes.

title: 6-minute pecan pie
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Add nuts.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes, or until
knife comes out clean when inserted.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water in saucepan.
Boil until it forms a hard ball in cold water or spins a thread.
Gradually pour over egg whites, beating constantly until thickens.
Add vanilla and nuts and continue beating until it holds its shape. Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: chocolate chip peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Blend in flour, salt and soda. Stir in chocolate chips.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes. Yield:
3 to 4 dozen.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cherries; mix thoroughly. Place in large, buttered pan, reserving one-fourth mixture for topping.
Add cherries.
Cover with topping.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: garden primavera
directions: In large skillet, stir-fry zucchini and cauliflower in margarine until crisp and tender.
Add tomatoes, macaroni and basil; heat thoroughly.
Add process cheese spread.
Continue cooking until cheese spread is melted.
Yield:
4 servings. Calories:
Diabetic exchanges:
2 meats, 1 starch and 3 fats.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, lard, salt and baking powder until crumbly.
Add egg with water.
Mix; sometimes it takes more water.
This dough will keep for a while.
Makes 6 pies.
Best if use homemade lard.

title: no cook buttercream frosting
directions: Cream butter in small mixer bowl.
Add cocoa and sugar alternately with milk (more milk if needed).
Blend in vanilla. Mix to consistency to spread.
Yields:
About 2 cups.

title: cranberry delight
directions: Mix all together.
When it starts to jell, mix with 1/2 of small container of Cool Whip.

title: broccoli and noodles
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Cook fresh broccoli 7 minutes (or frozen according to directions).
Add butter, cheese, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Mix all together.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix salmon, potatoes, onion, egg and pepper until blended. Form into 8 patties.
Spread crumbs on wax paper.
Press patties in crumbs to coat.
Heat oil in nonstick skillet.
Add patties and cook over medium heat about 4 minutes per side until golden and crisp.
Serve with green peas in cream sauce.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in greased baking dish.
