Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni for about 9 minutes (do not overcook).
Drain. In a Pyrex dish, layer macaroni on bottom.
Put pepper and pieces of butter; put cheese on it (about 8 pieces of cheese; do not overlap).
Repeat layers until top.
Put bread crumbs on top of last layer.
Pour milk on it halfway up the dish.
Cook in oven for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: homemade dressing for potato or macaroni salads
directions: Mix in large microwavable bowl.
Stir with whisk until well blended.
Cook in microwave 5 minutes on High.
Take out, whisk again, put back in microwave and cook again at 2 minute intervals, stirring each time, until done.
(It will change color and consistency.)
Let cool to room temperature and whip in 1 cup Miracle Whip dressing.
Now, it's ready to use, or can store in fridge for later use.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients except pie filling. Put 2/3 of the dough in a greased square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches. Spread pie filling over dough in pan.
Crumble remaining dough over pie filling.
Bake about 30 minutes.
Serve warm.
Serves 9 to 12.

title: wilton roll out sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar with an electric mixer.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add baking powder and flour.
The dough will be very stiff.
Do not chill dough!
Roll out, cut with cookie cutters and place on ungreased cookie sheet on top rack of oven for 6 to 7 minutes.
Remove cookies from sheet immediately.
Bake at 350°.
Yield: 2 dozen.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix ingredients and put in pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375 degrees.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bacon, and pour into casserole.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Heat to a slow boil; cook 30 minutes.
Put in cans.
Put cans in hot water bath for 20 minutes.

title: apple nut pie(no crust to make)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch glass pie plate with margarine.
Combine egg and sugar, stir in next 5 ingredients. Spoon into pie plate; top with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream. Serves 6.

title: unfried french fries
directions: Spread potatoes with egg whites.
Spread into a sprayed pan and bake in a 400° oven.

title: myrna's cocktail meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine beef, crumbs, parsley, eggs, soy sauce, pepper, garlic, catsup and minced onion in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Form into small meatballs and marinate in baking dish.

title: hot fudge dip
directions: In a saucepan, combine the milk, butter and salt.
Heat to boil for 1 minute.
Stir constantly.
Add chocolate chips and vanilla; heat and stir until chocolate melts.
Add water slowly. Keep it warm.
Dip fruit or cake cubes.

title: ham dip
directions: Mix together and serve with crackers or potato chips.

title: griffin rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Cream the Crisco and sugar. Add egg; mix thoroughly.
Add yeast and water mixture; stir together.
Mix in flour and salt.
Knead dough until elastic.
Put in greased bowl; turn to grease surface.
Let rise until double. Punch down; shape into 2 loaves or 24 rolls.
For rolls, form large, walnut size balls.
Put on lightly greased cookie sheets; let rise.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes, until lightly browned.
Makes large (about 3-inch diameter), soft dinner rolls. Serve warm.

title: casserole tyson(beef)
directions: Put all ingredients in a casserole.
Cover.
Bake 3 hours at 325°.

title: vegetable beef stew
directions: Cook beef in oil in a Dutch oven over medium heat until brown. Drain and stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil over high heat.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Serve with hot cornbread.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Put all ingredients in a gallon wide-mouthed jar. Add water to cover eggs. Use salt and pepper, garlic, cloves, horseradish, and sugar sparingly at first, then you can add to taste when you test the first egg. The eggs will not have a beet taste, only the color. The beets can be eaten too. More eggs can be added to the juice. Refrigerate 2 days for full taste.

title: dill dip
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl.
Mix and serve with raw vegetables.

title: chocolate covered orange slices
directions: Put chips and paraffin in double boiler; melt both.
Keep hot. Take the orange slices (use toothpick to hold), you can divide in half or leave whole, and dip in chocolate mixture.
Place on foil to dry.
If you desire, you can dip for second time, makes heavier chocolate coating.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple; save 3 tablespoons juice.
Combine sugar and flour.
Stir in juice.
Add cheese and pineapple chunks, mixing well.
Spoon mixture into a greased 1-quart casserole dish. Combine butter and cracker crumbs, stirring well.
Sprinkle over pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until crumbs are browned.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: broccoli with tangerine ginger sauce
directions: In small nonstick skillet over low heat, cook and stir onion and ginger in margarine until onion is very tender.
Stir in yogurt, tangerine peel and segments.
Cook and stir over low heat until heated through (do not boil).
Serve sauce over hot cooked broccoli.
Garnish with additional grated tangerine peel, if desired.

title: victorian blackberry punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in 3 cups water in saucepan.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Combine tea, syrup, fruit juices and ice water in a large container.
Pour over an ice mold into punch bowl Garnish with lemon and orange slices.
Yield:
20 cups.

title: snappy barbecue
directions: Put beef in roaster; combine all other ingredients.
Pour over meat.
Cover and bake at 350° for 5 hours.
Turn beef occasionally.
When done, shred with a fork.

title: ground beef dip
directions: Brown and drain ground beef. Add all ingredients except cheese. Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Add cheese and simmer 10 more minutes.

title: fruit magic
directions: Spread pie filling in 8 x 8 pan. Combine cake mix and nuts in bowl. Add soft margarine and mix until crumbly. Sprinkle over top of pie filling. Bake 45 minutes or until brown at 350°.

title: thomas' banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Check with a toothpick. Makes 2 loaves.
Mmmm good!

title: quick easy bars
directions: Place aluminum foil on 12 x 15-inch pan.
Butter the foil generously.
Put single layer of crackers in pan.
In a saucepan, heat butter and brown sugar.
Boil 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Pour over crackers.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Cool slightly. Pour chocolate chips over caramel layer.
Let sit a few minutes, then spread with a knife.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired. Refrigerate.
Ooh, it's so good!

title: pasta delight
directions: Cool cooked spaghetti.
Put in large bowl.
Add all other ingredients and toss. Serve cold.
Will keep several days.

title: melba jello
directions: Make Jell-O by dissolving both Jell-O packages in 3 cups boiling water. Add the juices (drained from peaches, strawberries and raspberries), plus enough cold water to make 3 cups, to the Jell-O.
Add fruits. Chill until set.
Makes one very large Jell-O or 2 medium-large bowls full.

title: pear blossom cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to wet mixture.
Add vanilla and fold in pears, nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: spicy oyster crackers
directions: Put all ingredients in something large that you can occasionally shake.
Let set for about 24 hours before eating.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut butter into cake mix (dry) until crumbly.
Mix in coconut.
Put mixture lightly into ungreased oblong 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan building up slightly edges.
Bake 10 minutes.
Arrange apple slices on warm crust.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on apples.
Blend sour cream and egg yolks; drizzle over apples.
Bake 25 minutes or until edges are light brown.
(Do not over bake.)
Serve warm.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Cream butters and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Then add flour, salt and baking soda.
Beat until mixed.
Hand mix in oatmeal.
Mix until blended.
Mix in chips and raisins.
Drop by heaping teaspoons.
Bake about 10 minutes at 375°.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place in pie shell and add cherries to top.

title: orange pineapple salad
directions: Combine sugar and crushed pineapple.
Heat over low heat until just boiling.
Remove from heat and dissolve orange Jell-O and cold water.
Refrigerate until just beginning to jell.
Fold in Cool Whip, cheese and pecans.
Chill until firm.

title: creamy broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain.
Heat oven to 400°.
Place broccoli in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Beat soup and milk together until smooth; pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix baking mix and margarine until crumbly; sprinkle over cheese.
Bake until crumbs are light brown, about 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil fryer; chop up.
Cook noodles in broth until tender; drain.
Put noodles and chicken in casserole dish.
Mix mushroom soup, chicken soup and sour cream together.
Pour over chicken and noodles.
Top with bread crumbs.
Melt margarine; pour on top. Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes, until brown.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Combine ingredients in Dutch oven or large casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: old-fashioned fruit cake
directions: Combine prepared fruits; add fruit juice.
Let stand several hours or overnight.
Prepare pans, 1 large tube pan or 3 medium loaf pans.
Grease pans and flour.
Cream shortening; gradually add the sugar mixed with the salt and spices.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add beaten eggs; beat well.
Beat in flour.
Add nuts and juice, softened fruit with any juice remaining in bowl.
Mix well until well coated with batter.
Pour into pans.
Bake at 250° for 4 to 5 hours or until done.
Place a flat pan with 2 cups water on bottom shelf while cake is baking to keep moist.
Makes 5 pounds of nice fruity cake.
Cool and store in tight container.

title: basic vinaigrette dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in an electric blender; cover and blend at high speed about 10 seconds or until smooth. Dressing can be stored in a screw-top jar in the refrigerator. For diet serving, allow 2 tablespoons. Makes about 2/3 cup dressing.

title: pasta salad
directions: With this recipe it is hard to measure.
You can use however much you want or as little of each ingredient.

title: applesauce puffs
directions: Combine biscuit mix, first 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Add applesauce, milk, egg and oil.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds. Fill greased 2-inch muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until golden.
Cool slightly and remove from pan.
Mix the second 1/4 cup sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Dip tops of muffins in melted butter or margarine, then in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Makes 18 muffin puffs.

title: turkey in a sack
directions: Dissolve salt and paprika in water and mix with oil.
Rub turkey inside and out with mixture.
Take remaining mixture and pour into large brown paper grocery sack.
Use additional oil if necessary to cover entire inside of sack.
Place turkey into sack.
Fold open end tightly closed; staple.
Cook at 350° allowing 10 minutes per pound of turkey.
The turkey will be a nice golden brown and not dry and completely done if cooked as directed.

title: hamburger bean soup
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion.
Drain off oil.
Fry bacon and chip up.
Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Do not drain beans.
Add a few shakes of Tabasco sauce.
Cook in crock-pot on low for 5 hours.

title: trout with hazelnuts
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously season the flour with salt and pepper; coat the trout with the mixture.
Melt 2 tablespoons of the butter in a shallow, flameproof roasting pan.
Add the fish and cook over high heat for 1 minute on each side.
Transfer to the heated oven and cook just until fish is cooked all the way through, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all together and bake 25 to 30 minutes in a greased pan at 350°.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: divinity
directions: You also need 1 roll wax paper.

title: deviled crab
directions: Saute onion, celery and bell pepper in butter. Add crabmeat, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, egg, salt, pepper and crackers. Mix and put into individual shells.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: christmas snowballs
directions: Cream the margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add vanilla flavoring and blend well.
Add flour, salt and nuts.
This dough ball can be refrigerated until ready to bake.
When ready to bake, break off pinches of the large dough ball and form into small balls.
Place balls on ungreased cookie sheet and bake slowly at 325° to 375° for about 30 minutes.
Do not let cookies get too brown.

Cool cookie balls for about 5 minutes, then pour confectioners sugar, a little at a time, into a paper sack or Tupperware with lid on and carefully shake the cookie balls every few minutes until they are well coated with the white confectioners sugar, making pretty white snowballs.
Makes about 60 snowballs.

title: black-eyed pea casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Mix in other ingredients in the order listed.
Stir.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: lime gelatin salad
directions: Mix gelatin as directed on package.
Set aside to cool. Have cream cheese softened and mix with electric mixer until creamy. Add nuts and celery and mix thoroughly. Slowly add gelatin and mix thoroughly.
Pour into dish and chill until firm.

title: martha's german chocolate pies(makes 2)
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cornstarch together.
Add eggs.
Blend well.
Add melted margarine and chocolate, mixing only until blended and smooth.
Gradually add milk.
Stir in vanilla and salt.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans in bottom of unbaked pie shells.
Pour chocolate mixture into shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Just as good without coconut!

title: green beans with bacon
directions: Preparation Time:
15 minutes.
Cooking Time 10 to 15 minutes.

title: christmas ramekin
directions: Cut bread down the middle and slice into strips. Drizzle with butter (and garlic if you desire) and bake at 350° for 8-10 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl. (Save some cheese to go on top.) Press in baking dish. Sprinkle leftover cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly. Sprinkle cheese (optional) on top and return to oven for 4 to 5 minutes until melted.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Mix 1/3 cup soup, 1/4 cup milk, onion and parsley.
Dip chicken in soup mixture.
Roll in stuffing, place in shallow baking dish, 12 x 8 x 2-inch.
Drizzle butter on chicken.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Combine remaining soup and milk, heat, stir now and then.
Serve over chicken.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: microwave hot cocoa
directions: In a 1-quart microwave-safe bowl, stir together sugar, cocoa, salt and hot water; microwave on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until boiling.
Stir in milk; microwave on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until hot.
Stir in vanilla; blend well.
Serve hot, topped with whipped cream, if desired.
Makes about 4 (6 ounce) servings.

title: date balls
directions: Cook oleo, sugar, nuts, dates and egg in heavy saucepan on low to low-medium setting for 10 minutes.
Add vanilla; stir.
Add cereal and stir well.
Allow to cool slightly, then roll into small balls and roll in sugar or coconut.

title: fettucini and shrimp
directions: Cook fettucini according to package.
Drain well and place in warm serving platter large enough for tossing.
Add butter or margarine, heavy or whipping cream, grated cheese and parsley to pan.
Cook over medium heat (do not let boil).
Just before boiling, add shrimp to heat through (couple of minutes).
Pour over fettucini and serve.

title: pears in wine
directions: Cut bottom of pears so pears stand up evenly in baking dish. Boil mixture of remaining ingredients for 15 minutes, until slightly thick.
Pour over pears.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Baste twice during baking.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: In a mixer beat sugar and eggs; add oil.
On low speed, add flour, salt, baking powder, orange juice and vanilla.
Mix well. Stir in apple mixture.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake 350° 1 hour and 45 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: out-the-door sunday chicken
directions: Place in order in a casserole dish.
Cover and leave in a low 250° or 300° oven on the way out to church.

title: baked squash
directions: Boil the whole squash in salt water until tender.
Carefully slice top off squash and use spoon to remove the inside.
Leave 1/2-inch shell.
Saute pepper and onion until done.
Combine onion, pepper, cheese, egg, crackers and oregano with the squash removed from inside.
Mix well and put in shells.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: bacon pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: aunt mary's lemon cake and icing
directions: Mix together in bowl and pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: ham souffle sandwich
directions: Butter each slice of bread on one side.
Place 8 slices, butter side down, in a buttered baking dish.
Spread ham, cheese and onion on bread.
Top with remaining 8 slices of bread, butter side up. Mix eggs and milk.
Pour over casserole.
Cover with foil.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Before baking, sprinkle with paprika. Bake for 1 hour at 325°, uncovered.

title: oriental salad - marinated
directions: Drain all cans of ingredients (first 6).
Combine vegetables in a large bowl, stirring gently.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Cover and chill 24 hours.
Drain before serving.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Slowly add eggs; add vanilla, vinegar and salt.
Pour into your made or ready-made graham cracker crust. Bake at 300° for 10 minutes, then bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: score cake
directions: Bake cake in a long pan.
Remove from oven and use the end of a wooden spoon and punch holes in the top of the cake.

While the cake is still hot, pour the caramel over the top of the cake. Then pour the can of condensed milk over the top and spread. Sprinkle 1/2 of the bag of Heath bits on top and let cool completely.
Spread the cool whip on top and garnish with the remainder of the Heath bits.
Keep refrigerated.

title: easy-excellent meat loaf
directions: Combine meat, evaporated milk and onion soup mix.
Mix well. Put in baking dish/loaf pan.
Pour tomato sauce on top.
Bake in 350° oven for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: best pot roast
directions: Place all ingredients in a crock pot on high for 4 - 6 hours. Serve.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Break the spaghetti in half and cook.
Combine with margarine, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form into a crust in a pie pan.
Spread cottage cheese over crust.
Fill with spaghetti sauce.
Cover with foil and chill for 2 to 4 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and bake 5 minutes more.
(You can put meatballs on top.)

title: fat-free cucumber salad dressing
directions: Shred cucumber. Spread on paper towel and sprinkle with salt. Squeeze out excess moisture from cucumber.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together and put in a casserole dish.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Cut peeled eggplant into 1-inch cubes; soak in salt water in refrigerator overnight (minimum of 6 hours).
Drain eggplant; place in pan.
Cover with water; simmer until tender.
Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Saute onion, green peppers and celery in melted margarine for about 15 minutes, or until tender.
Combine cooked eggplant, bread crumbs and melted margarine for about 15 minutes, or until tender.
Combine cooked eggplant, bread crumbs and sauteed vegetables.
Add eggs, pimento and seasonings; blend thoroughly.
Place in greased baking dish; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with grated cheese; return to oven until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: sour cream 'n dill chicken
directions: Place chicken in a single layer in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with pepper.
Combine soup, soup mix, sour cream, lemon juice, dill and mushrooms; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: cupcake cones
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix, water, oil and eggs at low speed until smooth.
Place cones into muffin cups.
Fill cones half full.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onion and celery.
Add broth, soup and cheese.
Add in chicken.
When heated, about 15 to 20 minutes, pour over cooked spaghetti.
Mix well.
Put in oven for about 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Heat, covered.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix together; make a ball and roll in nuts.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Beat cheese until light and fluffy. Slowly add Jell-O. Fold in remaining ingredients. Add food coloring to make a nice green color. Chill until firm. Yield: 8 to 12 servings.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Place pineapple in a large bowl.
Sprinkle pudding mix over pineapple and mix.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Place into container and refrigerate.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Mix soup, vegetables, and chicken in 9 inch pie plate. Mix milk, egg and baking mix. Pour over chicken mixture. Bake 30 minutes until golden brown.
tags: cream of chicken with herbs soup

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix cocoa, butter, sugar and milk in a saucepan and boil 1 minute.
Pour over peanut butter, oatmeal and coconut.
Stir. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: caramel pie
directions: Mix together pecans, coconut and butter; set aside.

title: skillet chicken
directions: In skillet, brown chicken in oil.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes, or until done.
Stir occasionally.

title: pizza bread snacks
directions: Brown beef and drain well.
Add sauce to beef and simmer for 5 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Separate garlic rolls and place on a cookie sheet.
Spoon sauce mixture over garlic rolls.
Top generously with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake approximately 20 minutes. Serves 12.
Kids love 'em.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Drain juice from maraschino cherries.
Add water to make 1 cup and add 1/4 teaspoon almond flavoring.
Chop cherries fine and drain.

title: easy malasadas
directions: Combine egg, milk and lemon extract.
Add 2 cups Bisquick to batter and mix until smooth.
Cut 4 slices of bread into 9 square pieces.
Drop bread into batter.
Deep fry bread in oil for about 2 minutes until golden brown.
While hot, roll in sugar.

title: cornell barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place chicken in sauce for several hours and allow to marinate.
Grill over open flames.

title: cucumber sandwich filling
directions: Grate and drain cucumber.
Add to cream cheese that has been softened with a little mayonnaise.
Season to taste.
Add onions or chives and food coloring.

title: danby delight
directions: Mix oatmeal and boiling water.
Cover and let stand 15 minutes.
Add eggs, sugar, brown sugar, salt, vanilla and oil; mix well.
Add flour, baking powder and soda and mix again.
Pour into greased 8 x 12-inch pan.

title: lemon cake pie
directions: Beat together the egg yolks, salt, flour and sugar.
Add the lemon rind and juice; stir in the milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into egg mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and onion until soft, but firm.
Drain.
Saute dressing in butter.
Place a layer of dressing in buttered casserole dish.
Mix all other ingredients together and add to casserole.
Put a layer of dressing on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: vegetable and hamburger casserole
directions: Put in layers, celery, green peppers, onions, corn and hamburger.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Then spread on the spaghetti sauce.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until done. Real hearty meal.
Have tossed salad or cole slaw with it.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and eggs until done, about 25 minutes.
Peel potatoes while still hot.
Chop eggs, pickles, onion and celery. Put in with chopped potatoes.

title: cheesee potatoes
directions: Combine sour cream, cream cheese, cream of chicken soup and onion thoroughly.
Melt margarine.
Pour over hash browns.
Mix in Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until creamy.
If it is too thick, add water.
Great for picnics.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: In a bowl, combine fruit and lemon juice. Sprinkle with pudding mix. Stir gently for 1 minute. Fold in bananas. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli; drain well. Melt cheese and mix with broccoli. Melt butter and mix with crushed crackers.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican corn casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Use approximately 8 x 11-inch pan.
Spray with nonstick spray.
Let butter melt in oven.
Mix all ingredients in bowl, then pour over butter, but do not stir in butter.
Cook at 375° for about 40 minutes.

title: sugar-free lemonade
directions: Combine and refrigerate.
Chill and serve over ice.
Yield: 4 cups.

title: apple crunch
directions: Arrange apples in a greased 8-inch pan.
Combine oatmeal, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and flour.
Stir in butter.
Sprinkle white sugar (approximately 3 tablespoons) over apples and about 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Then spread your brown sugar mixture over the top.
Cook at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: our favorite chocolate cake
directions: Cream shortening, cocoa and sugar.
Add 3 eggs.
Add water alternately with flour, baking powder, baking soda and vanilla. Bake at 350°
for 1 hour in greased and floured tube pan.

title: peach icebox pie
directions: Line a pie pan or baking dish with a thin layer of vanilla wafers.
Cream together the egg, confectioners sugar and margarine.
Pour over the crumb crust.
Cover with fresh sliced ripe peaches.
Top with whipped cream.
Sprinkle with vanilla wafer crumbs.
Refrigerate at least 12 hours.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Bring to a boil in saucepan the water, oleo, oil and cocoa. In a large bowl, put the sugar, salt and flour and mix well.
When the first mixture boils, pour over the flour mixture and mix well. Add the eggs, soda, vanilla and buttermilk.
Pour into a greased baking pan (should be at least 1 inch deep).
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: bayou shrimp and rice(louisiana cajun recipe)
directions: Drain shrimp.
In saucepan, saute onion and green pepper in oil.
Add tomatoes, including liquid, and all other ingredients, except rice.
Heat through.
Add cooked rice and continue heating. Add shrimp; heat thoroughly.

title: banana split pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add crumbs and press in bottom of pan.
Add together two sticks butter, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Beat for 15 minutes. Pour over crumbs.
Layer bananas, then pineapple, drained.
Top with Cool Whip, cherries and nuts.
Cover overnight.

title: quick and easy beef stroganoff
directions: Trim all fat from meat.
Slice across grain in very thin strips.
Saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter or margarine on High for 2 to 3 minutes.
Do not drain; set aside.
Melt remaining butter or margarine on High for 45 to 60 seconds; add meat and cook on High 2 to 3 minutes.
Add water, reserved mushrooms and soup mix; cook on High until boiling.
Combine next 4 ingredients; mix well and gradually stir into hot mixture.
Cook on 50% power just until mixture thickens, 2 to 3 minutes.
Do not overcook! Spoon stroganoff over noodles and sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with a fresh green salad and poppy seed rolls.

title: white chili
directions: Place chicken in heavy large saucepan. Add cold water to cover and bring to simmer. Cook until just tender, about 15 minutes. Drain and cool.
Cut chicken into cubes.

title: raisin tart
directions: Mix sugar and eggs until well blended.
Add washed raisins and vanilla to mixture.
Mix up pie crust as directed on the box. Roll out crust and cut with a biscuit cutter.
Place crust in greased muffin tins.
Put spoonfuls of raisin mixture in each muffin tin lined with crust.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave banana pudding
directions: Melt butter at 100% power.
Blend together the sugar, cornstarch and salt and stir into melted butter.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook at 100% power for 3 minutes.
While cream mixture is cooking, beat egg yolks by hand.
Stir a little hot cream mixture into beaten yolks, then pour the yolk mixture into cream, stirring well while doing so.
Cook at 100% power 4 minutes more or until desired thickness is reached.
Be sure to stir mixture 1 to 2 times while cooking.
Add vanilla.
Line a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish with vanilla wafers.
Top with 2 sliced bananas.
Pour half the custard over the bananas.
Repeat the layers.
Top with whipped topping or meringue.

title: easy cake mix cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, oleo and eggs.
Roll into walnut size balls and roll in sugar.
Smash on cookie sheet with bottom of glass.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until browned.

title: orange balls
directions: Crush vanilla wafers in food processor or between waxed paper with rolling pin.
Mix all ingredients except sugar in a large mixing bowl until fairly smooth.
Chill in refrigerator for
1 hour.
Roll
into
bite-size
balls
and
then roll in confectioners
sugar.
Refrigerate	until
served,	dust again with sugar if needed.

title: three bean bake
directions: Cook
bacon
crisp in covered 2-quart microproof casserole. Cook
on
High
to
6 minutes.
Set aside, reserving drippings. Stir onion into drippings.
Cover and cook on High 5 minutes
or until tender, stirring once during cooking time. Add remaining ingredients;
stir.
Cover.
Cook on High 20 to 25 minutes	or until
hot,
stirring once.
Top with reserved bacon and serve.

title: deluxe strawberry shortcake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture is fine.
Add milk and stir with a fork until all the flour is moist.
Turn out onto lightly floured surface and knead gently for 20 seconds.
Divide dough into two portions.
Spread in 2 ungreased 9 inch layer pans or roll out to 1/2 inch thickness and cut with lightly floured biscuit cutter for individual shortcakes.
Brush with melted butter.
Bake at 450° for 12-15 minutes for layers, or 8-10 minutes for individual ones.
Spoon sweetened strawberries between layers and on the top.
10-12 servings. Yummy-Yummy!

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Mix soup base and flour.
Stir in chicken broth a little at a time.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until thick.

title: dutch cider soup
directions: Boil cider, skim and add sugar.
Brown bread cubes in margarine.
Beat eggs well, add 2 tablespoons sugar, flour, milk and allspice and add to boiling cider.
Stir in browned bread cubes to mixture just before serving.

title: berry bavarian(lo-fat)
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water; dissolve well.
Take cold water and add ice to make 2 cups.
Stir into Jell-O, dissolve ice.
Add Cool Whip, stir in with whisk.
Pour into bowl or dessert dishes. Chill for 2 hours before serving.
One-half cup serving equals 60 calories and 3 gm fat.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat sugars and margarine until light and creamy.
Beat in eggs. Add dry ingredients.
Mix well. Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Preheat skillet over medium heat and add oil to heated pan. Dip meat in egg, then in flour to coat.
Place meat carefully into pan and sprinkle on the onion along with some herbs of your choice, if desired.
Pan-fry 3 to 4 minutes; turn over.
Pan-fry 2 to 3 minutes longer until golden brown.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown flour and chili powder in oil.
Stir in water gradually. Simmer for 30 minutes. Brown hamburger and onion.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic salt. Dip tortilla in chili powder mixture until softened.
Fill center of tortilla with hamburger mixture. Sprinkle with cheese.
Roll.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with remaining cheese over top.
Pour chili powder mixture over enchiladas. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted. Serve hot.

title: pork chops and potatoes(6 servings)
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides in skillet; drain and set aside.
In large bowl, combine soup, milk, sour cream, pepper and seasoned salt.
Stir in potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 cup French fried onions.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish; arrange pork chops on top.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, for an additional 5 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix jam with water; add lemon juice, salt and spice.
Stir in cornstarch and cook until thick.
Add drained beets.

title: sausage stars
directions: Use 1 cup Ranch dressing.
Drain browned sausage and mix with other ingredients and set aside.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Cook meat, celery, onion and pepper until meat is almost done. Add tomato paste.
Cook until done.
Pour mixture into casserole with beans.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: colorado peach cream pie
directions: Cut butter into flour and salt.
Press dough into 9-inch pan.

title: cheesy corn muffins
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together flour, meal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Combine egg, cheese, milk and oil; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Fill well-greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fiesta chicken breasts(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat baking sheet with cooking spray. Mix soup mix and chips together. Dip chicken into Italian dressing, then coat with chip mixture. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until crispy on both sides.
Remove from pan with spatula.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix meats together.
Add remaining ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Mold into greased loaf pan.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 75 minutes.
The last 20 minutes of cooking, uncover and bake until lightly browned.
Serves 10.

title: broccoli and shrimp quiche
directions: Saute onions, and mushrooms in butter.
Add shrimp
and cook until shrimp are pink.
Press pie crust sticks into a 9x13 inch pan; bake crust 10 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Drain pineapple.
Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Use pineapple juice for other cup; cool.
Mix marshmallows, cottage cheese and crushed pineapple.
Add Cool Whip and mix.
Chill overnight.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Press into a 9 x 12-inch pan. This will make the crust.
Mix the next three ingredients.
Pour over the crust.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes until a little brown.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Combine bean mixture and seasoning mix; spread evenly in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Layer remaining ingredients in order listed. Heat 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: grandma's caramel corn
directions: Boil together sugar, margarine and Karo syrup for 5 minutes, then add a pinch of soda.
Pour hot mixture over popcorn in a large bowl and mix until evenly coated.
Spread out in a shallow pan and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 200°.

title: mexican salsa bread
directions: Pre-heat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine 1/2 cup cheese, picante sauce, and cilantro in a small bowl.
Mix well and spread over pizza crust.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Place on a baking sheet and place in 350 degree oven for 15 minutes or until cheese melts.
Remove and cut into wedges.
Yield:
8 wedges (serving size:
1 wedge).

title: pumpkin pecan pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; stir until well blended. Sprinkle pecans on your pastry shell.
Pour blended ingredients over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until firm in middle.
Garnish with pecan halves.

title: corn and blueberry muffins
directions: Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Drain the oranges and pineapple well, then mix all three ingredients together and chill.

title: steak dinner in foil
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Trim fat from meat.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place meat in center of wide piece of foil.
Place vegetables on top of meat.
Bring edges of foil together and seal. Place in shallow pan and bake for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours until meat is tender.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix the potatoes and the milk together.
Drain the milk off and add the egg, flour, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Drop the potato mixture by the spoonful onto a well-greased frying pan and brown on both sides.
Serve while still hot.
Yields 4 servings.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes, then gradually add sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice.
Fold in dry ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan and then top with 1 cup chopped pecans.
Bake 15 minutes at
When done, turn onto towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll towel and cake up and let cool.
Unroll cake and spread with cream cheese filling.
Roll cake up again, without towel, and chill.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie roll into 1/8-inch slices and line a 12-inch round pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Cream the cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla.
Spread on the crust.
Line with fruit, either fresh or canned and well drained:
bananas, peaches, mandarin oranges, strawberries, pineapple, grapes, apples, red and green maraschino cherries.

title: powerful pea chowder
directions: Bring peas, onion and water to a boil in a large pot over medium heat. Cook 15 minutes. Add potato and salt. Cook 15 or 20 minutes or until peas and potato are soft. Add evaporated milk and margarine. Heat 5 minutes. Serves 6.

title: cheesy confetti rice
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, melt the margarine.
Add rice and onion.
Cook over medium heat, stirring, until rice is a golden color, 8 to 10 minutes.
Slowly add water, green chiles and bouillon.
Continue cooking until mixture comes to full boil (8 to 10 minutes).
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 25 to 30 minutes. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Serve immediately.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage until brown; drain.
With rolls, line a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Add sausage; sprinkle with cheese.
Beat eggs and milk together and pour over sausage and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: apple spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 10-inch cake pan. Dust the pan with flour, tapping out any excess flour.
In a mixing bowl, combine sugar, oil, eggs, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, ginger and vanilla.
Using an electric mixer fitted with a dough paddle, mix together until thoroughly combined.
Add the flour, mixing to thoroughly incorporate.
Fold in the apples.
(All mixing may be done by hand, but be sure that ingredients are thoroughly combined at each step.)
Transfer batter to prepared pan and bake about 45 minute until a tester inserted into the center comes out clean. Makes 10 servings.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until medium done.
Rise in cold water.
Arrange layer of carrots, green pepper and onions in bowl or container.
Combine all remaining ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil, stirring until thoroughly blended.
Pour marinade over carrot mixture and refrigerate until flavor is absorbed. Will keep for a week.

title: sugar cookies(grandma crissman)
directions: Cream the margarine and powdered sugar and beat well.
Add egg.
Sift dry ingredients together and add along with flavoring. Add flour a little at a time; chill dough overnight.
Roll and put sugar on top and bake about 8 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: spaghetti bread
directions: Add all ingredients into the pan in bread machine in the order listed.
Select white bread and push start; or knead and bake by hand.
Yields a 1 1/2-pound loaf.

title: coconut blender pie
directions: Blend in blender 30 seconds.
Pour in 10-inch pie plate, greased.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream jello
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Mix all ingredients and pour into an 8-inch square oiled pan.
Chill and cut into squares. Top with Cool Whip.

title: gingerbread boys
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and molasses thoroughly.
Stir in water. Measure
in
flour.
Blend
in
all
dry
ingredients. Chill. Heat oven to 350°.
Roll dough to about 1/2-inch thick on lightly floured board.
Cut with favorite cutter.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake about 15 minutes or until no imprint remains when touched lightly.

title: peanut butter topping
directions: Put water and sugar in small saucepan.
Boil 5 minutes. Remove from stove and with mixer or whisk, beat in peanut butter and vanilla.
Cool.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: *Use no substitute for Coca-Cola.

title: lite applesauce-oatmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups. Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves in large bowl.
In medium bowl, combine applesauce, oleo and eggs.
Stir this mixture into dry ingredients until moistened. Stir in 1 1/2 oats and raisins.
Spoon batter into muffin cups. Sprinkle tops with remaining oats.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen (8 g fat per muffin).

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking soda in a small bowl.
Beat Parkay and sugar in a large bowl with mixer until fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture; beat until blended.
Stir in chips.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 2 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheets.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: spaghetti with yoghurt and garlic
directions: Heat oil in a pan; add garlic and fry until golden brown.
Add yoghurt, parsley, salt and pepper to garlic.
Mix together, then add to spaghetti.
Eat it warm.
Makes enough for four people.

title: grandmother's pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 9 or 9 5/8-inch pie shell. Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
I fold aluminum foil strips over the crust at the edges to keep the edges from getting too brown.

title: fat-free delicious dairy dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a small bowl; chill.
Serve with fresh fruit.
This is a real lo-cal treat.

title: orange juice cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Pour nuts evenly over bottom. Mix yellow cake mix, pudding, 1 cup orange juice, oil and eggs. Pour over nuts.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into 4-inch strips. Place in wok or skillet along with all seasonings.
Cook on low-medium heat until meat is completely cooked.
Slice bell pepper and onion and then place into wok with the steak.
Add water to make a thin gravy.
Cook on low for approximately 20 to 25 minutes or until steak is tender. Serve over yellow seasoned rice.

title: spaghetti aglio olio
directions: Heat oil until slightly warm.
Add garlic and allow to soak for 2 to 3 minutes.
Toss with cooked pasta and fresh ground pepper.
Garnish with parsley, basil and thyme.

title: fried okra
directions: Mix okra and potatoes together.
Add salt and pepper.
Coat with cornmeal.
Drop in a hot skillet with oil.
Turn until browned.
Put paper towels in bottom of bowl to absorb extra oil.

title: ham salad
directions: Mix thoroughly and chill.

title: orange bran streusel cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter, stir in cereal and sugar and set aside.
Beat with electric mixer, cake mix, eggs, peel, orange juice, and oil in large bowl till moistened.
Beat on medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured 10 inch tube pan. Bake for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with cereal mixture.
Bake 30 minutes longer.
Cool 15 minutes and remove from pan.
Finish cooling on wire rack.
Drizzle with glaze.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and let stand overnight. Mix again before cooking in skillet.
Batter will be very thin.

title: st. louis barbecue pork ribs
directions: On your barbecue grill, cook the pork until medium; do not sear.
Do not season.
Put 1/2-inch of barbecue sauce on the bottom of a roasting pan.
Place a rack of ribs on the sauce in the pan.
Pour a little sauce on top, then add more ribs.
Add more sauce and more ribs on top of that.
When all of your pork is in the roaster, pour the rest of the sauce over the meat until the pan is about 2/3 full.
Cover the pan, then bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Sear ribs on barbecue for just a minute or two on each side.
Be careful!
The meat is so tender it can fall through the grill.
If the meat is too tender, just skip the searing.

title: mystery fruitcake
directions: Prepare cake mix and bake following package directions.
When cool, crumble into a very large bowl or pan.
Add fruits and nuts to crumbled cake.
Mix frosting by package directions and mix with cake mixture.
Pack tightly into foil-lined 10-inch tube pan or two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Cover cake with foil and chill in refrigerator at least 24 hours.
Cake should be kept refrigerated. Makes six 1/2 lb. fruitcakes.

title: buffet beef stew
directions: Melt butter in a Dutch oven and brown the beef.
Add onions and saute until onion are golden brown.
Add the celery salt, parsley, 1 can of consomme and one cup of water.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: pizza noodle bake
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and noodles and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Add noodles and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add cheese and bake 10 minutes more.
Cut in squares. Serves 6.

title: peanut butter squares(microwave)
directions: Mix powdered sugar and cracker crumbs.
Heat margarine and peanut butter in microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir.
Stir into crumb mixture.
Press in ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Heat chocolate chips in microwave on High for 2 minutes, stirring after one minute.
Spread over crumb mixture.
Refrigerate until firm, at least thirty minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: sallie's light rolls
directions: Mix the first four ingredients in pan you are going to make your dough. Mix yeast in water and add to above mixture.
Start adding flour about 3 or 4 handfuls at a time.
Mix in well each time until it forms a soft dough.
Knead well for 4 or 5 minutes. Place dough in a large greased bowl, turning once to coat dough on top.
Let rise 50%.

Punch down and let rise again till it doubles in size. Make into rolls or biscuits and let rise till double in size. Bake at 325° to 350° for 30 or 35 minutes, according to oven. This dough is good for sugar cake and will keep in refrigerator if tightly covered.

title: sweet 'n sour green beans
directions: Cut beans into 1-inch pieces.
Cook according to package directions, omitting salt, or cook fresh beans in 1/2 cup salted water until tender.
Drain and set aside.

title: gingerberry punch
directions: Float sherbet balls on ginger ale in large punch bowl.
Serve in punch glasses.
Makes 12 servings.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together and place on serving dish. Refrigerate overnight.
Top with 1/2 jar (or more if needed) chili sauce; then place 2 cans shredded crabmeat, drained.

title: berry delicious bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pan (bread pan).
In large bowl, add strawberries, sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add remaining dry ingredients.
Mix and pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar glaze.

title: peach dessert
directions: Pour peaches and juice into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over peaches.
Drizzle margarine over cake mix.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake is browned and peach juice is bubbling. Serve with whipped topping.
Yields 16 servings.

title: chiffon cake
directions: Combine both mixes; add eggs, water and oil.
Blend well. Beat as for ordinary cake.
Pour into tube pan and bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: mouth watering rolls
directions: Whisk yeast and water together. Add sugar, salt and oil. Mix well. Add 6 1/2 to 7 cup bread flour into wet ingredients. Knead until mixed well. Place bread in a greased bowl. Turn bread over to grease well. Cover bowl with plastic wrap and let rise until doubled in size. After bread has doubled in size, knead well and make into rolls. Let rolls rise and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: asparagus roll-ups
directions: Bring egg and cheeses to room temperature.
Combine egg with both cheeses.

title: homemade sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine ingredients in order listed in blender.
Process until smooth.
Makes 1 1/4 cups (the amount in a 15-ounce can).

title: cole slaw(serves 10)
directions: In a blender, blend the first 12 ingredients well.
Place the cabbage and peppers in a large salad bowl.
Pour sauce over and toss well. This should be done about 1 hour before serving. Tastes even better the next day.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Mix all together and beat by mixer well!
Add cake coloring to mixture, red or green for the holiday.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes; use 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool!

title: microwave grape jelly
directions: Pour juice and water into 2-quart glass bowl.
Add pectin and mix well.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes or until bubbles appear at edge of bowl, stirring after 3 minutes.
Add sugar gradually, mixing well.
Microwave, covered, for 6 to 7 minutes or until mixture has boiled for at least 1 minute.
Skim off foam; mix well.

title: raw vegetable salad
directions: *Measure in one empty can.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Serve with platter of fresh fruit.

title: mrs. fileccia's class famous pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease and flour two 1-pound coffee cans.
Stir together the pumpkin, oil, water and eggs.
In another bowl, mix the sugar, flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Combine the 2 minutes and stir in raisins and/or chopped nuts.
Pour into the coffee cans.
Bake for 1 hour.
Makes 12 delicious servings.

title: mama's custard pie
directions: Bake crust for 10 minutes at 400°.
Beat eggs in a large bowl. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into crust.
Cover edges with foil.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool completely.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: low cholesterol sausage
directions: Mix the turkey with seasonings and refrigerate for a few hours.
Form patties and bake in a 400° oven or fry in pan sprayed with cooking spray.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix and bake at 425° for 45 minutes; let set 5 minutes before cutting.

title: canned hot peppers 'n ketchup
directions: Remove seeds and cut up peppers. Parboil peppers 5 minutes; drain. Mix other ingredients together in large saucepan; bring to a boil. Add peppers and mix well. Pack into jars and seal. Cold pack 20 minutes. Makes approximately 10 pints.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add onion, pressed garlic, salt and pepper and continue to cook until onion is transparent.
Pour into large pan and add tomato juice, tomato paste and oregano. Bring to boil and let simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: brownies
directions: Melt shortening and chocolate.
Add sugar. Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flour, salt and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Turn off oven and let brownies remain for another 20 minutes.
Makes a 9 x 11-inch cake pan.

title: the greatest pork roast
directions: Place
roast
in
roasting pan.
Sprinkle roast lightly with garlic.
Combine
dry
onion
soup mix, butter, mustard, flour, black
pepper and brown sugar to form a paste.
Spread paste
over top, sides and ends of pork roast.
Dot shortening on top
and cover
pan.
Roast
in
475° oven for 30 minutes. Reduce heat
to 325° and continue baking for about 1 1/2 hours or
hours, basting
occasionally with drippings from meat. When roast is done or tender, carve or slice and serve.
Makes about 8 to 10 servings.

title: hobo stew
directions: In a large Dutch oven, cut hot dogs and sausage into small pieces.
Add ketchup and grape jelly.
Cook on medium approximately 40 minutes.
Cool about 15 minutes.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch or two 9-inch round layer pans.
Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Mix 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Beat 3 minutes on high speed, scraping bowl.
Pour into pans.
Bake oblong 40 to 45 minutes, layers 30 to 35 minutes. Cool and frost.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool 10 minutes.
Poke lots of holes in cake with a fork.
Combine cream of coconut and condensed milk. Pour slowly over top of cake, allowing to seep into the holes. Chill at least four hours.
Top with Cool Whip and flaked coconut.

title: sally ann soft molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add molasses.
Alternately add buttermilk and dry ingredients. Roll out and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 8 minutes.
If you don't have the right size cutter you can use a Spam can.

title: neiman-marcus cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars together.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix. Add flour, powdered oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Combine margarine, cocoa, milk, powdered sugar and vanilla. Mix well.
Stir in pecans and coconut.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add eggs and milk.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients, apples and nuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: party punch
directions: The jello determines the color of the punch. Store this mixture in large containers in the freezer until ready to serve. It makes a slushy punch that does not need ice. Add 2 bottles ginger ale as you stir the thawing mixture and put into punch bowl.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in 1/2 stick margarine.
Cook broccoli by directions on package.
Add oregano.
Cook 1 cup rice in salted water.
Add rice and broccoli to onion mixture.
Add soup, cheese and pepper.
Pour in casserole dish.
Sprinkle crushed crackers on top.
Drizzle with melted butter and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken in wild rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.
Makes a large casserole. Can easily be halved.

title: bruschetta al pomadoro
directions: Combine first six ingredients in glass bowl.
Add olive oil to cover 3/4 of way up.
Stir gently and let sit a few hours before serving.
Spoon sauce on toasted bread.

title: queen elizabeth cake(date nut cake)
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and soda, let stand about 5 minutes.
Mix together
sugar, butter, egg, salt, and nuts.
Add vanilla, baking powder, flour-mix to gather then ad to date mixture.
Pour into a greased 9 x 12 pan. Bake in 350 oven for 35 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: In large bowl of mixer, combine flour, granulated sugar, soda, cinnamon, oil, eggs and vanilla; beat at medium speed until well mixed.
Stir in apples and walnuts.
Turn into well-greased 12-cup fluted tube pan heavily coated with bread crumbs.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 60 to 65 minutes or until pick inserted in cake comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes, then turn out on rack to cool.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Makes 18 to 20 servings.

title: philadelphia cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream together first four ingredients.
Add the beaten egg and salt and flour (a little at a time).
Chill dough well.
Form into little balls the size of walnuts, dip in the unbeaten egg white and roll in chopped pecans.
Can also add to nuts a little red and green sugar crystals.
Bake in 350° oven until set (about 15 to 20 minutes).

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix together.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: steak pizziola
directions: Pound meat with flat side of mallet or rolling pin until very thin, being careful not to split fibers.
Brown lightly in hot oil in skillet.
Remove meat and set aside.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
While peas and onions are frozen, let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Set out about 1/2 hour before serving to finish thawing.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place potatoes and onion in greased 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.
In medium saucepan, melt margarine.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook until smooth and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk.
Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly.
Pour sauce over potatoes. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2
hours.
If desired, garnish with crumbled bacon.
Yields 4 servings.

title: sandwich filling #2
directions: Finely chop vegetables.
Mix with mayonnaise thinned with lemon juice.
Add salt to taste.
Spread on bread or roll and top with grated cheese, if desired.

title: homemade pretzels
directions: Mix yeast and water in bowl.
Add sugar and table salt.
Add flour and mix.
Knead dough until smooth.
Cut off pieces and make into shapes (not too thick, nor too thin).
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Brush egg on top of pretzels (cover entire top). Sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hearty potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, carrots and celery until tender.
Drain, reserving liquid and set aside vegetables.
In the sauce kettle, saute onion in butter until soft.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Gradually adding the milk, stir constantly until thickened. Gently stir in cooked vegetables.
Add 1 cup or more of reserved cooking liquid until soup is desired consistency.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: fudge cake (brownies)
directions: Melt
butter
and chocolate over low heat.
Remove from heat and add sugar, eggs, flour, nuts, vanilla and salt.
Bake in a
13 x 9-inch pan (greased and floured) for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: quick pie crust
directions: Mix as directed.
Makes enough dough for a 2 crust pie.

title: raw spinach salad
directions: Wash off spinach.
Cut off stems.
Tear to bite-size and put in salad bowl.
Add onion rings and bacon.
Combine mayonnaise, Equal and vinegar.
Pour over spinach.
Refrigerate, toss and serve.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients together, then add sugar, a little at a time.
Knead together.
Roll in small balls.
Roll in extra fine sugar and press into molds.
Take out of molds and let air dry.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs one at a time. Alternately add dry ingredients and sour cream.
Add flavorings. Pour into tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick melted butter in 12 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat 2 sticks melted butter, powdered sugar, egg and salt 15 minutes.
Don't underbeat.

title: zesty pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti per instructions.
Add tomato, cucumber, onion, bottle of dressing and dry dressing mix.
Toss and chill.

title: banana split pie
directions: In a small saucepan, combine pineapple, flour and sugar. Simmer until thick.
Cool.
Line crust with sliced bananas.
Pour pineapple mixture over bananas.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans. Cover with whipped topping.
Chill thoroughly.

title: garden special
directions: Prepare all ingredients before measuring.
Cook onions, peppers and celery 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes and seasonings. Bring to a boil.
Put into hot pint jars.
Process at 5 pounds for 10 minutes.

title: stromboli
directions: *I often leave off the pepperoni because it makes the sandwich very greasy.

title: mexican dip
directions: Melt Velveeta in crock-pot on low.
Add soup and chiles. While cheese is melting in crock, fry sausage in skillet (crumbly consistency); drain and set aside.
After cheese has melted, add sausage and mix together.
Add the Ro-Tel tomatoes (drained and chopped) and keep the excess juice.
Add the leftover juice to make a creamy dip consistency.
Keep the leftover aside, as you may need it as it sets in the crock and thickens.
Keep crock on low and serve with tostado chips.
Stir occasionally.

title: chicken fiesta salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed and drain.
Rinse with cold water and drain.
In large bowl, combine mayonnaise, cream, salt, pepper, celery and scallions.
Add macaroni, chicken and olives. Mix lightly.
Serve on lettuce garnished with tomato and green peppers.

title: sausage roll
directions: Place a piece of waxed paper onto surface.
Mash out crescent rolls (leaving them connected once unrolled).
Spread sausage on top evenly, then sprinkle grated cheese over sausage.
Roll up, beginning with long edge of crescent roll.
Wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate overnight.
Slice into 1/2-inch slices and bake on cookie sheet about 15 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach salad
directions: In a shaker, combine olive oil, vinegar, sugar and lemon and pepper seasoning salt. Shake well. Chill. Serve over fresh salad made with the remaining ingredients.

title: harvard beets
directions: Make a sauce by cooking cornstarch, water, lemon juice and salt for 5 minutes.
Pour over the beets.

title: fruit and yogurt parfaits
directions: In a small greased skillet, toast almonds and coconut over medium heat until golden.
Set aside and stir in raisins.
Thinly slice peaches and plums.
Halve strawberries and combine fruits in medium bowl.
In another bowl, stir in yogurt, sour cream, honey and vanilla.
Layer fruit and yogurt mixture in 4 parfait glasses, adding 1 tablespoon coconut mix to each glass when 1/2 filled. Top with remaining coconut mix.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Put Swiss cheese on top of chicken.
Prepare stuffing mix according to package and place on top of cheese layer.
Mix soup with milk and pour over chicken mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite sizes, saving the trunk.
You will need a place to store the meat.
This will take about 2 weeks.
Cook all but the rabbits.
This will take about 1 month.
This will feed about 3,000 people.
If more are expected, add the 2 rabbits, but don't unless needed, because some people don't like hare in their stew.

title: watergate cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes in tube pan or in 2 layers. (Less baking time for sheet cake.)

title: johnnie mezetti
directions: Saute meat and onions in oil.
Add salt, tomatoes and juice. Cook noodles until tender and add to meat mixture.
Add diced cheese and mushroom soup.
Heat and serve.

title: grandma ruth's turkey
directions: Wash turkey.
Squeeze lemon juice and rub on skin.
Brush with oil and salt and pepper.
Put other ingredients tucked in or around turkey.
Pour water in pan.
Cover with foil.
Cook according to directions.
Remove foil for the last hour of cooking to brown. This recipe works with a whole turkey or just a turkey breast.

title: christmas eggnog
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy and stiff and gradually beat in 1/2 cup of the sugar.
Beat egg yolks until thick and beat in remaining sugar, cream and milk. Add flavoring (vanilla to taste or 1 cup of sherry).
Lastly, fold in egg white mixture and serve in a punch bowl with nutmeg sprinkled over the top.

title: batter bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in large bowl.
Stir in sugar, shortening and egg.
Add flour, a little at a time.
Spoon batter into greased muffin pans and immediately bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Store rest of batter in covered container in refrigerator.
Keeps a week.

title: sugar crunch coffee cake
directions: Crumble all.
Sprinkle the yeast in lukewarm water in a small bowl.
Add one teaspoon of sugar and mix.
Let stand until the yeast is thoroughly dissolved, 5 to 15 minutes.

title: guacamole
directions: Mash the contents of 2 avocados with a fork in a large mixing bowl.
Grate onion and tomato and mix together with avocado.
Add canned chile peppers (hot, medium or mild according to taste), dash or 2 of Tabasco sauce, some white pepper, salt is optional, and finish with lemon juice.

title: orange cake
directions: Beat together and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350° or until done.
Cool and frost with topping.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Simmer sauce ingredients, then add carrots until warm.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put first six ingredients in saucepan.
Boil until golden brown.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soda, then pour onto warm buttered cookie sheet.

title: dry beef dip
directions: Blend milk and cream cheese.
Stir in beef, green pepper and pepper.
Add sour cream.
Refrigerate.

title: no fail dumplings
directions: Sift 2 cups of flour.
Mix all together, egg and milk mixed together first.
Drop by teaspoon or tablespoon into broth.
The secret is simmering the liquid while dropping dumplings.
Cover, heat to boiling and cook 10 minutes, covered, then 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: green chili enchiladas
directions: Heat soup.
Slowly add green chilies and gradually add sour cream.
Put approximately 2 tablespoons mixture in tortilla and chicken and small amount of cheese.
Roll tightly.
Place in baking dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° and pour remaining soup mixture over tortillas.
Sprinkle rest of cheese on top.
Bake another 10 minutes.

title: grandma cookies
directions: Chop dates, nuts and fruit.
Cream butter, sugar, egg, salt and cinnamon.
Sift together flour and soda and add to creamed mixture along with fruit juice.
Add fruit and nuts.
Mix well. Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Yields 9 dozen.
Freezes well.

title: texas cake
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients. Bring to boil remaining ingredients. Pour this over flour mixture. Mix well and pour into greased cookie sheet. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: mint puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line cookie sheet with foil and spray with Pam.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually beat in sugar. Add food coloring; blend in.
Add mint morsels; fold in.
Drop small spoonfuls onto cookie sheets.
Turn off oven and put cookie sheets in oven overnight.

title: zippy chicken wings
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Arrange wings in shallow baking dish and pour liquid over all.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: scalloped corn and squash
directions: Put half the squash in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Heat corn and milk. Gradually add to slightly beaten egg and salt. Pour half the mixture over the squash. Sprinkle with half of the cheese and crumbs and dot with half of the margarine.
Put remainder of the squash, corn mixture, cheese and crumbs in layers in casserole. Dot with margarine. Bake in oven at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in half; scoop the insides.
Mix the potatoes with the cheese, deviled ham and seasonings.
Mix in the cream until fluffy.
Scoop the mixture back into the skins and bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 17 minutes.
Serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs.
Add rest of ingredients.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: lime pineapple salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk over low heat.
Pour over gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Combine softened cream cheese and mayonnaise, mixing until well blended.
Gradually add gelatin, mixing until well blended.
Stir in pineapple.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in whipping cream.
Pour into 2-quart mold.
Chill until firm.

title: holiday green bean casserole
directions: You will also need Pam.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown onions and hamburger together.
Heat kidney beans and tomato paste.
Add 2 cups of water, salt, pepper and chili powder. Add hamburger and simmer about 20 minutes.

title: rachael's best squash
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Slice squash and boil until tender. Blend all ingredients into bowl except crackers.
Mix and blend together with hand mixer at low speed.
Add contents into 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Melt butter, then pour over crackers.
Bake for 45 minutes or until desired consistency.

title: cream cheese congealed salad
directions: Heat pineapple juice and add jello to dissolve.
Soften cream cheese and add to pineapple juice and beat with spoon or egg beater to dissolve cream cheese.
Then add milk, tidbits and pecans.

title: saud bakkels(norwegian pastries)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a bowl, blend together butter, margarine and sugar until smooth.
Stir in egg and vanilla or cardamon.
Mix in sifted dry ingredients.
Stir together until you get a stiff dough.
(May need to add more flour at this point.) Press into tins.
Bake
8 to 10 minutes or until very lightly browned.

title: baked penne and sausage, zucchini and fontina
directions: In frypan, saute onion until transparent. Add sausage, stirring until browned. Add zucchini until softened. Stir in cream and grated Fontina; season with salt, pepper and oregano. Boil penne pasta until done. Drain and add cream mixture to pasta. Fold together and pour into buttered greased casserole dish.

title: poisson croix(tahitian dish)
directions: Sprinkle the bite size fish with salt.
Place in a glass or "Tupperware" bowl because the lime is very acid.
Marinate the fish in the lime juice until the fish is cooked or "bleached" and no longer pink.
Drain well, pressing the fish a little to pour off the excess lime juice.
Add the green onions, tomatoes and blender mixed coconut milk, stirring gently to mix well.
Serve on a bed of chopped lettuce.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a quiche dish or 10-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Grease pan.

title: instant hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all together dry and store in jars.
To use, add 1 to 3 tablespoons to hot water.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables in microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Stir halfway through cooking.
Mix cooked vegetables, chicken, cheese and soup; put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt butter.
Crush crackers. Mix crackers and butter; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until cheese is bubbly.

title: skewered chicken cubes with honey-mustard sauce
directions: You will also need 12 wooden toothpicks.

title: jello ice cream
directions: To make orange pineapple, use orange jello and crushed pineapple.
Use just enough water to dissolve jello, then add crushed pineapple, drained, sugar, beaten eggs, cream and milk to fill a gallon freezer.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain corn, peas, green beans and pimentos.
Chop celery, green peppers and onion.
Boil sugar, vinegar and oil and pour over other ingredients while hot.
Seal well and refrigerate.

title: cheese bread
directions: Mix flour, cheese and salt.
Make a well.
Pour in yeast, eggs, Crisco and milk mixture.
Mix well.
Knead well.
Put Crisco on sides and bottom of loaf pans.
Place dough in each pan and punch down.
Let dough rise in pan 4 to 6 hours.
Smear egg yolks (2) on top of loaves.
Bake in 375° preheated oven for about 1/2 hour and check for doneness often after first 15 minutes.
Yield:
about 5 or 6 large loaves.
This recipe can be easily halved.

title: rumaki
directions: Combine soy sauce and sherry; mix well.
Pour over water chestnuts; toss lightly to mix well.
Wrap each water chestnut with halved bacon slice.
Secure with wooden pick.
Brush with soy sauce mixture.
Broil 3-inches from heat for 2 to 3 minutes per side, turning once or twice, until bacon is crisp.
Makes 32 appetizers.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Drop in shortening, 2 eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add remaining 2 eggs; beat. Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased pan lined with wax paper.
Bake 1 hour at 350° until done.

title: new orleans baked bananas(serves 4)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut
pieces
of foil each 4 x 6-inches.
Peel bananas
and
cut
in
half lengthwise.
Place each half on a piece of the cut foil.
In a small bowl mix the orange rind, honey,
orange
juice and vanilla extract.
Spoon over banana halves and
top each with a piece of butter.
Fold over the foil once	and
crimp
the
ends to seal.	Place on a baking sheet and bake
for 5 to 8 minutes.	If the bananas are really ripe, they will cook in five minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Set together cranberries and sugar overnight, then drain.
Add fruit and nuts to cranberry mixture.
Fold in 1/2 pint of well whipped cream.

title: chicken and rice fiesta salad
directions: Mix salad dressing with next 5 ingredients.
Add chicken and rice.
Serve with tortilla chips, guacamole and tomatoes.
Serve chilled.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir sugar and cinnamon into mix.
Combine milk and beaten egg.
Stir into mix and blend well.
Stir in rolled oats.
Drop by teaspoons on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: baked duck(serves 6)
directions: Season ducks with salt, black pepper and red pepper.
Stuff with 2 quarters of onion and pod of garlic.
Sprinkle inside and outside with Worcestershire sauce.
Add a little oil to roaster and add ducks.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours or until tender, turning occasionally.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt oleo in dish and then pour in with other ingredients. Mix.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 375° for an hour or until golden brown.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In a large mixer bowl, beat the cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into prepared 9-inch pie crust. Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with desired amount of pie filling before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: six-weeks muffins
directions: Pour the boiling water over 2 cups of bran and let stand while assembling other ingredients. Mix in oil. Mix rest of bran with sugar, eggs and buttermilk. Sift flour with soda and salt. Combine all ingredients. Pour into lined muffin cups. Bake as needed for 18 to 20 minutes. Mixture will keep 6 weeks in refrigerator. Makes 6 dozen.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into crust and freeze.
There will be some mixture left over.

title: saucy ham and potato bake
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Blend in flour and seasonings. Gradually add milk; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add 1 1/2 cups cheese; stir until melted.
Toss potatoes in cheese sauce.
Pour into 2-quart casserole, reserving 1 cup potato slices.
Arrange ham and remaining potato slices on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: red lobster biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and cheese until soft dough forms. Beat vigorously 30 seconds. Drop dough by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 450° until brown.

title: caramel icing and candy
directions: Brown 3 tablespoons of the sugar in a skillet.
Mix the rest of the ingredients and cook on medium heat.
Add browned sugar and cook to soft ball stage.
Cool slightly.
(For candy, omit the tablespoon of flour.)

title: gail's candy
directions: Drop on wax paper and let cool.
Store in refrigerator.

title: angel cookies
directions: Add vanilla to egg whites and beat until soft peaks form. Gradually add sugar beating until stiff. Fold in the morsels. Line cookie sheet with parchment paper. Using heaping kitchen teaspoon, spoon dough onto parchment paper leaving 2-inches between each cookie. Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix well and pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.

title: ham casserole
directions: Combine milk and cheese in a saucepan and place over low heat until cheese is melted.
(This can also be done in a microwave.) Stir in remaining ingredients.
Grease a 2-quart casserole and place mixture in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave 2-minute fudge
directions: Combine ingredients and cook 2 minutes on High.
Stir well. Add nuts if desired.
Pour into buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Allow to set for 20 minutes.
Refrigerate.

title: mexican punch
directions: Stir all together and serve cold.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill. Serves 6.

title: christmas cheer(wassail)
directions: Mix all ingredients in large pot and heat to almost boiling. Reduce and simmer 1/2 hour. Remove cinnamon sticks and cloves before serving.

title: healthy viva zapata squares
directions: Add cornmeal to boiling water, mixing vigorously until well blended.
Cover and simmer about 10 minutes until done.
Grease an 8 x 10-inch pan lightly with margarine and spread the cooked cornmeal flat on bottom of pan.
Saute the onions and green pepper until tender in margarine.
Combine with 1/4 cup salsa and refried beans; spread on top of the layered cornmeal.
Spread 1/2 cup medium hot salsa over bean layer.
Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Let sit about 10 minutes before serving.
Cut in serving squares.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
This will keep for about 2 weeks in refrigerator.
This is great on raw vegetables.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes in a cast-iron skillet.

title: cheese cake brownies
directions: Mix until smooth.
Butter 10-inch pie plate.
Pour mixture in evenly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally while baking.

title: raisin bars
directions: Bring raisins and water to a boil; add 1 cup of oil.
Remove from heat and let cool to lukewarm.
Mix together sugar and eggs. Mix dry ingredients together.
Add raisin mixture to sugar mixture.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour into oiled and floured 11 x 17-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Put icing on while hot, any kind of icing, good without icing.

title: pasta with salmon and dill
directions: Cook pasta, drain salmon, add dill, pepper, celery and onion. In small bowl whisk oil, lemon juice and vinegar.
Add to pasta and salmon and refrigerate 2 hours and serve.
