title: cookie bars
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt oleo.
Sprinkle crumbs.
Continue down list, placing ingredients on.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Great for any fruit dip.

title: caldo de queso(cheese soup)
directions: Cover bottom of saucepan with oil.
Add onions and saute.
Add chopped tomatoes and water for desired amount of soup.
Season to taste with garlic salt and salt.
Add potatoes and cook until tender, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add cheese. Cover and let sit 1 to 2 minutes until cheese is melted.
Serve immediately.

title: lemon-cream cheese brownies
directions: Combine cake mix, 1 egg and margarine in bowl; mix well. Press into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine confectioners sugar, 2 eggs, cream cheese and lemon extract in bowl; mix well. Spoon into prepared dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool completely; cut into squares.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Peel, quarter and rinse potatoes.
Place potatoes in a 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe casserole dish and add water.
Cover and cook on High for 15 to 20 minutes or until done, stirring once. Drain, mash or beat with mixer at low speed.
Add sour cream, cream cheese, 1 tablespoon butter, onion salt and pepper.
Gradually beat in enough milk to make smooth and fluffy.
Turn into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and cover.
Chill up to 24 hours.

title: apple dumplings
directions: After mixing ingredients for pie crust, roll out into large enough circle to enclose around the peeled and cored apples. Place in baking dish that has been greased or sprayed.
Pour liquid over top and bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes or until apples are done.
Baste a couple of times during baking.

title: buttermilk icing
directions: Boil until soft ball forms and pour over cake while hot.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Wash and cube potatoes (do not peel) in 2-quart microwavable bowl.
Add vegetable oil, salt, pepper to taste, onion and garlic powder as desired.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over potatoes.
Cover and microwave 15 minutes.
Top with grated Mozzarella and microwave 5 to 10 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar and melted butter.
Pat into a 9-inch spring-form pan on the bottom and slightly up the sides.
Cream the cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in 3/4 cup sugar.
Mix in sour cream and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Pour 1/2 of batter into crumb lined pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 the chocolate mini-morsels.
Pour remaining batter on top. Sprinkle with the remaining morsels.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes until top is light brown and begins to crack.
Cool to room temperature and refrigerate.
(If you do not have a spring-form pan, place in shallow pan with 1/2-inch water and bake as directed.)
Decorate with Cool Whip and sprinkle with chocolate chips.

title: apple cloud
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place pie filling in an 8 x 8-inch greased baking dish.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly over top.
(Nuts should be mixed in cake mix.)
Slice margarine into thin pats over cake mix.
Bake for 40 minutes.
May serve plain or warm with ice cream.

title: chuck wagon salad
directions: Decore and wash lettuce.
Tear into bite-size pieces.
Wash, peel and grate carrots.
Chop celery and cheese into small pieces. Take garlic cloves and peel skin off.
Place salt into small bowl and take garlic cloves and place in salt and mash with fork until mushy.
Drain kidney beans and mix beans with garlic and salt. Combine lettuce, celery, beans and cheese; mix well with salad dressing.

title: gingerbread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt, sugar and spices. Add shortening, water and molasses to dry ingredients. Beat for 2 minutes on medium speed. Add egg and beat 1 more minute. Bake in 9 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes. Top with lemon sauce and serve.

title: "hot to trott" cream cheese squares
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Press into greased cake pan. Mix cream cheese, 3 eggs and powdered sugar.
Spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Let cool before cutting.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Mix sugar and oleo.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add mashed bananas and flour mixture alternately.
Let rest for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add nuts.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Add flour to sugar.
Combine ingredients.
Cook and pour into cooked pie shell.
Cover with margarine and brown.

title: fast and easy squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Boil squash and onion until tender. Drain well.
Mix with cheese and chilies.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.

title: mock champagne
directions: Mix half grape juice and half ginger ale.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Wash and hull strawberries.
Slice 1/2 of them.
Add sugar, plus cornstarch; mix well.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Stir constantly until thick and clear.
Stir in lemon juice.
Set aside to cool (1/2 hour).
Add remaining berries, saving a few for garnish.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise and carefully remove yolks. Mash egg yolks in a small bowl. Stir in mayonnaise and next 4 ingredients and blend well. Spoon or pipe yolk mixture evenly into egg white halves. Garnish if desired. Chill.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix Jell-O according to directions. Drain fruit cocktail. Add fruit, marshmallows and nuts. Refrigerate until set. Before serving, stir on carton of Cool Whip. Add green cherries to decorate.

title: christmas cutouts
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and salt. Chill for 1 hour, covered.
Roll out 1/8-inch thick.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: bishop's pie
directions: Crush Ritz crackers; mix with melted butter.
Spread and pat in a 9-inch square pan or pie pan.
Bake for 8 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: angel food jello dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Add berries.
Cool until almost stiff.
Arrange angel food cake in 9 x 13-inch pan in serving pieces or smaller.
Pour jello mixture over cake.
Chill.
Top with whipped topping.

title: hellen's corn casserole
directions: Combine cream-style and whole kernel corn, onions, pimientos, milk, egg, cracker crumbs, cheese, margarine and sugar in a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° and serve.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: sweet barbecue chops
directions: Spread chops on cookie sheet.
Cover with brown sugar and ketchup on each chop.
Add a slice of onion on each chop.
Season to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, covered.
Uncover; bake for another 1/2 hour.

title: grandmother fitzgerald's jam cake
directions: *Dredge raisins and chopped pecans in a small amount of flour.

title: chocolate chip cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese and butter. Add sugar and vanilla. Stir in chocolate chips. Chill in bowl for 2 hours. Shape in ball and roll in nuts. Chill another hour. Serve with graham crackers or keep at room temperature and use as dip.

title: brandon's microwave scalloped potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes 10 to 11 minutes on High until potatoes are almost tender. Let stand 5 minutes; peel and slice.
In a 4-cup measure, heat butter, onion, salt and pepper 1 to 1 1/2 minutes on High until butter is melted. Stir in flour; gradually add milk, stirring until smooth.
Heat 6 to 7 minutes on power level 7 until sauce is smooth.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, layer potatoes and sauce (you can also add cooked ham, if desired, at this time). Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on power level 7.
Set time 14 to 15 minutes until heated through.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Add onion and bell pepper; saute until wilted.
Add soup and water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place all ingredients in large pan; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, tightly covered.

title: apple crisp #2
directions: Peel, core, slice, then arrange apples in a shallow baking dish.
Cream butter.
Blend in sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Stir in bran flakes.
Sprinkle mixture over apples.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll in balls the size of walnuts. Roll in sugar. Bake in a 325° oven for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: pistachio delight
directions: Mix Cool Whip, maraschino cherries, pistachio pudding, chunk pineapple (drained) and crushed pineapple (undrained) with small marshmallows.
Then chill.

title: pea soup
directions: In a 3-quart pan, combine potatoes, peas, green onions, chicken broth and curry powder.
Bring to a boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer until potatoes are tender, about 20 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, oil, zucchini, vanilla and cinnamon. In separate bowl, mix salt, soda, baking powder and flour.
Mix all together and add walnuts.
Pour into pans that have been sprayed with Pam.
Makes 2 loaves.
Does not work well if you try doubling recipe.
Mix only one batch at a time.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (approximate).

title: salisbury steaks
directions: Combine all and form patties.
Brown on 1 side; top with onion rings.
Add 1 can of beef gravy.

title: macaroni - hamburger casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and rinse 2 times. Brown ground beef and drain. Add 2 cups water, tomato sauce and onion soup to ground beef. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Put macaroni in bottom of buttered pan. Top with meat mixture and several slices of cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: orange julius
directions: Fill blender jar 2/3 full of ice (1 tray).
Add remaining ingredients.
Place lid securely and blend for 30 seconds on high. Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first 8 ingredients; mix well.

title: fruit dip
directions: Whip with electric mixer.
Works well with all fruit.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, cream cheese, fructose and sugar replacement.
Add egg and water, beating well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt and add to creamed mixture.
Mix until thoroughly blended.
Shape into a roll 1 1/2-inches (3.75 cm) in diameter.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight.
Cut into thin slices and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350°F (175°C) for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yield: 30 cookies.

title: nell's strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add strawberries. Stir until thawed. Add pineapple. Pour in 8 x 8 x 2 inch pan.
Add a little milk to cream cheese and beat until consistancy of whipped cream. Add nuts and spread over gelatin mixture and cover with foil.

title: bill's pronto pups
directions: Mix
all dry ingredients together and add egg and milk; beat with
a
rotary
eggbeater until batter is smooth.
Dip franks in
batter
and
fry
in hot deep oil until brown on 1 side;
turn over
and
brown
the other side.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with mustard or mayonnaise.
Yield: 10.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Place ground chuck in baking dish, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle over the meat a layer of chopped onions, 3 layers of sliced potatoes, salt, cheese, pork and beans, and tomato soup.
Cover tightly with foil; bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt both chips and peanut butter together.
Mix in whole box of cereal.
Divide powered sugar equally between 2 brown grocery bags.
Put half the mixture in each bag and shake until all cereal is covered.
Pour out on waxed paper and let cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook (boil) macaroni until tender.
Melt butter in casserole dish.
Add macaroni, drained.
Add eggs, beaten, then cheese and enough milk to almost cover macaroni.

title: washington pie
directions: Probably means graham cracker, vanilla wafers or butter cookies.
Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Brown meat.
Add onions, garlic, tomatoes and water; bring to boil.
Add remaining items except noodles.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add noodles and simmer until tender. Garnish with Parmesan cheese if desired.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch Pyrex baking dish.
Bake for 45 minutes or until brown on top in 350° oven.

title: chili stuffed potatoes
directions: Pierce potatoes; microwave
on High 16 minutes or until soft, rotating halfway
through.	In large skillet brown meat; drain. Stir in
corn,
tomatoes,
ketchup,
pepper
and chili powder. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Slit potatoes.
Spoon 1 cup meat mixture
over
each potato.
Garnish with sour cream, grated cheese and green onions, if desired.
Makes 4 servings. Total time:
25 minutes.

title: pizza snacks
directions: In a skillet, cook sausage over medium heat; drain.
Stir in pizza sauce, ketchup and garlic powder; set aside.
Place biscuits on well-greased pizza pan.
Use the bottom of a small drinking glass to make a well in each biscuit.
Spoon 1 or 2 tablespoons of the meat sauce into each biscuit; top with Mozzarella cheese and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield: 20 pizzas.

title: easy quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place filling of your choice in bottom over pie crust (crab meat, ham, mushrooms, etc.).
Place shredded cheese over filling.
Beat eggs, whipping cream, onion and sugar. Pour whipped mixture over filling and cheese.
Place on cookie sheet and bake for 15 minutes at 425°.
Lower temperature to 300° and bake an additional 35 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
(Time varies according to oven used.) Let sit 5 minutes before cutting to serve.

title: macaroni (frog eye) salad
directions: Cook over medium heat until thick. Cool.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Cover cabbage leaves with boiling water; cover and let stand until limp, about 10 minutes.
Drain leaves.
Reserve liquid.
Mix hamburger, rice, onion, mushrooms, salt, pepper, garlic and 1/2 cup of tomato sauce.
Place about 1/3 cup of the mixture at the stem end of each leaf.
Roll up leaf.
Repeat with remaining leaves. Mix remaining tomato sauce with sugar and lemon juice.
Cover. Cook on 350° for 45 minutes.
While cooking, mix cornstarch and water in a pan and stir in liquid from cabbage rolls.
Heat to boiling.
Serve with cabbage rolls.

title: millionaires
directions: Melt caramels in milk over low heat.
Add pecans.
Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper.
Chill.
Melt paraffin and chocolate morsels in saucepan.
Dip candy into chocolate and return to waxed paper.

title: oven barbecue ribs
directions: Salt and pepper ribs.
Cook for 20 minutes in large, flat, foil-covered pan at 500°.
Drain grease and add onion and sauce. Cover with foil again and cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or longer.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal, soda, salt and baking powder.
Add eggs, corn, Colby cheese, oil, milk, jalapeno peppers and onion.
Bake in 13 x 9 pan at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes and apple filling.
Put in a baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easter sugar cookies
directions: Put first 5 ingredients into a mixing bowl and beat until smooth.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Roll small portions of dough 1/8 to 1/4 inch thick on a floured cloth or board.
Cut with Easter cookie cutters.
Place on lightly-greased cookie sheets and bake in a preheated 375° oven for 6 to 8 minutes or until a light brown. Makes 4 to 5 dozen, depending on size of cutters.

title: bacon appetizer crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat cream cheese, bacon, Parmesan cheese, onion, parsley and milk in small mixing bowl at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.

title: baked herb fish
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan or melt in saucepan and spray pan with Pam (cooking oil spray).
Dip fish in melted margarine, then mixture of dry ingredients.
Lay in pan and sprinkle remaining dry ingredients over fish.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken before and cut into bite size pieces.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Heat
soup and broth; thicken with flour. Cool.
Add sour cream
to
soup
mixture and pour over chicken. Roll crackers until
fine
and
put
on
top.
Pour melted butter over mixture.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Mix your chocolate syrup into Cool Whip to your desire.
Lay graham crackers on rectangle cake pan, then your Cool Whip mixture.
Just keep layering until Cool Whip mixture is gone. Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients and buttermilk.
Mix lukewarm water and yeast together, then add the rest.
Cut out and put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix corn meal in cream; set aside.
Beat egg yolks; add sugar and butter, then cream and corn meal.
Pour in unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until set.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift together flour, salt, cream of tartar and soda.
Combine jam and sour cream.
Add alternately with dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in well-greased and floured loaf pans 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.

title: country chicken 'n biscuits
directions: In greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish, combine first four ingredients and 1 cup cheese.
Blend soup and 3/4 cup milk; pour over casserole.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: golden potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, water, celery, carrots, onion, parsley flakes, seasonings and bouillon.
Cover and simmer until tender. Gradually add milk to flour, stirring until well blended.
Add flour & milk mixture to hot vegetables, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese and stir until melted.

title: sweet and sour sausage balls
directions: Make balls out of sausage and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Drain well.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over hot meatballs.
Marinate for 24 hours.
Reheat and serve warm.
Makes about 100 balls.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Form a ball and chill.

title: easy perfect pie crust
directions: Put egg yolk in cup and fill to 1/2 cup with milk and vinegar. Mix flour and salt; cut in lard.
Add egg yolk and milk.
Makes enough for 2 (2 crust) pies.

title: chicken mornay
directions: Mix soup, mayonnaise, sour cream, curry powder and cheese together.
Place broccoli spears in bottom of a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Place chicken pieces on top of broccoli.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve with steaming hot rice.
Serves 4.

title: white mountain salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Let partially congeal.
Place this in mixer and whip in cream cheese, which has been partially broken up.
Add pineapple and nuts, then fold in Dream Whip or Cool Whip. Pour in 13 x 8 x 2-inch glass or Tupperware dish.
Chill overnight.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Cut top off potatoes.
Scoop out pulp (easiest when hot).
Add all ingredients, except cheese, and whip until fluffy.
Fold in cheese and mix well.
Stuff mixture back into potato shells and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until tops are browned and bubbly. Top with sour cream and crumbled bacon, if desired.

title: potato salad
directions: Do not over cook potatoes or they will be too mushy.
Combine all ingredients until you have the right consistency and to your taste.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind and drain the peppers and onions together.
Pour hot water (boiling) over and let stand 10 minutes to drain.
Put sugar, salt, vinegar, cloves and spice in large pot.
Bring to a boil and boil for 10 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: citrus drink
directions: Combine lemonade, orange juice and Irish whiskey in a large pitcher.
Serve over ice in highball glasses.
Garnish with orange slices.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken roll-ups(serves 8)
directions: Take one package chipped beef, turn boiling water over and set for 5 minutes in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Drain chipped beef.

title: oven swiss steak
directions: Process 2 hours at 15 pounds pressure.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Gradually add powdered sugar. Beat until mixture is light and fluffy.

title: parmesan browned potatoes
directions: Heat bacon fat in a heavy bottomed saucepan and add potatoes. Cover and cook over medium heat 15 minutes.
Uncover and add half the cheese;
dust with garlic powder, salt and paprika.
Turn over the mixture gently.
Add remaining cheese and cook about 5 to 8 minutes longer.

title: johnny appleseed pizza(great for breakfast)
directions: Place halved English muffins on a cookie sheet.
Squeeze margarine on each half.
Cover each muffin with cooked apples and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake in a 350° oven, preheated, for 5 to 10 minutes or until warm.
Great for breakfast!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions; drain.
Mix cooked broccoli, mayo, Cheddar, eggs, soup and onion until well blended. Place in casserole.
Mix crushed cracker crumbs with melted butter; put on top of broccoli casserole.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: pepper-onion relish
directions: Place peppers and onions in a food processor
Chop.
Cover with boiling water and let stand 5 minutes.
Drain.
Boil together vinegar, sugar, salt and seeds.
Add pepper-onion mixture.
Simmer 15-20 minutes.
Pack into jars and seal.

title: squash soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until mushy and tender.
Puree in blender and pour in pan; add 1 cup cream.
Heat until warm and sprinkle with cayenne pepper.
Serves 8.

title: potato candy
directions: Microwave potato, peel and mash. Add sugar to make stiff dough, then roll out on wax paper. Sprinkle with sugar, put layer of peanut butter and roll up like a jelly roll.
Chill and slice.

title: peanut chocolate squares
directions: Mix and press into 9 x 13 ungreased pan. Let set 1 hour in refrigerator or put in freezer. When crust is set, spread 12 ounce package of melted chocolate chips over top. Cut into squares right now or you won't get them out of the pan.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and eggs.
Beat.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Put half of batter in greased tube pan.
Mix last 3 ingredients.
Sprinkle 3/4 tablespoon of mixture over batter.
Pour remaining batter in pan and cover with rest of topping mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Do not take from oven before 45 minutes are up.

title: sausage with potatoes
directions: Brown sausage in large skillet with 1 tbsp. oil and 1 c. water.
When browned, approx. 20 mins., add potatoes.
Wait 15 mins, then add onions and pepper, a little water if needed.
Cover and cook on low heat another 20-25 mins.

title: creamed spinach(diet recipe)
directions: Cook spinach slightly less than time recommended on package. Melt butter in skillet; add spinach, garlic and onion powder and cook 5 minutes.
Add sour cream, cheese, sesame seed and parsley. Heat, stirring (but do not boil) until well mixed and hot.
Serve. Total grams:
Grams per serving:
Serves 8.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Put in a large bowl and mix.
Chill.
Half of recipe makes large bowl.

title: hot crab spread
directions: In a skillet, saute onion and garlic in butter until tender. Transfer to a 3-qt. slow cooker; add mayonnaise. Stir in cheese. Cover and cook on low for 30 minutes or until cheese in melted, stirring occasionally. Stir in crab; cover and cook 1 hour longer or until heated through. Serve spread warm with crackers. Yield: 6 cups.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Put shortening, sugar and salt in a large bowl (cream as if making a cake).
Then add potatoes and potato water; let cool enough so it won't kill the yeast, then add egg and yeast.
Lastly add 1 cup flour.
Mix well together and let stand for an hour.
This will rise halfway up the bowl.
At the end of the hour, add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Dough will last 3 or 4 days in the refrigerator or can bake at one time.
Bake at 350° until done. (Can be baked lightly and frozen if you like, delicious frozen and heated as you want to use them.)
Real easy after making the first time.

title: wacky chocolate cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sara's turkey pot pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place 1 pie crust in a deep dish 9 x 9-inch pan.
Pour in mixture.
Place remaining pie crust on top. Seal completely.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: speedy brownies
directions: In a bowl, mix the first 7 ingredients until smooth. Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle top with chocolate chips. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes; boil until done.
Cut into cubes or mash the potatoes.
Add
diced,
boiled
eggs.
Save
other
for decorative
appearance.
Add
rest
of
ingredients
and
mix thoroughly.
Take
last
egg and start from the pointed end of egg and cut
or
lines down to bottom of egg; do not cut flat part of egg, and only cut through the white of egg.
Very carefully set
the
flat part of egg into middle of the potato salad and
gently
start
at
the top and peel the white stems down to form flower.
Paprika can be sprinkled over top.

title: potato au gratin
directions: Coat 10-inch gratin dish with vegetable oil.
Layer 1/3 potatoes over bottom of dish, overlapping in a spiral pattern. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon flour and spices mixed over potatoes.
Layer another third of potatoes and sprinkle with 1 tablespoon flour and spice mix plus 1 tablespoon Parmesan cheese.
Top with zucchini and remaining potatoes.
Pour evaporated milk over top.
Add remaining Parmesan cheese and spices.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil, lower oven temperature to 350° and bake 15 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Serves 8.
This dish is low calorie.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Combine flour, salt and baking soda. Add to creamed mixture at low speed. Mix just until blended. Drop by heaping teaspoons 2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet. Flatten slightly in crisscross pattern with tines of fork. Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes or until set and just beginning to brown. Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: In medium size mixing bowl, combine 1/2 cup of the cereal, chicken, celery, mayonnaise and yogurt.
Chill mixture.
Slice tomatoes into 6 wedges, cutting nearly to the base.
Spoon chicken mixture into center of tomatoes.
Place in lettuce cup on individual salad plates.

title: hamburger roll-ups
directions: Mix together ground meat, dry onion soup, egg and garlic powder. Shape into rolls like a hot dog.
Brown in skillet with small amount of oil. Remove and drain off excess grease.
Place into a roasting pan and pour spaghetti sauce over. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve on long hot dog or hoagie buns.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Mix Ritz cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Press into 8-inch pie plate.
Saute onions with 2 tablespoons butter until clear. Spoon into pie crust.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and pepper and pour over onions.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until center is firm.
Sprinkle with parsley before serving.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Combine brown sugar, corn syrup and margarine.
Boil and stir 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and soda.
Add Spanish peanuts.
Pour over popped corn and stir.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: "porcupine" meatballs
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and form into balls 1 1/2 inches in diameter; set aside.
Combine tomato juice, cloves, sugar
and Worcestershire sauce in a heavy skillet.
Bring to a simmer.
Drop in the meatballs.
Cover tightly and simmer 50 minutes or place in a baking dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Place 1 cup milk in a glass jar or crock (nothing metal) and allow to stand at room temperature for 24 hours.
Stir in 1 cup flour.
(To speed process, cover jar with cheese cloth and place outside for several hours to expose dough to the wild yeast cells floating in the winds.)
Leave uncovered in a warm place (80° is ideal) for two to five days, depending on how long it takes to bubble and sour.
(A good place is near the pilot light on a gas range or in other slightly warm place; do not place it too close to the pilot light, however, because too much heat will kill the yeast.)
If it starts to dry out, stir in enough tepid water to bring it back to the original consistency.
Once it has a good sour aroma and is full of bubbles, it is ready to use.
Try to maintain about 1 1/2 cups starter.

title: party nut rolls
directions: Warm the milk to lukewarm with the butter.
In large bowl, mix flour, yolks and vanilla.
Crumble yeast cakes and 3 tablespoons sugar until melted.
Add to flour and egg mixture and salt.
Add milk and butter mixture and mix well.
Cover tightly and place in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, chop 6 cups of nuts and divide into 6 equal portions.
Beat egg whites and slowly add 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Divide into 6 equal balls.
Roll out one ball of dough very thin.
Spread one portion of egg whites over dough and one cup nuts over egg whites and roll dough like a cinnamon roll. Repeat process for remaining dough.
Place 2 rolls on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.
Freezes well, also.

title: crab meat bisque
directions: Heat soup.
When just under boiling, add other ingredients.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix cornmeal mix, buttermilk, eggs and sour cream together and bake according to package directions.
Remove from oven and sit aside to cool.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to directions.
Saute onions and margarine.
Add soups, mushrooms, milk and parsley.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, lay 1/3 noodles, cottage cheese, 1/3 noodles, chicken, 1/2 soup mixture, Cheddar cheese, 1/3 noodles, 1/2 soup mixture and Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or microwave 12 minutes at 80% power. Let cool before serving.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cook cake as directed in cake pan.
Break cake up with fingers when cool.
First, layer into bottom of punch bowl.
Then put half of other ingredients on top of cake, except Cool Whip.
Repeat with other layers.
Then put Cool Whip on top.
Save some of pineapple and cherry filling for top to decorate.

title: filling
directions: Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover; bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Put apples in a large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in a smaller bowl then pour over apples, tossing to coat well.
Put in a 9 inch pie crust, dot with butter, adjust top crust and bake. 450° for 15 minutes and then 350° for 45 minutes.

title: president ike's 7 minute frosting(over 50 years old - 1940)
directions: Mix all the items together in top of double boiler over boiling water and continue beating with rotary beater for about 7 minutes or until the frosting thickens and holds its shape when it is dropped from a beater.
Remove immediately from boiling water.
Add vanilla and continue beating until frosting is stiff enough to spread.

title: asparagus and turkey casserole
directions: Arrange asparagus in shallow, buttered baking dish. Cover with turkey slices. Combine soup, cheese and sherry in saucepan.
Heat until cheese melts.
Pour over turkey and broil until well browned.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Combine the soy sauce and 2 tablespoons of cornstarch.
Toss with meat until all pieces are coated.
Brown in hot oil; remove from skillet.
Drain excess fat. Blend vinegar and cornstarch in skillet.
Add sugar, catsup and reserved juice.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add meat.
Cover and simmer 40 minutes.
Add pineapple and green pepper; continue cooking 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mom's special orange salad
directions: Place fruit cocktail and mandarin oranges in a large bowl; pour dry jello over top and mix until fruit is coated.
Fold Cool Whip and cottage cheese into fruit mixture until thoroughly blended.
Refrigerate until it is set.

title: mother's coconut pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Cook until thick. Add vanilla and coconut, reserving part of coconut to sprinkle onto meringue. Pour into pie shell. Beat egg whites until stiff. Add sugar to sweeten (about 3 teaspoons).
Spread over pie. Sprinkle remaining coconut over pie.
Brown in moderate oven.

title: quick chilli
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onions in hot fat.
Add seasoning, tomatoes and beans.
Cook over low heat for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: judy's chicken divan
directions: Arrange broccoli in baking dish.
Top with chicken.
Blend remaining ingredients together; pour over all.
Sprinkle top with Cheddar cheese and bread crumbs. bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until hot.
May be made ahead and frozen.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: In heavy saucepan or top of a double boiler, combine eggs, sugars, cream and salt.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture coats a spoon.
Cool.
Add milk and vanilla. Refrigerate for several hours.
In a skillet, melt butter.
Add pecans and saute on medium heat, stirring constantly, being careful not to burn them.
Cool.
Pour egg mixture into the cylinder of an ice cream freezer; add pecans, stirring slightly to distribute.
Freeze according to manufacturer's directions.
When frozen, pack ice cream in airtight containers and store in freezer.
Yields 2 quarts.

title: velvet dessert
directions: Bake crushed Lorna Doones and 1 stick oleo in 9 x 13-inch dish at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: grilled steak kabobs
directions: Alternate sirloin pieces, green pepper pieces, mushroom pieces and zucchini pieces on each of 4 metal skewers.
Sprinkle Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper over prepared skewers. Grill kabobs 5 to 6 inches from medium coals for approximately 10 minutes on each side.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add small amount of flour and soda.
Add sour cream.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: low-fat sour cream
directions: Put in blender and whip until creamy.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Sift
dry ingredients into bowl.
Add egg, milk, shortening, corn
and
chili.
Beat
well.
Bake in greased 8-inch square pan in hot 425° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: crullers
directions: Cream together sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Add skim milk.
Mix together flour, salt, nutmeg and mace.
Mix into the creamed mixture.
Chill on lightly floured surface, roll out half of the dough to 16 x 10-inch rectangle.
Cut into 2 inch squares. Repeat with rest of dough.
Deep fry in vegetable oil until golden brown on each side.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Yield:
65 cookies. Carbohydrate 5 g, protein 0 g, fat 6 g, calories 74.
One cookie = 1/2 fruit exchange, 1 fat exchange.

title: basic muffins
directions: Combine cereal, nuts, raisins and baking powder.
Stir in sweetener.
Mix milk, egg whites and oil.
Then blend with other ingredients.
Line muffin tins with paper baking cups, then batter.
Store in plastic bag in refrigerator.
Makes 12.

title: ranch bean salad
directions: Drain first 4 ingredients and combine with bell pepper and onion (optional).
Marinate overnight or longer in:

title: apple snack stacks(yield: 4 servings)
directions: Wash apples; pat dry.
Pack center of each apple with about 1 tablespoon peanut butter or cheese.
Wrap tightly in plastic wrap. Chill for 30 minutes or until filling is set.

title: fruit salad
directions: Peel all fruits and cut up in 1/2-inch pieces.
Add the 3 juices.
Chill and serve.
Serves 6.

title: meat loaf(kjottpudding)
directions: In a large bowl add all ingredients except milk.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth and then beat some more! While you are beating, slowly add the milk.
Add 1 more cup of milk if it doesn't get too thin.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.
With less milk this recipe makes delicious meat balls.

title: grape ice
directions: Dissolve sugar in grape juice.
Mix and freeze; stir frequently.

title: chili surprise
directions: Brown turkey in oil with onion and green pepper.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer one hour.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake at 325°
for glass baking dish. In medium bowl, combine flour and sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles corn meal.
Press firmly in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
In medium bowl, beat condensed milk, egg and vanilla with a beater until light and fluffy.
Stir in brickle bits and chopped nuts.
Spread milk mixture evenly on pie crust.
Bake 25 minutes more or until golden brown.
Cool.
Chill thoroughly before cutting.
Cut into bars. Store in covered container in refrigerator.

title: dump cake
directions: Add each ingredient as listed in layer form.
Do not mix.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fish creole
directions: Thaw fish slightly and cut into bite size pieces.
Combine all ingredients into a 2 quart casserole dish.
Stir to break up tomatoes.
Cover and bake at 375° 1 3/4 hours or until fish and rice are tender.
Stir once after 45 minutes.

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Pat into 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: chicken wings
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken and bring to a boil to make marinade.
Marinate wings for 4 hours.
Place wings in 2 (9 x 13-inch) cake pans and pour sauce over wings.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Turn once during cooking.

title: pheasant in wine sauce
directions: Dredge pheasant quarters in flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Heat oil in large, heavy skillet or Dutch oven and brown. Remove bird from pan.
Add more oil, if necessary, and brown vegetables on all sides.
Add wine and return pheasant to pan. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover pan.
Lower heat and simmer until the leg meat is tender, about 30 minutes.
Turn meat once during cooking.
Add more liquid, if necessary.
Each pheasant serves 2.

title: alfredo sauce
directions: Over low heat, mix all ingredients until cheese melts.
Serve immediately over hot fettucini or spaghetti.

title: friendship cake
directions: Mix the starter juice, 2 1/2 cups of sugar and 1 large can of sliced peaches with juice into a glass gallon jar.
Stir daily for 10 days.
On the tenth day, add other 2 1/2 cups of sugar and large can of crushed pineapple with the juice.
Stir daily for 10 more days.
On the 20th day, add the maraschino cherries and stir daily for 10 more days.
On the 30th day, drain fruit for 2 to 3 hours.

Divide fruit into 3 parts (enough to make 3 cakes apiece). You should have enough juice for 5 cake starters to give friends. (If you don't have enough for 5, just divide what you do have for each cake.)

title: ham and noodles
directions: In saucepan brown ham and mushrooms in butter.	Stir in remaining
ingredients.
Heat and stir until thoroughly heated and serve.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: red hot salad
directions: Dissolve red hots in boiling water before adding to Jell-O. Add applesauce last and refrigerate.

title: seven layer dinner
directions: Place layer of potatoes in bottom of greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with other ingredients in order given.
Sprinkle each layer with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: corn delight
directions: Stir all together into 2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour, covered and 1/2 hour, uncovered.

title: brown bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add rest of dry ingredients. Blend.
Add raisins-water mixture and nuts.
Fill to half 4 (No. 2) cans that have been well oiled or greased.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until bread springs back when pressed lightly.
Cool 5 minutes, then remove from cans.
Finish cooling.
(Freezes well.)
Any No. 2 vegetable or fruit can will do.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Coat a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Unroll crescent rolls for a flat dough and press into bottom of pan.
Spread hash browns and onions on rolls.
Place mushrooms, olives and meat on top of hash browns.
Break eggs into bowl and beat until mixed.
Pour eggs over everything in pan.
Sprinkle cheese over eggs.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes or until set.

title: king favorite
directions: Cut margarine into flour, add nuts and pat into pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.
Cool before adding next layer.

title: russian fluff bake dish
directions: Make instant rice.
Put all ingredients into a bake dish container.
Mix 1/2 cup of the cheese into the bake dish.
Mix one can of water with the tomato soup into the dish also.
Put the rest of the cheese on top of bake dish also cover it with crushed chips or dry roasted onions.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: enrapture chicken
directions: Cut green pepper into slices lengthwise.
Dice onions.
Cook for 5 minutes in butter or margarine.
Boil chicken in water. Cook rice.
When chicken, peppers and onions are ready, combine together with Ragu sauce and barbecue sauce.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: pork chop potato casserole(makes 8 servings)
directions: In a large casserole dish, alternate layers of potatoes and onions. Salt and pepper to taste. Mix mushroom soup, chicken soup and water. Pour over casserole. Brown pork chops. Place them on top of casserole. Cook in 350° oven for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender and pork chops are well done.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Mix ingredients together and roll into marble size balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet or pan.
Flatten with a fork. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: tunnies
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients.
Fill hot dog buns.
Wrap in aluminum foil.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Yields 6 servings.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and chips.
Put into flat 8 x 12-inch greased baking dish. Cover with thick slabs of cheese. Sprinkle generously with crumbled potato chips. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: grandmother's brown bread
directions: Mix well.
Turn into two 1-pound coffee cans which are well-greased.
Steam for 3 1/2 hours.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: In a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, layer vegetables, soup, cheese and crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: blueberry supreme
directions: Cook until thick, then add 2 more cups of blueberries and a little cinnamon.
Put mixture in ready prepared pie shell and chill.

title: apricot salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and add water.
Bring to boil and dissolve jello in the hot liquid.
Add Philadelphia cream cheese, then add Cool Whip to the mixture.
Add celery, pineapple and nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: easy puff pastry
directions: Combine the butter and unsifted flour in a bowl.
Using a pastry blender or food processor, cut butter into flour until size of peas.
Mix the sour cream with egg yolk.
Stir into mixture until well blended.
Gather into a ball.
Divide in half.
Wrap each piece in clear plastic wrap.
Chill at least 4 hours or overnight.
(Can be kept up to 4 days.)
Roll out dough and cut into squares (4 or 5-inch).
Fill each square with any meat you desire.
Roll up; seal edges.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: easy chocolate eclairs
directions: Bring water and margarine to a boil; add flour, then 1 egg at a time.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients with a little milk.
Add rest of milk. Cook over boiling water and stir.
Cover and cook 15 minutes longer; stir occasionally.
Beat egg yolks.
Add a little of hot mixture to egg yolks.
Pour back and cook a few minutes.
Add butter, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: corn tamale pie
directions: Brown burger in a large skillet.
Add other ingredients, chopping tamales into mixture.
Pour into casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Wash and cut potatoes lengthwise into 4 wedges.
Place skin side down in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine remaining ingredients; brush over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, brushing with oil/cheese mixture at 15 minute intervals.
Turn potatoes for last 15 minutes.

title: cloud biscuits
directions: Serve in generous portions.

title: one pan rice pudding
directions: Pour rice slowly into boiling water. Cover and cook 7 minutes. Add the milk and butter.
Stir a little and bring to a boil. Cover and turn to low. Cook 1 hour.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Blend first eight ingredients until blended.
Add flour until dough forms.
Spoon out on cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 minutes at 300°.

title: grandma christine's sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add sour cream and eggs.
Add 1 cup flour with salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Then add 5 or 6 more cups flour until dough is nice to roll.
Vanilla or nutmeg may be added.
Roll out.
Cut with cutter.

title: blue-ribbon cranberry chicken
directions: In a bowl, combine cranberry sauce, salad dressing and soup mix.
Rinse chicken; pat dry with paper towels.
Remove and discard skin, if desired. Arrange pieces in one layer in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour cranberry mixture over chicken pieces. Cover and chill the chicken mixture in the refrigerator for several hours or overnight.
Bake the chicken mixture, uncovered in a 300° oven about 1 1/2 hours or until the chicken is done, stirring glaze and spooning over chicken once or twice.
Serve the chicken and glaze on a platter with hot, cooked rice, if desired. Garnish the chicken with fresh rosemary, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Drain.
Boil eggs and peel.
Set noodles in a bowl and mix drained tuna, soup, peas and onion together until blended well.
Add diced eggs and mayonnaise and mix.

title: scratch dumplings
directions: Make enough biscuit dough according to how many dumplings you want.
Add egg to dough and make with sweet milk and self-rising flour.
Work into soft ball, put in refrigerator and let chill a couple of hours or more.
Boil chicken, bone.
If using fryer, add a can of cream of chicken soup to chicken broth and chicken.
Roll out chilled dough thin.
Cut into small pieces,
1 1/2 or 2-inches.
Drop into boiling broth, a few pieces at a time. Slightly stir with wooden spoon, don't overstir.
Add a little butter and salt and pepper to taste.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Brown meat, drain. Add BBQ sauce and set aside. Place biscuits in ungreased muffin pan. Press dough up sides of edge of cups. Spoon meat mixture into cups. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 400 degree for 12 minutes.

title: ginger chicken
directions: Combine sugar and seasonings; coat cut up chicken in mixture. Refrigerate for several hours.
One hour before cooking, drench chicken in flour.
Brown in margarine and Crisco for 40 minutes on low heat, turning occasionally.
Cover and cook for 20 minutes. Remove and place chicken on paper towel-lined pan.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes and serve hot.

title: sammy's cookies
directions: Place the raisins in a small bowl and completely cover with water.
Allow the raisins to soak for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Boil sugar, shortening, cocoa and milk over low heat 3 minutes.
Add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Drop on wax paper and refrigerate to cool.

title: lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together 1 3/4 cups flour and 1/3 cup powdered sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Press evenly and firmly onto bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Beat together eggs, sugar and lemon juice until sugar is dissolved.
Sift together 1/4 cup flour and baking powder.
Add to egg mixture and beat at low speed just until blended.
Pour over baked crust.
(Crust does not have to cool.
Just add custard and return to oven.)
Bake an additional 25 minutes.
Decorate top with sugar sprinkles.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 24 bars.

title: strawberries with honey
directions: Rinse and drain strawberries; slice in bowl.
Toss with lemon juice; drizzle with honey.
Serve at room temperature.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Add pineapple and mix.
Pour into baking dish.
Cut bread into cubes. Melt butter and put bread cubes in mix.
Spread over top of mixture.
Put in 420° oven for about 25 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: braised coot with onions
directions: Melt bacon fat in a frying pan and add enough sliced onions to cover the bottom.
Add pieces of coot and salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and cook on low heat with occasionally stirring until done.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix well and store in airtight container.
Mix to taste with cup of hot water, about 2 tablespoons per cup.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well (except brown sugar).
Pour into greased 8 or 9-inch cake pan (or 9 x 9-inch dish).
Sprinkle brown sugar on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate plunge dip
directions: In medium saucepan, stir corn syrup and cream.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate; stir until completely melted.
Serve warm as a dip for fruit.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: four cup salad
directions: Drain fruit and discard juice.
Mix all ingredients and chill for at least 4 hours (or overnight) before serving.

title: delicious baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Wash chicken.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place 2 pieces of dried beef on each piece of chicken.
Wrap 1 piece of bacon around each piece of chicken.
Mix sour cream, soup and black pepper to taste.
Pour on top of chicken.
Cover with foil.
Cook for 5 hours.
It will melt in your mouth.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into flowerets.
Peel stalk and slice thinly. Cover raisins with hot water.
Soak 5 minutes.
Drain.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Crumble into salad.
Blend salad dressing, sugar and vinegar.
Pour on salad and mix well.
Marinate 4 hours before serving.

title: chinese chicken and cashews
directions: In wok or frying pan, heat enough oil to cook chicken. Stir-fry 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Add 1/2 cup water and celery.
Steam 2 minutes.
Celery should be crisp, not limp, when served.
Remove from pan.
Warm cashews in same pan.
Add chicken and celery to cashews.
Serve chicken over rice.
Sweet and sour sauce may be used, if desired.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in an uncovered 2-quart casserole dish at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Microwave chips and 14 ounces almond bark in 2-quart dish on High for 2 minutes.
Stir.
Continue for 1 to 2 minutes until smooth.
Stir in marshmallows, cereal and peanuts.
Pour onto greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Top with cherries.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Place dry ingredients in a bowl and mix in milk to form a batter.
Pour over margarine in baking dish.
Arrange peaches over batter.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add soda, sour cream and vanilla. Add eggs, 2 at a time with 1 cup flour, beating well after each addition until all the flour and eggs are added.
Bake at 325° for one hour to 1 1/4 hours or until done.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Dissolve pudding in crushed pineapple.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all together (breaking canned chicken into small pieces as you go). Add mayo to taste.

title: frozen bread caramel roll
directions: Thaw frozen bread, but don't permit to rise.
Break bread up in bottom of a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Melt butter.
Add brown sugar and pudding; mix milk and cinnamon.
Mix all together and pour on top of bread; let rise 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Bake approximately 1/2 hour at 350°.
While still hot, flip rolls onto cookie sheet and scrape remaining caramel over them.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, "dump" the cherry pie filling and crushed pineapple.
Sprinkle cake mix over ingredients.
Pour melted butter over the cake mix.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over the cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve with ice cream.

title: french-fried onion rings
directions: Peel onions under running water to prevent eyes from watering. Cut into 1/4-inch slices and separate into rings.
Heat oil (1-inch deep) in 3-quart saucepan to 375°.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Dip each ring into batter, letting excess drip into bowl.
Fry a few onion rings at a time, turning once, until golden brown, about 2 minutes; drain.

title: french doughnuts
directions: Tear biscuits into halves. Roll halves of biscuits into balls and put holes into 10 biscuit halves left, making rings. Fry in oil and flip when brown.
Oil is ready when biscuits float immediately. Take out and put doughnuts and holes into powdered sugar which is in bag. Shake well and put on a plate when you take them out of the bag.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and add sugar.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
After 24 hours, add pineapple, Cool Whip, marshmallows and walnuts. Fold all together.

title: carrot salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Refrigerate overnight. Yields 6 servings.

title: ham and cheese balls
directions: Chop ham into small pieces, chop onions.
Mix 1/2 ham with all other ingredients.
Form ball, then roll ball in the reserved ham. Serve with favorite crackers.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Wash peppers and cut 1 inch ring off top.
Clean out and discard seeds and membrane.
Cut stem from top ring.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Stuff peppers.
Place 1 inch rings on top of each pepper.
Press down.
Stand peppers in baking dish upright, so that they fit snugly.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.
Meat and rice should be tender and done. Serves 6.

title: fudge and ice cream cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and beat 4 minutes. Pour into greased and floured pan, either 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake about 50 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: sour cream jumbles cookies
directions: Cream crisco, sugar, eggs, and sour cream. Stir in remaining ingredients. Drop by spoonfulls onto cookie sheet; Bake 350° 7-10 min.
Still soft to touch when done.
May double recipe.

title: aunt edith's crab cakes
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, parsley flakes, mayonnaise, mustard, egg and Old Bay together.
Add to crab meat (always check crab meat for shells).
Stir lightly.
Shape into a crab cake.
Refrigerate approximately 15 minutes.
Saute in 2 tablespoons of oil and margarine until brown.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Cut in thin slices.
Peel and slice onions and green peppers.
Combine onions, cucumbers and peppers.
Add salt. Let stand two hours.
Drain.

title: russian tea mix(makes a great gift)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in an airtight container.
Use 2 or 3 generous teaspoonfuls of mix to 1 cup of hot water.
Yield:
1 pint.

title: crispy nutty cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients twice and add to mixture.
Add vanilla.
Blend well and add oatmeal, cornflakes, coconut, chopped pecans and raisins (optional).
Spoon on greased baking sheet and bake at 350° for about 12 minutes or golden brown.

title: impossible garden pie
directions: Sprinkle zucchini, tomato and cheese in greased 10-inch pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake at 400° until golden brown (about 30 minutes).
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Garnish with tomato and zucchini slices if you wish.
Makes 6 servings.

title: microwave chili cheese dip
directions: Cut cheese into 2-inch squares.
In a 1-quart casserole dish, microwave cheese for 2 minutes and 30 seconds to 3 minutes and 30 seconds on Power 8, or until melted.
Stir once or twice during cooking time.
Add chili; stir until blended.
Microwave 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes on Power 8, or until heated through, stirring once. Serve with chips.
Yield: 3 cups.

title: hot brown
directions: Melt 1/3 stick butter until clear. Add milk, salt, red pepper and flour.
When mixed, add eggs, Velveeta, Colby or Cheddar and 1 tablespoon butter.
Stir until dissolved. Do not boil.
Assemble 4 slices toast, turkey and slice of ham. Top with cheese sauce, slice cooked bacon and slice of tomato.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Broil until bubbles.

title: roast beef and gravy
directions: Season meat with salt, pepper, garlic and 1 tablespoon flour. Brown roast on all sides in oil. Remove roast; add flour and brown. Add water and onion; return roast to pan and bake at 350° until meat is falling apart.

title: chocolate covered peanuts
directions: Melt both chocolates in microwave until completely melted. Mix salted peanuts or Spanish nuts into chocolate until all chocolate is full of nuts.
Spoon onto aluminum foil until it hardens.

title: ginger's favorite wine
directions: First Batch:
Pull stems from grapes.
Mash, skins and all, to pulp with clean 2 x 4.
Add 10 pounds sugar.
Mix well with 2 x 4. Put resulting mess in barrel.
Do not seal.
Cover opening with cheesecloth.
Shake daily for 10 days.
Wait 3 months.
Drain and strain liquid.
Drink at will.

title: mushroom dip(hot)
directions: Slice mushrooms and fry in margarine 10 minutes with onion. Add flour and sour cream (thicken).
Add cheese and seasoning. Put in casserole dish.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown onion and garlic in olive oil.
Add tomato paste and tomato sauce.
Cook about five minutes.
Add water, celery, parsley, sweet basil and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer at least 2 hours.
Remove celery before serving.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Cut bread into small pieces.
Mix other ingredients. Place in casserole.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients with milk. Pour over fruit and nuts.
Drop from spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: date nut bars
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, nuts, dates, milk and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together. Mix dry mixture to rest of recipe. Grease 9 x 11-inch pan.
Spread dough in pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: date balls
directions: Melt margarine on medium to low heat.
Add sugar and egg. Cook slow for 10 minutes, stirring constantly, being careful not to scorch.
Add dates and cook until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Mix well.
Shape into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar or coconut.

title: light breakfast in a cup
directions: Combine rice, 1/2 cup cheese, chilies, pimentos, milk, eggs, cumin, salt and pepper in large bowl.
Divide mixture evenly into 12 muffin cups coated with spray.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until set.

title: no roll pie crust
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and stir in flour.
Pat in bottom of pie pan.
Makes one (1-crust) pie.
Add pie filling and bake as instructed.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat oil with eggs.
Chop apples.
Pour oil over apples.
Let stand while mixing dry ingredients.
Add to apple and oil mixture. Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 350° in an oblong pan for 40 minutes.

title: red velvet punch
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, stirring until blended.
Chill mixture.
To serve, pour mixture into punch bowl and add champagne.
Add ice ring.
Yield: 5 quarts.

title: krispy baked chicken
directions: Put chicken in plastic bag and add dressing.
Squeeze bag until pieces are evenly coated.
Roll in crumbs and arrange in baking pan well coated with cooking spray.
Bake until crisp and brown.
Time will depend on size of pieces.
Wings or legs take about 40 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook onions slowly with butter and oil in a heavy, covered 4 qt. saucepan for 15 minutes.
Stir in 1 tsp. salt and sugar. Increase heat to moderate and cook uncovered 35 - 40 minutes stirring often, until onions are a deep golden brown.
Sprinkle with flour and stir for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat, add bouillon and water and blend well.
Add wine, salt and pepper, and simmer, partly covered about 35 minutes longer.
Pour over toast rounds and serve with parmesan cheese.
VARIATION:
After adding wine, salt and pepper, bring to a boil, pour into an oven proof tureen and stir in Swiss cheese and granted onion.
Float toast rounds on top of soup and sprinkle parmesan cheese and melted butter over toast. Bake at 325 degrees for 20 minutes.
Broil 1-2 minutes or until top is lightly browned.
Serve at once.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of boiling water for 10 minutes, or until tender; then drain.
In skillet, melt margarine, add brown sugar and honey; simmer 2 minutes.
Add carrots and cook until well done.

title: lo-cal and low-fat skillet chicken
directions: Boil chicken until done and cook rice.
In large skillet, saute onion, peppers and mushroom pieces, using cooking spray if needed to brown.
Saute until tender, then add V-8 juice, Worcestershire sauce, soy sauce and chicken.
Cook for 15 minutes. Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Add cooked rice to skillet mixture and mix well.
Add chicken broth for moisture. Serves 4.

title: gingerbread with lemon sauce
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour square pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Beat all ingredients in large mixing bowl on low speed, about 30
seconds, then medium speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into pan and bake for about 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix corn, celery, onion, green pepper, soup and cheese and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crush Ritz crackers,
mix with melted margarine and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: no-peek beef stew
directions: Mix together tapioca, sugar, salt, pepper and V-8 juice in large pan.
Add steak, potatoes, carrots and onion.
Bake at 250° in a covered pan for 5 hours.
Do not lift lid while baking for 5 hours.

title: mimi's easy cheese souffle(serves 6)
directions: Combine eggs, milk and seasonings; set aside in bowl.
In deep, well-greased covered baking dish alternate bread and cheese layers.
Pour entire liquid mixture over bread layers.
Cover and let stand 4 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.
It's great with kielbasa and stewed tomatoes on the side.

title: frozen coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions in two round pans.
Mix first 3 ingredients and set aside.
When cake is cool, slice layers in half and frost between each.
Put cut side down on each. Frost over all cake with rest of icing.

title: nachos
directions: Cook ground beef and drain grease; add Hormel chili and Cheez Whiz and mix together until cheese is melted.
Then serve over chips!
Or add lettuce, tomatoes and salsa and have a taco salad.

title: squash casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Boil squash until tender. Combine ground beef, squash, soup and cheese.
Simmer on low until cheese has melted.
Pour into ungreased baking dish and bake at 350 F for 30 minutes.

title: bechamel sauce
directions: In a saucepan combine butter and flour to make a roux; cook approximately 5 minutes, until roux is cooked.
Then add warm milk in small amounts, stirring until all the milk has been added. Turn heat up and cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens. Add nutmeg, salt and pepper to taste.
Sauce is done.

title: garlic potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Layer in a glass 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Slice the butter over the potatoes.
Sprinkle with the garlic powder.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: rich and easy chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool completely in pan.
Punch holes in cake with a small birthday candle.
Pour condensed milk evenly over cake (spread with spoon). Take lid off jar of caramel topping and warm topping in microwave, just a little (not hot).
Pour over condensed milk and spread evenly.
Place cake in refrigerator for 15 to 20 minutes. Spread Cool Whip over top of cake and sprinkle with chopped Hershey bar.

title: mustard pickles
directions: In sterile jars, pack with onions, cut into chunks.
Add 1 part vinegar
to 1 part water. Can add other vegetables such as hot peppers, green peppers, carrots (cut in chunks), celery, etc. Store in refrigerator.

title: mandel bread
directions: Beat eggs with sugar and oil.
Add rinds, chips and nuts.
Add flour, baking powder and salt mixture.
Mixture will be very sticky.

title: pizza fondue
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Put all ingredients in crock pot until cheese is melted.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine beef, pork, bread crumbs, eggs, 1/4 cup ketchup, all but the 1 teaspoon soup mix, parsley and pepper.
Mix and shape into a loaf.
Place in an 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a small bowl, stir together the 2 tablespoons ketchup, 1 teaspoon soup mix, apricot jam and mustard.
Spread over meat loaf and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: swiss chicken cutlets
directions: Pound chicken breasts to about 1/4-inch thickness with a meat mallet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dip into egg and then bread crumbs.
In skillet, add oil and brown chicken.
Set chicken aside in a baking dish.

title: alamo tamale supper
directions: Slice tamales in half crosswise and arrange in bottom of greased crock-pot.
Sprinkle onion over tamales.
Add corn.
Mix tomato sauce and chili powder.
Pour into crock-pot.
Top with grated cheese; cover and cook on low for 5 to 7 hours.
High for 2 hours.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spoon into greased baking dish. Bake in oven at 350° until hot and browning.
Serve hot with Melba rounds.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Mix ingredients and add the following dressing.

title: butter pecan rolls
directions: Layer ingredients in Bundt pan.
Spray Bundt pan with Pam. Cover bottom with few pecans.
Sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon. Place rolls in pan tightly together.
(Place two from edge to center of pan.
Add more pecans.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Add instant butter pecan pudding (dry).
Add butter and brown sugar mixture.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and add more pecans.
Place Bundt pan on cookie sheet.
Cover with wet towel and set overnight. Early morning or 8 to 10 hours later, remove towel.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Loosen rolls from side of pan.
Remove from pan at once.

title: party rye
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger in skillet; drain.
Melt Velveeta and add to meat mixture.
Season with herbs.
Spread mixture by spoonfuls on party rye and broil until bubbly, 10 to 15 minutes, just before serving.

title: dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Melt in sour cream and sherbet.
Use whisk to mix.
Add fruit.
Pour in mold or bowl. Refrigerate until solid.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions. Drain. Add hash browns and soup. Season with salt and pepper. Place in baking dish and bake at 385° for 30 minutes. Layer with cheese. Bake for another 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hawaiian dessert
directions: Mix cake batter according to directions.
Pour into 2 greased 13x9x2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cakes test done; cool completely.

title: sesame poppy seed salad dressing
directions: Put first 6 ingredients in blender.
Slowly add oil and vinegar until mixed well.
Serve over spinach or other green salad.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground chuck, bell pepper and onion together.
Add spices.
Melt cheese and Ro-Tel tomatoes in double boiler.
Layer on platter in this order: lettuce, tomatoes, chips, hot meat mixture and top with Ro-Tel and cheese mixture.
Serve immediately.

title: friendship cake and starter
directions: Combine peaches, pineapple, cherries, sugar and yeast.
Stir with wooden spoon 3 to 4 times the first day, then stir daily for 2 weeks.
Store in glass jar on counter with lid just barely set on.

title: libby's red velvet cake
directions: Cream together oil, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add red food coloring and vinegar. In a separate bowl, mix together flour, baking soda, salt, and cocoa.
Sift flour mixture and add to batter alternately with buttermilk.
Pour batter into three 8 inch round cake pans and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and let cool before icing.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix with 1 egg and margarine. Spread in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish to make a crust.

title: swiss mocha mix
directions: Shake all ingredients together to mix evenly.
Use 4 teaspoons per cup of hot water.
Store in airtight container.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Mix together real good.
Make into balls.
Great on crackers.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together and spread into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 400°.
Let cool completely.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Prepare meatballs or use frozen ones purchased from the store. Mix brown sugar and cornstarch in skillet. Add pineapple, vinegar and soy sauce and bring to boil. Reduce heat slightly and stir until thickened. Add green pepper and cook until tender. Add meatballs and simmer until heated through. Serve over cooked rice.

title: pralined yams
directions: Beat yams.
Beat separately the eggs, sugar and allspice; add to yams.
Melt the butter and add 1/2 to yam mixture.
Add other 1/2 of butter to brown sugar, then add to yam mixture.
Add pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hopping john soup
directions: Mix. Cook slowly until rice and onion are done, 1 to 3 hours.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, shortening, brown sugar, and white sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla, beat until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour, salt, and soda, into creamed mixture.
Add chocolate morsels.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until cookies are brown around the edge, but the centers are not done.
Yields 96 cookies.

title: quiche
directions: Fry bacon; drain and break into small pieces.
Mix milk, whipping cream, eggs, flour and nutmeg (mix well, set aside).
Mix cheese, bacon, mushrooms and onions.
Place into pie shells.
Pour milk mixture over cheese.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes and at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix all together (except crackers).
Layer whole crackers on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then layer 1/2 pudding mixture, then crackers, 1/2 pudding mixture and then crackers.

title: corn meal cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add egg and raisins.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: baked apples
directions: Put apples in a baking dish with about 1/2 inch of water.
Put 1 pat of butter and 1 teaspoon of sugar inside each apple. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until apples are tender or bake in microwave for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken divine
directions: Make a layer of broccoli in sauce made of the first 3 ingredients.
Put in layer of chicken and more sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
In the last 10 minutes or baking time, sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.

title: bloody mary tomato juice
directions: Simmer all until juiced, about 40 minutes, covered.
Press through a sieve.
Return to kettle, bring to a boil.
Put in hot jars.
Process quarts 30 minutes (same for pints).

title: chicken breasts
directions: Boil chicken breasts and take from bone.
Cut into pieces. Layer all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: coleslaw
directions: Mix cole slaw mix, ranch dressing mix, and tomato.
Add mayonnaise, creole, and garlic to taste.
Refrigerate for at least 15 minutes before serving.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Layer potatoes, onion and soup in a sprayed casserole dish. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 1 hour.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Add as many blueberries as you wish.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 and bake at 350° until brown.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix sugar, peanut butter and butter together in a large bowl. Roll mixture into small balls.
Place on wax paper.
Put in refrigerator until firm.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin. Dip balls and put back into refrigerator until firm.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, syrup, salt and butter. Add vanilla and nuts. Place in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Makes 1 pie.

title: becky's bran muffins
directions: Spray muffin pan with nonstick spray.
Spoon out 1/3 cup of batter.
Press in pan with a spoon.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: famous pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine filling ingredients in order given; pour into pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake an additional 45 minutes or until knife inserted near center of pie comes out clean.
Cool; garnish, if desired, with whipped topping or glaze.
Yields 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: cherry nut crunch
directions: Spread pie filling in bottom of a casserole dish.
Sprinkle cake mix over pie filling.
Don't mix.
Cover with nuts and dot with cut-up butter.
Bake at 350° until it turns golden brown.

title: pumpkin jelly roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed 3 minutes. Gradually add sugar. Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice. Fold in the flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger, salt and nutmeg. Spread in greased and floured jelly roll pan. Top with chopped nuts. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Turn onto towel sprinkled with powdered sugar. Roll up until cool. Beat powdered sugar, cream cheese, butter and vanilla until smooth. Spread on roll. Roll up again and refrigerate.

title: monster cookies
directions: Beat margarine and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Stir in soda and oats; add chocolate chips. Mix well.
Drop by 1/4 scant cups on cookie sheet 2 inches apart. Press down flat.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: orange-lemon icing
directions: Mix together until smooth and of spreading consistency.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli about 5 minutes; place in buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with chicken pieces.
Combine remaining ingredients with 1/3 cup broth; stir well.
Pour on top of chicken; top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken-roni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Combine with chicken, cheese, soup, milk, mushrooms, pimento and mustard.
Put crumbs on top and add the butter.
Cook at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: pickled beets
directions: Boil sugar, vinegar, beet juice, spices and bay leaves.
Add beets and bring to a boil.
Seal in sterile jars.
Allow two weeks before opening.
If desired, add sliced onions one hour before serving.

title: double chocolate mint bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Stir together flour, sugars, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Cut in 3/4 cup butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Beat in eggs and 1/4 teaspoon mint extract.
Spread into pan and bake 23 to 25 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in comes out clean.

title: chicken surprise
directions: Wrap bacon around each chicken breast. Put chipped beef on the bottom and chicken breasts on top.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour mixture over chicken breasts.
Bake 3 hours at 300° in square pan. Do not cover.

title: fruit cups(snacks)
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients well.
Spoon into paper-lined cupcake pans and freeze.
Keep frozen until ready to serve.
Makes 24.

title: layered casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Set aside.
Slice potatoes and carrots. Cook potatoes and carrots until just tender.
Layer potatoes, carrots, green beans and 1/2 cup of juice.
Sprinkle rice on top of these.
Ground beef over these, then pour on spaghetti sauce. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hostess cupcake filling
directions: Make 2 cake mixes into cupcakes.
Combine the first 5 ingredients and beat at high speed 10 minutes and then add the last 2 ingredients and beat well.
Let cupcakes cool and fill with pastry tip.
Fill three holes with filling.
Frost with boxed creamy frosting.

title: shrimp fettuccini
directions: Saut onions, garlic and parsley in butter until tender.
Add shrimp.
Cook three to five minutes, until tender.
Remove shrimp with platted spoon and add 1/4 cup butter to onions and sauce. Mix well.
Add 1 pint half and half or canned milk with milk and the 1/2 cup grated cheese.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Mix and heat to simmering the soups, tomatoes, broth and onion.
Sprinkle layer of crushed chips in greased 8 x 12-inch dish.
Add half of the chicken pieces.
Cover with a layer of soup mixture.
Repeat, ending with chips and finally cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: egg-n-sausage casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch greased pan and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves approximately 6 to 8.

title: tasty coconut pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter in mixer bowl until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add coconut and flour; mix well. Add buttermilk and vanilla and mix well.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until set.
Yields 8 servings.

title: crabmeat quiche
directions: Thaw pie shell.
Blend together first 4 ingredients; add crabmeat, cheese and onions and mix thoroughly.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: asparagus and english pea casserole
directions: Cook asparagus and peas according to package directions, omitting salt.
Drain asparagus and peas, reserving 3/4 cup of asparagus cooking liquid.
Cut asparagus into 2-inch pieces and place asparagus, peas and mushrooms into a 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole, sprayed with vegetable spray.
Stir together.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in Dutch oven.
Set aside until syrup forms.
Bring peach mixture to a boil; reduce heat to low, and cook 10 minutes or until tender.
Remove from heat; add extract and butter, stirring until butter melts.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Blend flour and milk together in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add butter, sugar, shortening and vanilla.
Beat with mixer until light and fluffy (about 10 minutes).
Store in refrigerator for several days or use right away.

title: cheddar cheese potato salad
