directions: In frying pan, cook chopped bacon over medium heat, stirring until crisp.
Remove bacon from pan with a slotted spoon and put into a large bowl.
Add the onion to pan and cook until limp.
Lift out with a slotted spoon; add to bacon.
Discard fat.
Add potatoes, eggs, cheese, mayonnaise and mustard to the bacon and stir until evenly mixed.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve or cover and chill overnight.
Yields 6 servings.

title: ernestine's favorite meringue(for 2 pies)
directions: Add water to egg whites and beat until foamy.
Add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, until egg whites are stiff.
Keep beating, adding 1 teaspoon cornstarch at a time until gone.
Put on 2 pies and bake at 400° for 5 minutes or until brown as desired.

title: cocoa cappuccino
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sweetened condensed milk, cocoa, butter and coffee.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until butter melts and mixture becomes smooth.
Remove from heat and cool.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Mix sauces, water, spinach and tomatoes.
Layer sauce, noodles and cheese.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Parmesan cheese. Serves 8.

title: divinity candy
directions: Combine sugar, water and syrup into 3-quart glass casserole. Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cook with microwave 5 minutes. Stir and cook about 5 to 6 minutes longer or until a hard ball is formed when tested in cold water.
While mixture is cooking, beat egg whites stiff.
When syrup is ready, pour it over the egg whites slowly, beating constantly with a wooden spoon.
Beat until creamy, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Add nuts, cherries and vanilla. Pour into a buttered pan.

title: yeast bread or rolls
directions: Use mixer.
Mix scalded milk, sugar, salt and butter.
Cool slightly.

title: quick "7 minute" frosting
directions: Put egg white, sugar, water, corn syrup and salt in top of double boiler.
Mix thoroughly and place over rapidly boiling water.
Beat until mixture will hold a peak (about 2 1/2 to 3 minutes).
Remove from over boiling water.
Add vanilla and beat until thick enough to spread (about one minute).
Makes enough frosting to cover tops of two 8 or 9-inch layers.

title: monkey nuts
directions: Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Put 3/4 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon of cinnamon in bag and shake pieces.
Arrange in tube pan.
Melt butter, 1/2 cup sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon. Pour mixture over top of pieces in tube pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: broccoli-chicken casserole
directions: Arrange cooked broccoli
in
x
13-inch pan or large flat casserole.
Cut
chicken
in
large
bite-size pieces and place over
broccoli.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise and lemon and pour over broccoli and chicken, then sprinkle with cheese, then crumbs and drizzle the melted butter over the top.
Bake, covered, at 350° about 1 hour, until bubbly and very hot.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Add 1/4 cup mixture to 6 ounces of hot water.
Mix well.
Top with marshmallows.

title: working girl's chewy butter cake
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9
x
2-inch pan.
Melt butter; cool. Add butter to 1 beaten egg.
Spread
mixture in pan and sprinkle with dry cake mix.
Blend cheese and remaining 2 eggs with sugar and pour over dry cake mix.
Bake
at
for 45 minutes.
When cool, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: one dish meal
directions: Cook beef, onion and pepper together until almost brown.
Cook macaroni until almost done.
Mix all together and pour in baking dish.
Bake at 350° until a little brown.
Can be frozen and eaten later.

title: pecan pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat together eggs, corn syrup, sugar, butter, vanilla and salt.
Arrange pecans on bottom of pie shell. Carefully pour egg mixture over pecans.
Bake on bottom rack of preheated oven set at 400° until knife comes out clean.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chopstick tuna
directions: Combine celery and onion in 1 1/2-quart ovenware oblong dish. Cook in microwave oven 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Add soup, 1 cup noodles, nuts, tuna and pepper.
Toss lightly.
Sprinkle remaining noodles over top.
Cook in microwave oven 4 1/2 to 5 1/2 minutes. Total cooking time: 7 minutes.
Recipe yields 6 servings.

title: garden chow-chow
directions: Grate cabbage, onions, peppers and tomatoes; add sugar and vinegar.
Cook until comes to boil, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat.
Put in jars.
Yield:
10 to 12 pints.

title: coconut and caramel pie
directions: Melt butter in large skillet, then add coconut and pecans. Cook until brown.
Set aside and let cool.
Combine cream cheese and condensed milk.
Beat until well mixed, then fold in Cool Whip. Put 1/4 cream cheese mixture in each pie shell.
Sprinkle each with 1/4 ounce pecan/coconut mix.
Layer caramel topping.
Repeat layering until all is used.
Wrap and freeze until firm.
This recipe yields 3 (9-inch) pies.
Tastes better when pie is frozen.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter in a 3-quart saucepan over medium-low heat.
Add

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Place sugar, milk, cocoa and Karo in boiler.
Bring to a rolling boil and boil for 2 1/2 minutes.
Take off stove and let it set for 5 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla; beat until it loses its gloss.
Add 1 cup pecans and pour into a buttered pan.

title: cheese and onion appetizer
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and put in 8 x 8 inch dish.	Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.
Sounds like a lot of onions but everyone will enjoy this appetizer.	So Easy To Make!

title: cheesy chicken spaghetti
directions: In large boiler, mix chicken, soups, cheese, and tomatoes. Heat on medium heat, stirring until cheese is melted.
Fold in spaghetti noodles.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Cut fryer in half.
Spray baking pan with Pam.
Place fryer halves in pan, skin side up.
Sprinkle generously with seasoned salt.
Cover.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour.

title: rum raisin cheesecake
directions: On hot chargrill, place fresh peppers to roast; brush with melted butter.
Turning frequently to prevent burning, brown all sides (this is to loosen the outer skins).
After cooking thoroughly, remove chilies and place them in damp, steamy warm towel.
Removing chilies from towel one at a time, peel skins, remove seeds and stems.
It is important to leave the roasted chilies in the towel until peeled because cold chilies are more difficult to peel.

title: cheese ball #1
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Form mixture into ball and roll in chopped nuts.
Serve with party rye bread.

title: true butterscotch pie
directions: Put the scant cup of white sugar, the butter and the salt into a heavy saucepan or iron skillet and brown (scorch) lightly, until sugar, etc. is melted.
Then pour in the hot water over the sugar mixture.
Let boil for a short time until all is well dissolved. Next, take the flour and mix in with the milk and the beaten egg yolk.
Pour this slowly (so will not curdle) into the sugar-syrup mixture.
Cook over low heat until pudding is thick and pour into an 8-inch baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue made from one's favorite recipe.

title: salmon chowder
directions: Remove skin and bones from salmon; crumble.
Set aside.
Peel and dice potatoes and carrot.
Put in the 3 cups water. Cook until tender.
Do not drain potatoes and carrots when they are cooked. Fry bacon in skillet until crispy and brown. Remove and drain. Put celery and onion in bacon grease and saute
until tender but not brown.
Remove and drain. Add celery and bacon to vegetables and water. Add the butter, half and half milk, salt, pepper, parsley and salmon and heat just until heated through.
Do not boil.

title: canned pineapple cake
directions: Put into bowl.
Beat all for 2 minutes and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce. Stir until melted.
Add pineapple, including juice and wine. Chill until partially set.
Add nuts and pour into mold.
Chill until set.

title: homemade hush puppies
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add onion, egg and milk.
Stir lightly. Drop by spoon in a skillet with hot grease.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain and serve hot.

title: great grandmother robinson's chocolate pie
directions: Scald milk on medium heat.
Mix together dry ingredients. Separate eggs.
Stir in about 2 tablespoons dry mixture with egg yolks so when added to the milk it will not curdle.
Add flour mixture to milk slowly and let get thick.
Add butter and vanilla while hot.
Pour into cooked pie crust.
Put meringue on and cook.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Layer broccoli in buttered casserole.
Put chicken on top of broccoli.
Mix soup, Miracle Whip, lemon juice and curry powder together.
Pour on top of chicken and broccoli.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Pour melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: rice salad
directions: Combine rice, pineapple, oranges, carrots, raisins and walnuts.
In separate bowl, combine milk, curry powder, and lemon juice.
Add mixtures together.
Add mayonnaise for added zing.

title: cold cucumber soup
directions: Salt onions and cucumbers.
Let stand in the refrigerator for 2 hours or overnight.
Add half and half and buttermilk to cucumber mixture; mix well.
Serve over hot potatoes.
Good on a hot summer day.

title: easy pepper steak
directions: Slice beef into very thin strips in skillet over medium heat in 1 tablespoon oil.
Brown beef; remove from stove.
Add pepper, onion and garlic powder.
Cook over medium heat until tender-crisp. Add gravy and Worcestershire sauce.
Return beef to pan; heat. Serve over rice.
Serves 4 people.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream shortening with brown and white sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Sift and add flour and soda.
Mix in oatmeal and nuts.
Form into long rolls and chill thoroughly.
Slice 1/4-inch thick and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: onion garlic bread
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread margarine mixture over bread slices.
Lightly sprinkle cheese over top of bread slices.
Broil bread for about 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 12 servings.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil water.
After water is boiled, add macaroni.
Let cook until soft.
Strain water.
Melt Velveeta in microwave.
Add cheese to macaroni.
Then stir and add salt and butter preferred to taste.

title: french bread
directions: Spoon flour into measuring cup and level off.
Pour onto wax paper.
Combine 2 cups flour, undissolved yeast, sugar and salt in large bowl.
Stir well to blend.
Add shortening.
Add hot tap water.
Beat with electric mixer at medium speed for 2 minutes. Scrape bowl occasionally.
Add 1 cup more flour.
Beat at high speed for 1 minute or until thick and elastic.
Gradually stir in just enough of remaining flour with wooden spoon to make a soft dough which leaves sides of bowl.
Turn out onto floured board. Knead 5 to 10 minutes or until dough is smooth and elastic. Cover with plastic wrap, then a towel.
Let rest 20 minutes on board.
Punch down.
Divide dough in half.
Roll each half into a 15 x 8-inch rectangle.
Roll up tightly, beginning with long side. Seal lengthwise edge and ends well.
Tuck ends under.
Taper ends gently with hands.
Place seam side down on baking sheets or thin French bread pan greased and sprinkled with cornmeal.
Brush dough lightly with oil.
Cover loosely with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 2 to 24 hours.

title: better than sex cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix cake mix, instant pudding, sour cream, eggs, water and oil well.
Add grated chocolate bar and mix again.

title: egg rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients, excluding wrappers, together.
Next, separate the wrappers and place them diamond-shaped in front of you.
Place one spoonful of the meat onto one side of one of the corners.
Beginning at that corner, fold the wrapper over the meat and roll until you get to the other corner.
Heat vegetable oil in a skillet.
Place a couple of rolls in the skillet.
Put on medium-high heat.
Fry until golden brown.
Serve with traditional Vietnamese sauce.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour; stir.
Add cheeses and milk; cook until thick and bubbly.
Stir in broccoli.
Place in casserole dish; top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: party cheese
directions: Work ingredients with hands to form into two balls.
Roll in paprika on waxed paper to cover balls.
Chill.
Spread on crackers or bread.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve at room temperature with crackers.

title: skillet candy
directions: Mix together and cook 10 minutes over medium heat:
butter, sugar, eggs and dates.
Remove from stove.
Add 1 cup pecans, Rice Krispies and vanilla; mix well.
Cool, then shape into balls.
Roll in coconut.

title: apple pie
directions: Make bread into crumbs in blender.
Grate cheese.
Place all bread crumbs, except 1 tablespoon in bowl.
Mix in cheese to form a ball.
Work ball to make dough with hands.
Form ball again. Roll out to form a crust, very thin.
Line small pie tie or muffin tin with dough.
Slice and peel apple.
Mix in sweetener and cinnamon.
Put apple mix in pie tin.
Melt butter, add remaining bread crumbs.
Stir to moisten crumbs.
Top each pie with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350°.

title: brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs.
Mix together.
Add flour, cocoa, salt, vanilla and nuts in order.
Mix thoroughly.
Place in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: spinach lasagna(made with uncooked lasagna noodles)
directions: In large bowl, mix Ricotta, 1 cup Mozzarella, egg, spinach, salt and oregano.

title: double chocolate crumble bars
directions: Cream
margarine
and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Stir together
flour,
nuts,
cocoa,
baking powder and salt. Stir in egg
mixture.
Spread
into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for
15 to
20 minutes until done.
Remove from oven and put marshmallows
on
top.
Bake additional 3 minutes.	Cool. In saucepan, melt chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Add Rice Krispies.
Spread on top.
Chill if you want to serve soon.

title: apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Prepare crust.
Peel, core and slice apples into crust.
Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt and sprinkle over apples.
Dot with butter.
Top with second crust; seal and cut vents for steam.
Brush crust with milk and sprinkle with sugar, if desired.
Bake 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate cloud kisses
directions: Beat egg whites and salt; add tartar and beat until stiff. Add sugar slowly and beat until mixture forms stiff peaks.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
Allow clouds to cool before removing from cookie sheet.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix first three ingredients well and form into 1-inch balls. Flatten and press a chocolate kiss into top of each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes on a greased cookie sheet.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 dozen.
These cookies are very rich and taste like Reese's cups.

title: frozen delight pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and yogurt.
Pour in pie shell.
Freeze 2 to 3 hours (overnight is best).
Serve.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Fry ground beef and drain.
Add kidney beans (drain off juice), cream of chicken and mushroom soups and enchilada sauce to ground beef on medium heat. Allow to simmer. Take Doritos and place in pan.
Pour ingredients over chips and top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Place in oven at 350°.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: 3 cheese vegetable lasagna
directions: In covered skillet, combine water, broccoli, carrots, Italian seasoning and garlic powder.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Drain.
Mix, in large bowl, the soup, 1/2 of Parmesan cheese, Ricotta and Mozzarella cheese.
Reserve 1 cup of cheese mixture.
Stir vegetables into remaining cheese mixture.

title: candy bar pie
directions: Make crust by combining graham crackers and melted butter. Shape crust in pie plate and bake 8 minutes at 375°.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Saute onions in butter until translucent.
Set aside to cool. Combine eggs, sour cream, salt, pepper and spice over low heat to blend well.
Combine with cooked onions.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with crumbled bacon.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 300° and bake until crust is light brown, about 30 minutes.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Put celery and onions in a small pan and cover with water; bring to boil.
Let simmer for 10 minutes.
Set aside while you prepare other ingredients, then add those to celery and onions.

title: graham cracker nut cake
directions: Note:
4 cups crumbs in 1 pound box of crackers.

title: classic beef stew
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown the beef, half at a time, in oil. Drain.
Return all meat to pan.
Add onion, tomatoes, beef broth, tapioca, garlic, parsley, salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil; remove from heat.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Stir in carrots, potatoes and celery.
Bake, covered, 1 hour longer or until meat and vegetables are tender.
Remove bay leaf before serving.
It can all be put together and baked for 2 hours. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: virginia's meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into a loaf.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
After meat loaf is cooked, take out of oven.
Mix 1 cup catsup and 1 tablespoon firmly packed brown sugar.
Pour over meat loaf.
Turn oven down to 200°.
Bake 20 minutes longer.

title: chicken strata
directions: Dry out bread slightly in oven.
Butter 4 slices; cut in 1/2-inch cubes and set aside.
Cut remaining bread in 1-inch cubes; place half of unbuttered cubes in bottom of ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine the next 7 ingredients; spoon over bread cubes.
Sprinkle remaining unbuttered cubes over chicken mixture. Combine eggs and milk; pour over all.
Cover and chill 1 hour or overnight.
Spoon soup over top.
Sprinkle with buttered cubes. Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes or until set.
Sprinkle cheese over top last few minutes of baking.
Makes 12 servings.

title: quick spinach salad
directions: Wash and dry spinach leaves; tear into bite-size pieces. Place in large bowl.
Add onion rings.
Just before serving, add cheese and salad dressing to taste.
Toss and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: garlic dip
directions: Blend well and chill overnight.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: cornbread
directions: In bowl, add meal and flour.
Stir.
Add egg and buttermilk. Mix well.
Put oil in skillet and pour mixture into skillet.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: calico salad
directions: Bring to boil first 3 ingredients and set aside to cool.
Mix dressing in bowl with lid.
When sugar mixture is cool, pour over vegetable mixture.
Mix well, cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: pineapple and cherry dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch oblong cake pan.
Spread each ingredient evenly into cake pan in the order given, one on top of another. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: In a frying pan, gently brown minced garlic in olive oil. Remove sausage meat from casing, crumble meat and fry also. In bowl, combine bread crumbs, cheese, parsley and egg.
Add cooked sausage.
Wash mushrooms quickly.
Remove stems.
Fill caps nicely with stuffing.
Place them in a baking pan lined with foil.
Add a little chicken stock to bottom of pan (5 to 6 tablespoons).
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: broken glass cake
directions: Dissolve each package of Jell-O separately in 1 1/2 cups hot water.
Pour each Jell-O into a shallow square pan and let sit in refrigerator overnight.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add melted oleo and sour cream.
Add corn and muffin mix.
Mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: southern corn bread
directions: Mix cornmeal, baking powder, salt and flour.
Then add milk and mix.
Add eggs and oil; stir.
Pour into greased preheated pan and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Add milk and all
ingredients
to beaten eggs.	Bake in greased baking dish for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel corn
directions: In a medium saucepan, cook all but the last 2 ingredients to the hard ball stage on the candy thermometer (270°).
Just before removing this from the heat, stir in the soda and butter.
Pour this hot mixture over popped corn which you keep warm in the oven. We usually made enough to fill a water-bath canning kettle 3/4 full.
Quickly stir the corn to coat evenly and turn out on a table to cool.
Store airtight.

title: mexican torte
directions: Brown ground beef or turkey, salt and pepper to taste and drain off excess fat.
Add to beef the medium salsa and tomatoes and simmer for 5 or 10 minutes.

title: cornish hens in wild rice and herb dressing
directions: Prepare wild rice according to box, using 1 can chicken broth combined with water to make enough liquid.
Cook only 20 minutes. When rice is finished, add stuffing mix and remaining chicken broth.
Stir until moist.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into a greased casserole dish and bake at 375° for 45 minutes. or until well set.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs lightly; add sugar, vanilla, oil and zucchini.
Sift dry ingredients; add to mix.
Add nuts.
Divide into 2 loaf pans, well-greased.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, soda and salt together.
Add eggs, fruit cocktail, oleo and vanilla. Mix well.
Pour into baking dish. Bake until firm, about 30 minutes, in 350° oven.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Combine broccoli and cauliflower together.
Add remaining ingredients and stir together.
Store in refrigerator.
Make the day before serving.

title: reese's bars
directions: Mix together and put in a 9 x 13 pan the first 4 ingredients. Melt chocolate chips and spread on top.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Brown meat and onion together with seasonings.
Add remaining ingredients, except tortillas, cook together for 1 hour.
Tear up tortillas in small pieces and add about 5 minutes before end of cooking time.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Spread over chicken breasts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Mix sausage, water, eggs, butter and stuffing mix thoroughly and chill.
Roll into 1-inch balls and wrap with 1/3 slice bacon.

title: sourdough pie crust
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda into bowl.
With 2 knives or pastry blender, cut in shortening.
Stir in sourdough starter with a fork; mix gently until dough sticks together and cleans sides of bowl.
Turn out onto floured pastry cloth and roll out lightly. Makes enough for a 2-crust pie or 2 pastry shells.

title: tuna loaves
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute in skillet with 4 tablespoons butter, onion, celery and parsley until onion is golden, about 5 minutes.
In large bowl, combine onion mixture with lemon juice, bread crumbs, hard-cooked eggs, pepper, tuna, salt and beaten eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
On lightly greased jelly roll pan, shape mixture into 8 loaves, using about 3/4 cup for each.
Use remaining butter to brush on top of loaves.
Bake for 25 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except eggs.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Grease Bundt or tube pan.
Pour in batter.
Bake in 350° preheated oven for 50 minutes.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Crust:
Combine Ritz crackers and margarine and press into 9 x 13-inch pan (reserve small amount for garnish).

title: pumpkin patch pie
directions: Place sherbet in bowl.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in half Cool Whip until well blended.
Spoon into crust.
Sprinkle with chopped Oreo cookies; press firmly into sherbet.
Cover with remaining Cool Whip.
Freeze 4 hours or until firm.
Let stand at room temperature 10 minutes before serving.
Garnish with finely chopped Oreos and candy pumpkins.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, brown sugar, eggs and salt.
Scant on spices.
Add milk.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 400° or 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Place thawed spinach in a strainer to drain.
In
a saucepan, melt margarine, stir in flour, add milk and cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Remove from
heat.
Beat egg substitute, add drained spinach, green onions, nutmeg and salt and pepper to taste.
Add to flour mixture.
In a large mixing bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Carefully fold spinach mixture into the egg whites.

title: orange delight salad
directions: Bring to a boil water with sugar.
Add jello.
Dissolve and add pineapple.
Let set
partially.
Fold
in 1 large Cool Whip, 1 cup grated Cheddar
cheese and 1/2 cup chopped pecans. Let congeal, better if overnight.

title: yummy chili bake
directions: Grease bottom of casserole dish.
Line with Fritos.
Layer with chili, then onion, then cheese.
Repeat, and be sure to top with extra cheese.
This is a good recipe for leftover chili.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all together and bake in casserole for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cry baby cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar, then molasses.
Add beaten eggs. Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Add alternately with coffee mixture.
Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° until golden.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Bake pastry 10 minutes at 450°.
Cream margarine, and brown sugar.
Stir in nuts.
Spread on bottom of pie shell.
Bake 5 minutes longer or until crust is golden.
Combine the 3/4 cup sugar, pumpkin pie spice, gelatin and salt in double boiler.
Stir in egg yolks, milk and pumpkin.
Cook over hot, not boiling, water, stirring for 15 minutes.
Chill until it starts to set.
Beat egg whites, adding 1 tablespoon sugar at a time until soft peaks form; set in pan of ice.
Beat pumpkin mixture until fluffy.
Gently fold into chilled meringue, still over ice.
Spoon into shell, making deep swirls on top with tip of spoon.
Decorate with a crown of whipped cream and more nuts.

title: sicilian casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, sausage, pepper and onion (drain grease).
Put 1/2 sauce in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in 1/2 pasta.
Add pepperoni.
Add mushrooms and 1/2 cheese.
Add rest of pasta, then rest of sauce.
Add remaining cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: glazed spiced nuts
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil.
Cook sugar, butter, orange juice and spices in large skillet.
Add nuts; toss to coat.
Spread in single layer on cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Let cool; transfer to foil.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, tossing lightly.
Put in covered dish and chill for 12 hours before serving.
Serves six generously.

title: old-fashioned soft sugar cookies
directions: Blend sugar, egg, salt and shortening together; add vanilla. Combine soda with buttermilk.
Sift together baking powder and flour.
Add buttermilk and flour mixtures alternately to sugar mixture.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or less.

title: bean bundles
directions: Place green beans on bacon slices in bunches of 6 to 8.
Wrap ends of bacon around bundles so that they cross over the tops of the bundles.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour dressing over beans.
Cover and chill 3 hours.
Bake, uncovered at 350° for 40 minutes, turning bundles over after 20 minutes. Remove from baking dish with slotted spoon before serving.

title: corn bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Stir cereal and milk in a large bowl. Let stand for 10 minutes.
Combine flour, cornmeal, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add beaten eggs, oil and vanilla to milk.
Whisk in brown sugar until smooth.
Add dry ingredients.
Spoon batter into prepared cups.
Bake 20 minutes, until toothpick comes out clean.

title: bread pudding
directions: Tear bread into small pieces in a big bowl.
Mix the rest of the ingredients with bread.
Pour into greased 9-inch cake pan and bake 30 minutes.
Dot with butter before putting into oven.
(You can add cinnamon to mixture.)

title: six-in-one cookies
directions: Dough:
Cream butter; gradually add sugars.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla, mix well. Sift together flour, soda and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture, beating well after each addition.

title: cream cheese apple dip
directions: In a bowl, cream together the cream cheese, sugars and vanilla.
Blend in peanuts.
Chill.
Serve with apple wedges.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: beef stew
directions: Cover meat with water in a large
pan.
Bring to a boil, then reduce and simmer until meat is tender. Add cut up onion and cover pan.
Peel the potatoes and carrots and cut into small pieces. Add to meat and continue cooking about 30 to 45 minutes until meat and vegetables are tender.
When ready to serve, add a can of peas, drained and heated.

title: sugar and spice pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water until frothy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir in nuts.
Spread on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 200° for 45 minutes.
Stir often.

title: chicken and biscuits and gravy
directions: Heat oven to 425° (hot).
Mix Bisquick, salt, pepper and paprika in a paper bag.
Place shortening in pan to melt.
Shake 3 to 4 pieces of chicken in the bag to coat thoroughly. Bake skin side down for 45 minutes. Turn over.

title: mr. kraker beans
directions: Place
all
ingredients
in
crock-pot and cook 4 hours with top on and 1 hour with top off on low heat.

title: peanut butter swirls
directions: Combine margarine and brown sugar in a medium bowl; add egg substitute.
Beat with electric mixer (or by hand) until thoroughly combined, then add vanilla and beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to sugar mixture, stirring well.
Divide batter in half.
Stir in cocoa into 1 half and stir peanut butter into the other half (peanut butter mixture will be thick).
Spoon dollops of each batter alternately into a 9-inch square pan coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Cut through batter in pan with a knife to create a swirled pattern.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted in the middle comes out clean. Remove from oven and let cool completely on wire rack.
Yields 16 brownies; 162 calories, 4.5 g fat.

title: mushroom cheeseburger casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 2-quart baking dish.
Cook meat and onions in large skillet until beef is browned and onions tender.
Stir in mushrooms, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and 2 tablespoons baking mix.
Set aside.

title: oven crusted chicken
directions: Flatten the chicken slightly with kitchen mallet.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cook before putting into baked pie crust.
Add meringue and brown.
Sprinkle coconut on top of meringue.

title: baked custard
directions: Mix well.
Bake in buttered custard cups at 300° until done. Place in pan of water in the oven to bake.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: apple burritos
directions: Cook apples in apple juice concentrate slowly until tender. Set apples aside and heat pineapple juice and thicken with cornstarch mixed with a little water to make a paste.
Cook until clear and bubbly, stirring.
Fold 1 cup pineapple thickened juice into cooked apples.
Place 1/3 cup apples on center of each tortilla.
Roll tortilla and place seam side down in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan sprayed with vegetable spray.
Cover with remaining pineapple juice.
Bake, covered, at 350° for about 20 minutes until heated through.
Serve hot or cold.
You may add raisins or nuts, if desired.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Put cucumbers, pepper and onions in a mixing bowl.
Boil sugar, vinegar, mustard seed and celery seed together and then let cool.
Pour this mixture over cucumbers and let stand overnight. Put cucumbers into containers and freeze.

title: cream of carrot soup
directions: Melt butter.
Add vegetables, garlic and rice; mix well over gentle heat for 5 minutes without browning.
Add parsley, peeled orange rind, stock, sugar and seasonings; bring to boil.
Lower heat; simmer 30 to 40 minutes, until vegetables are tender.
Put into electric blender or food processor and blend until smooth.
Or put through food mill.
Return to pot; reheat, adding orange juice. If not thick enough, add cream and egg yolks.
Mix egg yolks and cream well.
Add few spoons hot soup.
Strain back into soup; stir constantly.

title: reuben sandwiches
directions: Combine ingredients in a casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve on cocktail rye bread.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add soaked gelatin.
Add cranberry sauce, pineapple, celery and nuts.
Serves 10.
(Doubled goes in 3-quart casserole.)

title: apple cake
directions: Cream together the eggs, sugar, and salt.
Add oil and beat until light and fluffy.
Blend in vanilla, flour, cinnamon, and baking soda.
Mix by hand.
Add nuts and apples.
Blend thoroughly.
Add the last cup of flour (there are 3 cups of flour altogether in the cake).
Mix well.
Bake at 350°.
Use 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Chill unopened can of milk for 3 to 4 hours.
Dissolve jello in hot water; chill until partly set.
Whip until light and fluffy.
Add lemon juice and sugar.
Whip milk and fold into jello mix.
Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with crumbs.
Pour mixture over and top with remaining crumbs.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares and serve with whipped cream.

title: alligator dip
directions: Stir all ingredients together and let set overnight.
Take top off bread, tear out bread in bite-size pieces to dip.
Place dip inside shell at last minute.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into mixing bowl.
Add butter or margarine, 1/2 cup milk and vanilla, using fold/dry on mixer to moisten ingredients, then mix cycle for 2 minutes.
Scrape bowl sides and bottom.
Add remaining milk and egg yolks; mix cycle for 2 minutes.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serve with confectioners sugar on top.

title: eagle brand milk
directions: Mix at high speed until thick.
Equals 1 can.

title: chicken souffle
directions: Cut crust from bread, crumble and place in bottom of well greased 9x13 baking dish.
Combine chicken, onions, celery, peppers, mayo, salt & pepper and spread on top of crumbled crusts. Fit slices of bread on top of chicken mixture.
Mix beaten eggs with milk and pour over bread slices.
Let stand a few minutes. Spread un-diluted soup over bread.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Uncover and bake 50 minutes at 325°.
Add grated cheese.
Sprinkle over top and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir peanut butter, sugar and eggs in bowl until blended.
Roll tablespoonfuls into 1 1/4-inch balls. Place 1 1/2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 12 to 14 minutes, until cookies look dry and tops are crackled. Remove from oven and immediately press a chocolate kiss in center of each.
Cool on cookie sheet for 1 to 2 minutes, then remove to wire racks to cool.
